title: federal bread(this is a civil war recipe)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, lemon extract and eggs. Beat well.
Stir in flour, soda and buttermilk.
Batter is very stiff.
Place in greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients into crumbs.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs.
Pour water, syrup and soda over the crumbs in the bowl. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with the reserved crumbs. Bake at 350° for approximately 50 to 60 minutes.
Test with toothpick to be sure not to overbake.

title: salad dressing for broccoli and mushroom salad
directions: Mix and add to salad just before serving.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Place chicken in Dutch oven.
Salt and paprika to taste.
In large bowl, mix soup, wine and mushrooms and pour over chicken. Cook uncovered in oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove chicken and add sour cream to sauce.
Place sauce over medium to low heat and simmer until well heated.
Serve rice with chicken and use sauce as a gravy.

title: watergate cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, put the cake mix.
Blend in oil, eggs and 7-Up, beating a little after each addition.
When all is blended, fold in dry pistachio pudding mix, nuts and coconut.
Pour into a Bundt cake pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Frost with Cover Up Frosting after the cake has cooled.

title: fish cakes or pudding
directions: Remove all bones and skin from fish.
Cut fish into small chunks and mince in food processor or blender.
While blending, add flour and salt, then gradually add cream and milk.
Dough should be light and fluffy.
Add spices.
Form mixture into small flat cakes and brown in greased pan until golden on both sides.

title: marinated zucchini salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; stir well. Add vegetables; cover and marinate in refrigerator several hours or overnight.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add 2 cups flour and 1 teaspoon soda. Stir in 2 cups fruit cocktail, until well blended.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped nuts on top of batter.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: skillet hominy
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on toweling and crumble.
Pour off all drippings except 1 tablespoon.
Add onion, green pepper and hominy.
Cook gently.
Stir often until onion is yellow.
Beat eggs and add pepper.
Pour over hominy mixture.
Sprinkle with bacon. Cover and cook gently until eggs are set.
Sprinkle with cheese. Cover and let stand off heat until eggs are done and cheese melts.

title: steak marinade
directions: Score steak in crisscross pattern on both sides.
Combine ingredients in shallow pan.
Marinate, covered, for several hours or overnight.
Turn occasionally.
Grill or broil as desired.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk.
Blend good.
Add whipped topping.
Pour into crust.
Top with Cool Whip, drizzled chocolate and chopped nuts.

title: pumpkin rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Will be thin.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put wax paper on greased pan.
Pour mix on wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
When done, turn on dish towel while hot. Peel off wax paper.
Roll long ways.
Let completely get cold and unroll.

title: baked pork steak and rice
directions: Brown the pork steak or chops.
Salt and pepper.
Mix the soup with the water.
Add the rice to the soup mixture.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch pan and place pork steak over this. Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: quick triple chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour oil into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Tilt pan until bottom is covered with oil.
Put remaining ingredients into pan.
Stir with a fork or spoon until well blended (about 2 minutes).
Scrape sides and spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until toothpick in center comes out clean.
When cool, sprinkle with confectioners sugar or frost with Cool Whip.

title: spaghetti with meatballs
directions: Use 2 medium pans for boiling.
Mix hamburger, egg and onion soup mix.
Make meatballs, drop into 1 of the pans of water.
Boil until meat is brown.
Put noodles into other pan of boiling water. After meat is brown, drain water, add sauce and let simmer until noodles are done.
Mix together.

title: baby pineapple chicken
directions: Combine boiled or baked meat in a blender with canned or fresh pineapple.
If using canned, strain the drained juice.
Mix with water for a great drink!

title: spiced cider
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients until sugar dissolves and mixture is well heated.
Add cider, stirring well.
Add applejack, if desired.
Strain and serve.

title: rise to the top crust
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk together and pour over margarine.
Mix fruit and vanilla with sugar.
Pour over flour mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Crust will rise to the top.

title: curried pumpkin soup
directions: In large saucepan, saut the onion in butter until tender. Stir in flour and curry powder until blended.
Gradually add broth.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Add pumpkin, milk, honey, salt, pepper and nutmeg; heat through.
Serve garnished with fresh chives, if desired. Makes 6 servings.

title: pizza spaghetti casserole
directions: Melt 1 stick of margarine in
9 x 13-inch pan.
Toss cooked spaghetti in butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Layer on top of spaghetti 8 ounces Mozzarella, mushrooms, pepperoni slices, spaghetti sauce and 8 ounces Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly at 350°.
Let set for 15 to 20 minutes before cutting.

title: busy day steak casserole
directions: Mix soups with sherry and onion soup mix and pour over meat in a deep casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours, covered.
Serve over your choice of rice, potatoes or noodles.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in casserole dish. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Peel and mash avocados until smooth.
Add onions.
Begin layering in 2-inch deep dish or oblong glass casserole dish. Layer in order: bean dip, avocado/onion mixture, sour cream, salsa, grated cheese, sprinkle black olives.
Serve cold with naco chips.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and onions, cook on top of stove.
Drain. Shred 1 pound Cheddar cheese.
Add butter (to taste), salt, pepper and milk.
Mix together, add to potatoes.
Place in 325° to 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and cook all day in slow cooker. One hour before finished, you may remove cover. Stir in sour cream 15 minutes before serving. Serve over noodles.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix all together and pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with nuts, if desired.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Thoroughly mix dry ingredients.
Stir in buttermilk, eggs and molasses, just until moist.
Grease or line muffin cups and fill about 2/3 full with batter.
Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: crusty baked catfish
directions: Thaw catfish if frozen.
Rinse in cold water.
Pat dry with paper towel.
Mix milk and mustard.
Dip catfish in the mixture. Roll dipped fish in minced pecans.
Place into a shallow, buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 400° 10 to 12 minutes.
Garnish with lemon wedges, if desired.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and bacon.
Mix together Miracle Whip, sour cream and lemon juice.
Pour over salad and toss well to coat.

title: world's most delicious cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together butter and sugars; add egg.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients, one at a time, except pecans.
Mix until combined.
Stir in pecans.
Form dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Do not overcook.
Allow to cool a few minutes before removing from pan.
Sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Makes approximately 6 dozen cookies.
Each cookie has 113 calories.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine fruit slices, cinnamon, cloves and water in large non-aluminum saucepan. Bring to boil and boil 5 minutes. Press mixture through a strainer; discard pulp and spices. Add pineapple juice, sugar and tea to citrus mixture. Stir well; serve hot. Yield: about 2 gallons.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine undrained pineapple, flour, egg, sugar and extract in casserole.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt butter or margarine in skillet.
Add cubed bread and brown lightly. Spread over pineapple mixture and bake 35 to 40 minutes longer. This is not a dessert.
Serve with ham.

title: italian beef
directions: Dissolve seasoning in water.
Put roast in crock-pot, pour water over roast.
Cook slowly 8 to 10 hours until tender.
Slice beef and serve on Vienna bread or kaiser buns.

title: white sauce
directions: Melt butter to bubbling; add flour.
Whip until smooth.
Add milk, cooking and stirring until it thickens.
Add touch of sherry.
Using wire whip, add Swiss cheese and whisk until melted.

title: homemade granola
directions: Spread the oatmeal on a cookie sheet and heat in a 35° oven for 10 minutes.
Combine all but the last two ingredients.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet or pan for 20 minutes, stirring once to brown evenly, and allow mixture to cool in oven.
Add wheat germ and raisins.
Refrigerate in glass jars or plastic containers.

title: never fail icebox rolls
directions: Soak warm water and yeast.
Cream together sugar, salt, shortening and egg.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over mixture.
Mix together well.
Let mixture cool and add yeast mixture.
Add 4 cups all-purpose flour.
Refrigerate dough 2 hours before ready to use. Take out of refrigerator and put into rolls.
Let rise 2 hours. Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Makes about 18 rolls.

title: tasty-cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together, then add next 2 ingredients. Pour into a greased and floured jelly roll pan or cookie sheet. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
When done, spread with peanut butter.
Let cool.
Melt Hershey bar in top of double boiler. Spread over peanut butter on cake.

title: italian spaghetti(feeds 15)
directions: Put butter in pan.
Brown meat until it falls apart.
Add onions and peppers.
Cook and add tomatoes.
Cook until it is fairly thick.
Combine with spaghetti and grated cheese.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in shortening.
Add pimento, mushrooms, crab meat and shrimp.
Heat; stir in seasoning, rice and soup.
Place into buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with almonds. Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: won ton soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together in small bowl.
Take the won ton skins.
Place 1 teaspoon mixture in the center.
Make a triangle; turn top triangle to meet fold.
Now, moisten the edges with water and cornstarch; press to seal.
Take corners and twist, then overlap.
Dust each won ton with cornstarch and set aside, until ready to drop into your soup, or freeze each won ton separately. After frozen, put all your won tons in freezer bags and use them as needed.

title: harvard beets
directions: Heat beet juice, sugar, cornstarch, vinegar and butter together until boiling, stirring constantly. Add beets to hot mixture. A bit of cinnamon is good (optional).

title: fried eggplant
directions: Select a nice, firm eggplant, free of blemishes.
Peel and slice.
(Slice anyway you please, round, shoestring or wedges, etc.).
Soak at least 15 to 20 minutes (longer if preferred) in very salty water.
Drain and pat dry.
Mix onion, eggs and enough cornmeal and flour to make a batter.
Dip eggplant in batter and fry in hot grease, being careful not to burn grease.
(Always use fresh shortening or oil.)
Serve at once.
Serves a large family.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugars, beating at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; stir well.
Add to creamed mixture, beating well.
Stir in nuts.
Shape dough into two 10-inch rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and chill at least 8 hours.
Unwrap rolls and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool on wire rack.
Makes 6 1/2 dozen.

title: carolina soup
directions: Put milk in top of double boiler with mace and lemon peel; allow to simmer for a few minutes.
Add crab, butter and cream; cook for 15 minutes.
Thicken with cracker crumbs; season with salt and pepper.
Allow to stand on back of stove for a few minutes to bring out the flavor.
Just before serving, add sherry.

title: almond frosting
directions: Beat powdered sugar, butter and almond extract 4 to 5 minutes. Tint with food coloring.

title: sunday-go-to meetin' casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix corn, crushed crackers and eggs in baking dish; cover the top with bacon slices.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: buttered baby peas and carrots julienne
directions: Prepare peas as directed on package.
Meanwhile, in medium saucepan, bring carrots and water to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 8 to 11 minutes or until carrots are crisp-tender; drain.
Stir in peas and butter sauce.

title: rose's cheese ball(serves 10 to 25)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into a ball and roll ball over pecans reserved for garnishing.
Can be made ahead of time.

title: chocolate chip applesauce cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add shortening, applesauce, eggs, 1/2 cup of walnuts, 1/2 cup chocolate chips and raisins.
Beat until smooth.
Pour batter into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: fabulous cheese casserole
directions: In a 2-quart greased casserole, put a layer of bread cubes, a layer of cheese and 1/3 of the onion.
Make 2 more layers and sprinkle with salt and pepper; press down firmly.
Beat eggs lightly and add to milk along with the mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over bread cubes and place in the refrigerator at least 8 hours or overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 2 hours before baking to allow to come to room temperature.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour until it has risen to top (or over) of side of dish. Serve at once.

title: macaroni bake
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13 pan.
Stir in macaroni until coated well with butter.
Add salt and pepper.
Chunk Velveeta cheese on top of macaroni.
Pour on milk.
Don't stir.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: butternut squash pie
directions: Mix sugar and spices together.
Mix into squash.
Add eggs and milk.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 450° for 15 minutes and 350° for 30 minutes.
(Squash is better if steamed instead of cooked in water.)

title: french dressing
directions: Put everything in blender on puree for 1 to 2 minutes.

title: steak and bacon tornedos
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: ziti bake
directions: Preheat spaghetti sauce.
Meanwhile, in 8-quart Dutch oven, prepare ziti macaroni as label directs; drain.
Set aside.

title: new england squash pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt, spices and egg.
Add to squash.
Add evaporated milk to this.
Pour squash mixture into pie shell. Bake at 400° until knife comes out clean, approximately 45 to 50 minutes.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Boil the 3 fryers for 45 minutes.
Remove from stock.
Cool and remove meat from bones.
Refrigerate stock overnight.
Skim fat off top of chilled stock.
Brown and drain the hamburger and pork.

title: five layer cream cheese pie
directions: First Layer:
Mix butter and flour; spread into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: susan's pizza casserole
directions: Put brown hamburger in casserole dish.
Add jar of pizza sauce.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Mix together Bisquick, milk and eggs.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: no fat vegetable soup
directions: Add onion and celery to V-8 juice.
Cook until tender.
Add all other vegetables.
Cook to desired consistency.
Add any seasoning you may prefer, like thyme, oregano, basil and bay leaves.
Makes 8 servings.
Calories, 108.
Fat 0 grams. 0% fat.

title: raisin sauce for baked ham
directions: Bring sugar and water to boil in a 1-quart saucepan.
Add raisins, butter, vinegar, spices and jelly.
Stir over low heat until jelly is dissolved.
Dissolve cornstarch in water.
Add to sauce and heat until raisins are plump and sauce begins to thicken. Serve warm with holiday baked ham.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Mix vegetables and mayonnaise and pour in casserole.
Top with crackers, mixed with butter.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.
(One cup grated cheese may be added, if desired.)

title: patsy's quiche
directions: In 9-inch pie plate sprayed with Pam, layer chopped jalapeno peppers, chopped onion, sliced mushrooms (optional) and grated cheese. Pour beaten eggs over all. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: sicilian meat roll
directions: Combine eggs, bread crumbs, tomato juice, parsley, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic.
Stir in ground beef and mix well.
On foil or waxed paper, pat meat into a 12 x 10-inch rectangle. Arrange ham slices atop meat, leaving a small margin around edges. Sprinkle shredded cheese over ham.
Starting from short end, carefully roll up meat using foil to lift; seal edges and ends. Place roll, seam side down, in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Place cheese wedges over top of roll.
Return to oven 5 minutes or until cheese melts. Serves 8.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken in seasoned water.
Debone and chop.
Cook rice in chicken broth with slightly less liquid than called for in package directions.
Mix chicken and cooked rice with remaining ingredients.
Place in large casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika and chopped parsley.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: charion's pasta and veggie delight
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package.
Boil or steam vegetables. Drain pasta and veggies.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot.

title: orange peach marmalade
directions: Peel and slice firm peaches.
To each cup of peaches, add 1 cup sugar.
For 5 cups peaches, allow 1 orange sliced very thin.
Let these stand 2 hours.
Boil; stir frequently until syrup is heavy. Delicious with Scottish Scones.

title: banquet potatoes
directions: Mix all together except 1/2 the butter.
Place in ungreased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Top with corn flakes and remainder of butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: country fried steak
directions: Flour cube steaks and brown in frying pan. Cut potatoes and carrots and
place	in
casserole
dish.
Salt
and pepper carrots and potatoes
to taste.
Place each steak over carrots and potatoes.
Sprinkle
package
of
soup
mix
over carrots, potatoes and steaks.
Pour	3/4
glass
of	water in casserole dish. Cover dish with glass top or aluminum foil. Bake at 425° for 45 minutes or until carrots and potatoes are tender.

title: yummy amish supper
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef; salt and pepper to taste.
Add onion.
Drain.
Add tomato soup to meat.
Stir thoroughly.

title: chicken veronique
directions: Combine crumbs, tarragon, salt, pepper and chives and coat chicken.
Melt half of butter in frying pan and brown chicken. Remove to casserole dish.
Add onions and mushrooms and saute. Then add chicken stock and wine and bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken, cover and bake about 30 minutes or until done.
Add grapes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tuna log
directions: Mix first six ingredients.
Chill for an hour or longer. Shape mixture into a log.
Combine pecans and parsley.
Roll tuna log in nut mixture.
Serve with crackers.

title: catfish parmesan
directions: Thaw frozen fish.
Clean, wash and dry fish.
Combine breadcrumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley, paprika, oregano, basil, salt and pepper.
Dip catfish in butter and roll in crumb mixture.

title: asparagus in wine
directions: Snap off and discard tough ends from asparagus; wash asparagus. In wide frying pan, bring 1/2-inch salted water to a boil.
Add asparagus; cover and cook over medium heat until tender-crisp when pierced (5 to 7 minutes).
Drain well and turn into a shallow 3 to 4 cup casserole.
Melt butter in frying pan over high heat; add wine and cook, uncovered, until reduced by about half.
Pour butter-wine sauce over asparagus.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste, then with cheese.
Place under broiler, 2 to 3-inches from heat until cheese melts (about 2 minutes).

title: oriental salad
directions: Mix oil, sugar, flavor package and vinegar for dressing. Layer cabbage, almonds and sunflower kernels in serving bowl. Just before serving, crumble noodles on top and pour dressing over.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cottage cheese and cream cheese.
Add taco mix and Tabasco sauce; mix well.
Spread on plate.
Layer lettuce, tomatoes and shredded cheese.
Sprinkle sliced olives on top.
Serve as dip with nacho chips.

title: chili
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces and fry in medium-size pot.
Add diced onion.
Fry well.
Add chopped meat, salt and pepper and brown.
Add tomatoes and cook on low for 1 1/2 hours.
Add kidney beans and cook 1/2 hour more.
Add chili powder.
Serve with shredded cheese and raw onion, if desired.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup of water.
Add small can of pineapple, nuts and strawberries. Cut bananas up on top of salad. Refrigerate and after salad has congealed, spread sour cream on top.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Slice apples and put in salt water to keep from discoloring.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Put together as they come, except put the cheese on top of the Tater Tots.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: creamy kale
directions: Drain off most of the liquid from the kale.
Add salt and pepper.
Heat slowly until very hot. Drain again.
While greens are warming, mix the sour cream, mayonnaise and lemon juice together. Fold this sauce into well drained greens.
Heat a minute longer.
Serve at once. Serves 3.

title: everlasting muffins
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add nuts, soda, cinnamon and salt; blend well.
Add applesauce alternately with flour.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes (2 minutes in microwave).
Makes about 50 muffins or 100 small muffins.

title: mac and cheese casserole
directions: Mix together and let stand overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: latkes (potato pancakes)(makes 12 pancakes; breakfast-brunch)
directions: In medium bowl, combine eggs, flour, onion and pepper; set aside. Pat shredded potatoes with paper towel. Stir into egg mix. In skillet over medium-high heat, melt 1 1/2 tablespoons margarine. For each pancake, spoon 1/3 cup potato mixture into skillet, spreading to 4-inch circle. Cook 5 to 6 minutes, turning over once to brown both sides. Remove and keep warm. Repeat to make a total of 12 pancakes, using remaining margarine as needed. Garnish as desired (raspberry sauce swirl is nice or serve in circle topped with applesauce or dab applesauce on top or serve with applesauce in small bowl in center of pancakes).

title: pasta e fagioli
directions: In frypan with small amount of water, one teaspoon olive oil and garlic, fry the sausage.
Transfer to large pot.
Add remaining oil, sauce, pepper, salt and bay leaves.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Add 4 cups of water.
Bring to a boil.
Add macaroni, stirring slowly.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add beans with liquid and reduce to simmer.
Remove and discard bay leaves.
If not loose enough, add more water.

title: sweet potato and banana casserole
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Place in a large saucepan with salt.
Add boiling water to cover.
Boil for 30 to 35 minutes.
When they are ready, cut into 1/4-inch thick slices.

title: amber's cupcakes
directions: You will also need cupcake liners.
Replace water with milk. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake as directed.
Cool, then frost.

title: green chili chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except 1 cup cheese.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with cheese.
Heat at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips and white almond bark in microwave.
Add peanuts. Spoon out on wax paper and cool.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Place chicken in greased baking pan; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place kraut over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Pour dressing over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Add to mixture of other ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.

title: popeye power
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into a baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until it starts to bubble and browns around the outer edges.

title: aunt ruby's chicken-asparagus casserole
directions: Place asparagus in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Slice eggs over asparagus.
Cover with chicken, cut in chunks.
Mix soup, cheese, mayonnaise and lemon juice together.
Spread soup mix over eggs and asparagus.
Crumble crackers and mix crumbs with margarine.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Shake paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: With mixer, blend the first 5 ingredients together.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread 1 package of crescent rolls flat, cutting to fit the pan.
Spread cream cheese mixture over flat pastry. Spread second package of crescent rolls over mixture.
Brush with egg white.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and refrigerate for 1 hour before cutting. Keep in refrigerator.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish and then add all other ingredients. Put lid on dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: baked applesauce
directions: Mix and cook over medium heat until thick, the first 6 ingredients.
Put applesauce in baking dish and pour mixture over it.
Place graham cracker crumbs on the top with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: eggs benedict with fresh herb hollandaise
directions: Preheat a griddle.
Brush the muffins with the butter. Place the muffins on the hot griddle and pan-fry for 2 minutes on each side. Remove the muffins from the griddle and set aside.

Heat a skillet over medium heat. Add the ham steak and sear for a couple of minutes on each side. Remove the ham steaks and cut into 8 portions. Bring a pot of salted water and the vinegar to a boil. Slide the whole eggs into the water, one at a time. When the water returns to a boil, reduce the heat to low and simmer until the eggs are set. Watch carefully and remove the eggs while the yolks are still soft, about 2 to 2 1/2 minutes. Remove the eggs from the water and drain on a paper-lined plate. Season the eggs with salt and pepper.

title: 4 day pickles
directions: Fill glass gallon jar with whole clean cucumbers.
Dissolve salt in warm water; pour over cucumbers.
Let it stand 24 hours. Pour off brine.
Dissolve 3/4 alum in hot water.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let it stand 24 hours.
Pour off brine.
Put cucumbers in clear water for 24 hours.
Boil vinegar and water with cloves for 20 minutes.
Tie cloves in bag while boiling.
Pour this mixture in over cucumbers.
Let it stand 24 hours.
Pour off vinegar.
Rinse cukes.
Put layer of sugar in jar.
Slice cukes in 1 layer, then put sugar, then cukes.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Mix jello, sweetener
and cornstarch together in saucepan. Add the water and bring
to full boil.
Pour over strawberries in pie shell.	Chill and
top	with
Cool Whip Lite or vanilla yogurt if desired.

title: relish dish
directions: He criticized her pudding.

title: bread pudding
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam.
Pour bread crumbs in baking dish. Beat eggs, milk, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over bread crumbs and sprinkle top with nuts.
Bake in water that has been added in pan; sit baking dish in water.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl, combine sugar and flour. Stir in corn syrup. Whisk in eggs. Stir in pecans, evaporated milk and vanilla. Pour into frozen pie crust. Bake in preheated 350° oven on preheated baking sheet for 50 minutes or until firm. Cool on wire rack. Makes 8 servings.

title: microwave cheese scalloped potatoes
directions: Gradually stir milk into soup in 2-quart casserole.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes; stir.
Cover and cook until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: oriental dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well and store in refrigerator.

title: low-fat taco dip
directions: Mash black beans and spread in oblong pan.
Pour over picante sauce.
Layer first lettuce, onion, tomatoes then spread over sour cream.
Sprinkle with cheese, chill or eat while beans are warm. Serve with corn chips.
This recipe actually has no fat in it, depending on the chip you serve with it.

title: greek-baked lamb with orzo
directions: Place chops in 10-cup gratin dish or large baking dish. Sprinkle lamb with oil, lemon juice and salt and pepper to taste. Turn chops to coat evenly.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, turning once.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Add wine, cinnamon stick, onions and garlic.
Bake until meat is still pink inside (but not red) when cut, about 15 minutes longer.
(Meat will cook more later.)
Remove chops.
Cut meat from bones, keeping meat in large pieces and reserving bones.
Reserve meat on plate and cover.
Return bones to pan and stir.
Continue baking until onions are tender, 10 minutes. Discard cinnamon stick and bones.
Add tomato sauce, oregano and 2 cups boiling water to pan.
Season well with salt and pepper.
Stir in orzo.
Bake 20 minutes without stirring.
Set meat pieces on top in 1 layer and press gently into mixture.
Bake until orzo is tender but firm to the bite and meat is done to taste, 10 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve immediately from dish.
Serves 6.

title: sugar pecans
directions: Beat egg white stiff.
Fold in brown sugar and vanilla. Stir in pecans.	Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 200° for 30 minutes.

title: pinacbet
directions: Boil 1/2 to 1 cup water in a saucepan.
Drop the pork, tomatoes, garlic, ginger and bagoong.
Simmer until pork is tender.
Add the ampalaya and eggplants and cook until done. Season with ajinomoto and salt, if necessary.

title: today's pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Shake flour in oven bag; place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Add tomatoes, soup mix and pepper.
Squeeze bag to blend ingredients. Trim fat from roast; place roast in bag. Turn bag to coat roast with sauce.
Place vegetables in bag around roast. Close bag with nylon tie; cut 6 half-inch slits in top. Bake until roast is tender, 1 1/2 to 2 1/4 hours. Let stand in bag 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sugar-free spice loaf
directions: Boil raisins and water together until water boils out, leaving about 1 Tablespoon
in pan.
Mix together with egg, oil, powdered sweetener, vanilla, soda, self-rising flour, sugar-free applesauce, cinnamon, nutmeg and nuts.
Mix all together and bake in loaf pan at 350 degrees until done.

title: carrot bread
directions: Sift together first 6 ingredients.
Combine with carrots, applesauce, walnuts or pecans and eggs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tomato aspic jello
directions: Mix well.
After almost set, mix again.
Chill until set.

title: apple bacon salad
directions: Prepare rice according to directions on package.
Meanwhile, heat water to boiling in a medium saucepan.
Add green beans and cook 2 minutes over high heat.
Add broccoli and cook 1 to 2 minutes more, until vegetables are tender crisp.
Drain and rinse under cold water.
In medium skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add garlic and cook 30 seconds, then add chicken and cook, stirring frequently, 3 to 4 minutes until chicken is no longer pink.
Remove from heat and add soy sauce, orange zest, orange juice and honey; toss to coat chicken.
In large bowl, combine cooked rice, broccoli, green beans and chicken mixture.
Stir in carrots, red pepper and green onions; toss to coat.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: scottish scones
directions: Knead together 4 or 5 times.
Pat dough out into an 8-inch square on floured surface.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar, mixed with 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Cut diagonally into 16 triangles.
Bake in 375° oven about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: butter tarts
directions: Cream butter and add brown sugar, soak raisins in boiling water until edges of raisins begin to turn white. Drain raisins. Combine and mix all ingredients well. Fold in drained raisins. Fill 24 medium tarts. Bake at 350° until golden brown. Enjoy.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together cornmeal, buttermilk and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir together.
Pour into greased iron skillet and bake in 350°
oven for 1 hour.

title: golabki (cabbage rolls)
directions: Remove core from cabbage.
Scald cabbage in boiling water and remove leaves as they soften.
Saute onions in margarine very lightly; do not brown.
Combine with the meat, rice, eggs and seasonings.
Mix well.
Place 2 tablespoons of mixture in center of cabbage leaf and roll.
Wrap and push sides of roll in with finger to hold together.
Pour tomato sauce on rolls, then squeeze tomatoes from can and arrange on top of rolls.
Simmer over low heat for 2 hours in a heavy soup pot.

title: traditional adobe or pork in vinegar and soy sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients except cooking oil, in a pot and let stand for about 30 minutes.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Drain and reserve sauce.
Heat cooking oil in skillet.
Brown meat on all sides.
Transfer to a serving dish. Pour off all remaining oil from skillet.
Add reserved sauce and cook for a minute or two, scraping all brown bits sticking to pan. Pour sauce over meat and serve.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix cake mix, melted butter and 2 eggs.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: no crust pumpkin pie
directions: Mix well. Pour into 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
On medium speed of electric mixer, beat the eggs.
Add milk and heavy cream; beat to blend.
Add butter, orange rind, sugar and 3/4 cup coconut, mixing until blended. Pour into pie shell; sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, or until custard is well set.
Cool before serving.

title: escalloped cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water with salt and sugar 4 minutes. Drain well.
Make sauce with butter, flour and milk.
Put cabbage in casserole.
Pour sauce over cabbage.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: party cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar; beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together.
Add to the sugar and egg mixture; mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's.
Reserve remaining candies for decorating.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate top of cookies with remaining M&M's.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter. Cook macaroni as instructed on package. In large container, mix cheese, pimento, mushroom soup, milk, mayonnaise, pepper and salt. Mix with mixer. Add sauteed onions and cooked macaroni. Stir with spoon until all ingredients are mixed well. Pour into large casserole dish. Top with Ritz cracker topping and cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: golden green bean bake
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in green beans, 1/2 olives and 1/2 of the onions. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Top with remaining olives and onions.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: hannah's pumpkin trifle
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat milk and pudding mix on low speed for 2 minutes. Stir in whipped topping, pumpkin and pumpkin pie spice. Mix well. Fold in pecans. Spoon half of mixture into trifle bowl. Top with half of gingersnap crumbs. Repeat layers. Top with additional whipped topping. Yield: 6 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Pressure chicken at 10 pounds for 15 minutes in water to cover with salt, parsley and onion flakes.
Cool and debone.
Set aside.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Put Cool Whip in bowl; shake yogurt well, then add to Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: smoked sausage and cabbage skillet dinner
directions: Chop onion and cabbage.
Cook in skillet with water until almost tender.
Cut up smoked sausage and add salt, pepper and paprika.
Cook until cabbage is tender.
Serve with cornbread.

title: lasagne roll ups
directions: Prepare filling, whip ricotta cheese with electric mixer. Add eggs on at a time, beating well after each one.
Add salt, pepper, nutmeg, cheese and parsley.
Set filling aside.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet; drain.
Pour meat and remaining ingredients into casserole dish.
Stir.
Bake at 325° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: tuna casserole #2
directions: Partially fill a large pan with water.
Add peas, celery and onion and bring to a boil.
Add pasta and cook about 10 minutes. Remove from stove and drain.
Pour mixture into a casserole dish. Mix in tuna, soup and cheese well.
Top with more cheese and French fried onions.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Save 1 2/3 to 2 cups broth.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt margarine.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the bread cubes from the stuffing mix over bottom of dish.
Layer chicken on bread cubes and cover with seasoning packet.
Mix 1 cup of the broth, soup and sour cream together.
Pour over the chicken.
Cover with remaining bread cubes from stuffing mix and sprinkle with remaining broth.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill, adding ginger ale just before punch is served.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken breasts in rectangular pan.
Sprinkle with water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Mix sour cream, soups and 1 cup of chicken stock together.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with dressing. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
tags: cream of chicken soup and cream of celery soup

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs, butter and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients, then combine the two and add milk.
Beat until well blended.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef.
Take taco seasoning and mix.
Drain Ro-Tel tomatoes; mix with sour cream and refried beans.
Spread over bottom of pan.
Put beef mixture over that.
Shred lettuce over this; dice 2 tomatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: tea cakes
directions: Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: beans and burger
directions: Brown beef.
Add onion and saute until golden.
Add pork and beans and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until heated thoroughly.
Could add one can drained corn for a casserole.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Bake or boil potatoes.
Peel, cool and mash potatoes.
Mix all ingredients; work in the flour.
Roll out and cut or pat out biscuits to desired size.
Place on greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into greased casserole dish.

title: hot sausages and peppers
directions: Cut hot Italian sausage into bite-size pieces and brown in skillet.
Drain fat and add in onions, green peppers, and tomato paste and 3 cans of water.
Simmer 1 hour.
You may need to add more water.
Cook egg noodles, drain and add butter while noodles are hot so that the butter melts.
Serve sausages over noodles.

title: barbecued kolbassi
directions: Bake kolbassi until tender.
Slice 1/4-inch thick and place in electric frypan.
Mix other ingredients and stir into kolbassi. Simmer 2 hours.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first eight ingredients, beating well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and cut with pastry blender.
Put on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat in eggs.
Add bananas alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Stir in chocolate chips and bake in greased and floured bread pan for 60 minutes at 350°.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Brown meat on all sides; add onion.
Combine the mustard, brown sugar, salt and paprika.
Combine Worcestershire sauce, catsup and vinegar; add to mustard mixture.
Add to the meat and add 1 cup of water.
Stir and cover.
Cook over low heat until meat is very tender (1 to 2 hours).
Blend flour with remaining 1/2 cup water.
Add to meat mixture.
Stir until thickened.
Serve meat mixture over cooked noodles.
You may need to add more water as it cooks.
Serves 4.

title: custard
directions: Beat egg until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Don't overbake.

title: beef burgundy hero
directions: Cut loaf in half lengthwise; hollow out each half.
Butter insides; place under broiler to toast and set aside.
Fry bacon. Saute steak in drippings.
Sprinkle flour over meat in pan; stir. Add broth and Burgundy; stir until thickened.
Add thyme, tomato paste and bay leaf; simmer gently.

title: angel hair pasta with quick tomato sauce
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, saute garlic in water with bouillon cubes.
Add tomato and fresh basil and cook gently for approximately 10 minutes.
Add pine nuts.
Sauce is now ready to be poured over cooked angel hair pasta; sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.

title: dreamsicle punch
directions: Mix together in large punch bowl.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Sum people, 'cause of th' name "vinegar pie," might think this here pie was specially fer people thet are sourpusses, or to be give to people you don't like, but thet ain't so.
This is a real tasty pie.

title: cabbage and sausage casserole
directions: Cook the sausage in a pan of water for about 10 minutes. Remove the sausage.
Use the same water to cook the cabbage in, adding about 2 more cups of water.
Boil the cabbage, onion and bacon pieces for about 20 minutes.
Drain thoroughly the can of sauerkraut.
Squeeze the sauerkraut of its liquid and add to the cabbage mixture.
Mix well and boil for another 15 minutes.
Stir often as to prevent scorching or burning.

title: mocha punch
directions: Mix first
4 ingredients.
Let cool.
Ten or 15 minutes before serving, add remaining ingredients.
Serves 50.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar together.
Dredge nuts, cherries and pineapple in 2 cups flour.
Add baking powder to remaining 2 cups of flour.
Add to margarine and sugar mixture alternately with egg yolks, beating well after each addition.

title: pico degallo
directions: Combine and chill. Serve with tortilla chips. Also, may use red wine vinegar, seasoned salt, and black pepper.

title: monkey bread
directions: Take cinnamon and brown sugar and put in a small bag.
Take the biscuits and cut each one in quarters.
Put in bag with sugar and cinnamon and shake good.
Layer in a Bundt pan all over and up until all biscuits are done.
Melt margarine and pour all over biscuits.
Take rest of cinnamon and pour on top.
Cook at 350° until done.
Mix powdered sugar and milk and pour on top of cool biscuits.

title: dirt cups
directions: Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Gently stir in whipped topping and half the crushed cookies. Place 1 tablespoon crushed cookies into bottoms of 8-ounce paper or plastic cups.
Fill cups about 3/4 full with pudding mixture. Top with remaining crushed cookies.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Pour hot water over jello.
Drain pineapple and use juice and add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Chill until syrupy.
Beat cranberry sauce lightly with fork.
Fold in with rest of ingredients.

title: luby's butternut brownie pie
directions: *Another version calls for Ritz crackers (22), crushed.

title: apple crisp topping
directions: Place apples in an 8-inch square dish.

title: bean and corn casserole
directions: Drain beans and corn.
Mix beans, corn, soup, celery, onions and sour cream.
Saute crackers in butter.
Place on top of mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Place almonds on top and allow to brown.

title: tennessee mud
directions: Mix the cake mix, 1 egg and butter.
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix the cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour on top of crust.
Put pecans on top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
It will be soft in middle.

title: butterscotch oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat.
Add vanilla.
Combine flour, oatmeal, soda and salt.
Add alternately with water to creamed mixture.
Stir in butterscotch chips and nuts.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening and butter until creamy; add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well each time.
Stir in lemon and vanilla flavorings.
Sift together flour and baking powder; add alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour and beating smooth after each addition.
If desired, stir in coconut.
Pour in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and place in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes and mix ingredients well.

title: hamburger cookie
directions: Yellow equals mustard, green equals lettuce, red equals ketchup and white equals mayonnaise.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Crush crackers; add pecans and butter.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Save 1/2 cup for topping.
Mix ice cream, pudding and milk in mixer just until lumps are out.
Pour on top of cracker mix.
Chill for 1/2 hour.
Spread Cool Whip on this mixture and sprinkle rest of cracker mix on top.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together in a blender and chill.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Follow directions on stuffing mix box.
Let cool.
In mixing bowl, combine hamburger, one egg and cooled stuffing mix.
Shape into loaf; bake at 350° for one hour.

title: german pasties
directions: Prepare the roll mix according to the package directions. Brown the ground beef; drain well.
Layer leaves of cabbage over ground beef.
Add 1/4 to 1/2 cup water.
Cover; cook until the cabbage is tender.
Cut up cabbage and mix into the ground beef.

title: wiener appetizers
directions: Cut each wiener into 4 pieces.
Combine all ingredients. Bring to a boil and and then cook over medium heat until sauce becomes thick, approximately 1 hour.
Serve on toothpicks.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate in 9 x 12-inch dish.
(Recipe can be cut in half.)

title: company coming casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix ingredients and bake 1 hour in greased casserole at 325°.

title: submarine sandwiches
directions: Cut loaves of bread in 1/2 lengthwise.
Brush with dressing mix that you have already prepared as per package.
Heat in warm oven on cookie sheet.
Layer on warm bread the meat, lettuce, tomato and cheese.
Wrap in foil individually.
Cook at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tonkatsu
directions: Cut pork into one inch slices from bone.
Dip in mixture of flour and black pepper.
Tenderize.
Dip in egg and milk combination.
Dip in bread crumbs.
Fry in oil until golden brown. Cut pork cutlet into 1/2-inch strips across and serve over rice topped with Tonkatsu Sauce (Japanese steak sauce).

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Mix together and top with maraschino cherries and chill.

title: crazy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 8-inch square pan. Sift together dry ingredients.
Make 3 holes for oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Pour water over mixture and stir with fork.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dig deep salad
directions: In large clear bowl, spread bottom and sides of bowl with lettuce.
Layer carrots, chestnuts and green pepper.
Add frozen peas and top with onion rings.
Spread mayonnaise on top and cover mayonnaise with Parmesan cheese.
Wrap tightly with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: hamburger sausage party treats
directions: In a large frying pan, break up hamburger and sausage; cook until well done.
Drain well in colander and return drained meat to pan; spread sliced cheese over top.
Cover and allow cheese to melt through meat.
Spread on rye bread and refrigerate or freeze until ready to use.
Cook on cookie sheet at 375° for 10 minutes or until brown on top.
Makes 36.

title: italian rum cake
directions: Layer 1 package Anisette toast in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan by breaking toast in half.
(Don't worry about spaces between toast, pudding will fill it up.)
Cook vanilla pudding according to package instructions.
Add 1 jigger of rum and pour over toast. Break up second package of toast and layer on vanilla pudding. Cook chocolate pudding according to package instructions.
Add 1 jigger of rum and pour over toast layer.
Cover with foil.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
In morning or before serving, frost with Cool Whip.
Cut into squares and serve.
Serves 12.

title: ramen noodle salad
directions: Mix oil, sugar, vinegar with seasoning packaged in Ramen noodles.
Set aside noodles. Combine cole slaw, sunflower seeds, slivered almonds and green onions. Just before serving, add dressing and broken up uncooked noodles.
Add parsley and/or green peppers if desired.
Enjoy......This will feed a small group or large depending on how much cole slaw you use.
Even good the next day, if any is left!

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Place croutons and cheese in the bottom of a greased 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until set.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: chocolate angel food cake
directions: Combine flour packet from cake mix and cocoa.
Stir well with a wire whisk.

title: sally's jam cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add the jam and spices, stirring well.
Then add the milk, soda and flour.
Mix thoroughly and bake in a 350° oven in three layers.
When cool, ice with Caramel Icing.

title: diet banana split cake
directions: Place cracker crumbs in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Prepare pudding according to directions using skim milk.
Add bananas, pineapple and strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oven-fried chicken (diabetic)
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Combine crushed corn flakes, paprika, and powders.
Roll chicken in milk.
Roll chicken in form flake mixture.
Place chicken in small nonstick baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix 1 box of cornbread mix according to directions and fill bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix hamburger, soup and salsa and pour over the layer of cornbread.
Mix the 2nd box of cornbread and pour on top.
Bake according to cornbread directions.
Top with cheese to melt.
Serve with sour cream.

title: mystery pecan pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, 1 egg, 1 teaspoon vanilla and salt until thick and creamy.
Beat remaining eggs in a bowl, only until blended.
Add remaining sugar, corn syrup and remaining vanilla, blending well.
Spread cream cheese mixture evenly over bottom of pie shell; sprinkle with pecans.
Pour corn syrup mixture gently over pecans.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until center is firm to touch.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, pineapple, oranges and Jell-O.
Fold in Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add rest of ingredients. Simmer 15 minutes.
Pour into greased baking dish and cover with corn bread mix. Bake at 350° until corn bread is brown.

title: the best chicken
directions: Boil chicken until it is done or almost done.
Heat all three soups, milk and water together.
Place chicken, in a 9 x 12-inch glass casserole dish.
Place rice over the chicken.
Pour liquids over the chicken and the rice.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: tomato salsa
directions: Simmer tomatoes.
Cook peppers, celery, onions and garlic. Combine with tomatoes and cook for 30 minutes.
Add lemon juice and tomato paste.
Put into jars and pressure cook at 10 pounds for 15 minutes for pint jars, 20 minutes for quart jars.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Melt together soup, lemon juice, Cheddar and margarine.
Pour mixture over broccoli.
Sprinkle with 1 cup crushed cheese crackers and 1/4 cup slivered almonds.

title: strawberry pie or peach pie
directions: Boil until thickened and clear.
Cool.
Put in graham cracker shell or regular pie shell.
Refrigerate.
Serve with whipped cream or soft ice cream.

title: holiday salad
directions: Dissolve jello into boiling water.
Stir well. Drain pineapple; heat the juice and add to jello mixture.
While still hot add the cream cheese. Beat with the egg beater until dissolved.
Add salt.
Let chill until slightly thickened.
Mix in whipped cream.
Add pineapple, pimento, celery and nuts.
Chill. Cut into squares.
Makes a large salad.

title: crab luau
directions: Mix drained crab with onions and water chestnuts (I chop them fine).
Mix lemon juice, soy sauce and mayonnaise together. Combine with crab mixture.
Taste and add pepper and paprika to taste.
Serve with crackers or rye bread

title: marinade
directions: Mix all together. Add desired beef & poultry & pork, marinate over night, one time use.

title: katie's quick chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Boil breast; debone and set aside.
Drain stock through a colander and save.
Slice and brown sausage in 2 tablespoons oil. Put on a paper towel to drain the excess grease.
Set aside.
Now is the time to make the roux.
Pour cooking oil in cast-iron pot. If you don't have one, go get one now.
How have you been cooking without it?
Heat the oil until it's really hot and slowly stir in the flour.
I like to use a wooden spoon for this part.
Turn the heat down.
The roux should be cooked slowly if you are cooking on an electric stove, you've probably burned it by now.
The roux should have a watery consistency during this process.
Keep stirring until it is a deep, rich brown.
Pour in the bag of frozen seasonings.
The seasonings will cook down in the roux.
Stir for about 2 minutes.
Add chicken stock and deboned chicken and sausage.
Simmer for about 20 minutes.
Season with peppers, garlic, file and other seasonings as desired.
Serve over rice with American cheese; Ritz crackers and more file.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Best cooked in double boiler.
Combine all ingredients and cook at least 1/2 hour to 45 minutes, stirring often.

title: cherry pizza cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour cherry pie filling into dish.
Sift white cake mix over pie filling.
Melt margarine and pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crescents
directions: Form into crescents (or ball). Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar baked.

title: ricotta rhubarb bread*
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In medium bowl beat together margarine, Ricotta, milk, eggs and extract.
Add Ricotta mixture to dry ingredients; stir just until blended.
Fold in rhubarb and nuts.
Scoop batter into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until tests done.
Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely.
Keep in airtight container. Slices better the next day.

title: instant banana pudding
directions: Layer with bananas and cookies.

title: hot dog chili iii
directions: Mix ingredients. Cook on medium-high heat until it starts to boil; then cook on medium. After done, let simmer on low for 2 to 3 hours.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf for six
directions: Crush crackers (crush them inside a plastic bag and they won't make a mess).
In a 9-inch pie plate mix beef, onion, crackers, salt, pepper, egg and 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Form a round loaf.

title: tomato pie
directions: Bake pie crust per instructions. Peel and slice tomatoes. Layer in bottom of baked pie crust. Chop green onions and spread over tomatoes. Sprinkle basil and lemon pepper over tomatoes/onions. Mix mayonnaise and cheese. Spread on top of pie. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt butter in 1 quart dish.
Beat together corn, milk, sugar, flour and
eggs.
Place in dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: holiday brew
directions: Combine all ingredients in large boiler or slow cooker.
Heat on low about 3 hours.
Serve hot.
Makes about 12 servings.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Make Jell-O as per package and jell.
In blender, blend 1/2 of the jelled Jell-O and the frozen strawberries.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch dish.
Then blend the other half jelled Jell-O and package Dream Whip.
Pour over the top of the other mixture.
Cover with nuts.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: crumbs for pie topping(enough for one 9-inch fruit pie)
directions: Using pastry blender, mix together all ingredients until they are fine crumbs. Spread evenly over fruit filling in unbaked pastry shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then 30 minutes longer at 350°.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine first 7 ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Add buttermilk and mix well on high speed, about 5 minutes.
Add raisins and seed; mix in with a spoon.
Pour mixture into a greased and lightly floured 10-inch tube pan.
Let stand in pan about 15 minutes to cool, then remove and continue to let cool.

title: devil's food cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into ball and cook on cookie sheet. Let cool and put frosting in the middle.
Can use any cake mix.

title: mrs. both's meat marinade
directions: Combine the above ingredients with any cut of meat.
This is a delicious, easy meal.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in water.
Add salt, vinegar and onion.
Combine broccoli, beef consomme and eggs with rice mixture.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage lasagna wraps
directions: Cut kielbasa into 4 to 6 pieces, split lengthwise.
Stuff each with 1/2 slice Mozzarella cheese.
Wrap each piece in a cooked lasagna noodle.
Place in small baking dish; cover with spaghetti sauce.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: frosted pumpkin bars
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, oil, pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients. Mix together.
Add nuts, pour on a large greased cookie shet. Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash peppers
and
cut in half;
take seeds out and set aside. Place
oil
in
large
skillet.
Heat.
Brown okra and onion in oil.
Add tomatoes, ground country ham, chili sauce, tomato ketchup,
Worcestershire sauce and red pepper.
Cook in skillet for
30 minutes. Stir in Rice Krispies.
Stuff mixture into the 12 pepper halves and bake, using shallow baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes in their skins until tender.
Cool, peel and mash.
Beat in eggs, sugar and remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with cream.
Can be doubled for 2 pies (except bourbon; use 1/2 cup).

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix together melted butter, 3 tablespoons sugar and pretzels. Put mixture in large greased dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes. Let cool.
Beat together cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled pretzel crust.
Dissolve strawberry jello in frozen strawberries.
Let set 10 minutes.
Pour on top of cheese mixture and chill.
Can fix the night before.

title: fat-free barbecue sauce
directions: Mix everything together; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: marinade for chicken or pork
directions: Heat all ingredients to boiling point and cool thoroughly. Prick large pieces of meat with fork or cut into cubes for shish kabob.
Pour mixture over meat and marinate at least 4 hours. Charcoal broil.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve jello in pineapple and juice, heated.
Cool and add other ingredients.

title: swiss steak
directions: Season steak with salt and pepper.
Roll in flour.
Saute in oil until brown.
Remove from skillet.
Stir in remaining flour and cook until brown.
Pat steak and vegetables in skillet and add 1 cup water.
Simmer for 2 hours or until steak and vegetables are tender.

title: corn and rice bake
directions: Chop onion and green pepper; cook in butter until tender. Mix all ingredients together with 1/2 cup of shredded cheese. Bake for 40 minutes in 325° oven.
Top with 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: fruit drops
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add egg; beat well.
Add vanilla and orange peel.
Add dry ingredients with milk and fruit.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°.

title: refrigerator rolls for company
directions: Heat milk, shortening and sugar until sugar is dissolved. Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to milk mixture. In a large bowl, beat in enough flour to make a thick batter. Cover with a towel and allow to rise in a warm place for 2 hours.

title: saffron rice
directions: Cook like regular rice.
Wonderful with any chicken dish or baked ham.

title: huevos con chorizo(eggs with mexican sausage)
directions: Slice chorizo in nickel-size pieces; remove outer skin.
Beat eggs with milk, onion and grated cheese until foamy.
Heat bacon drippings or oil in large skillet.
Blend chorizo into egg mixture.
Fry in skillet until lightly browned.
Turn and cook other side, until egg and chorizo are done.
Serve immediately with hot flour tortillas.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumber and mix with onions.
Cover with ice cubes. Stand overnight and drain.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk.
Then add well beaten egg whites.
Add nuts. Bake in layers put together with Caramel Icing and nuts.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Add shortening, sugar and salt to scalded milk.
Add 1/4 cup warm water to dry yeast.
Let scalded milk mixture cool to lukewarm and then add yeast mixture.
Add flour until you have a good dough mixture.
Knead on floured board or paper.
Place dough in a greased bowl; grease top of dough and cover with dish towel.
Let raise in warm place until double in bulk.
Punch down and make into rolls; cover.
Let rolls raise until double in size.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° in oven for 30 minutes in 8 x 8-inch square pan.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour baking dish. Combine flour, baking powder and soda in large mixing bowl. In a blender, blend walnuts and add to mixture. Blend remaining ingredients; add to bowl. Mix until smooth. Add to baking dish and bake for about 35 minutes.

title: caramel crispix
directions: Mix brown sugar, corn syrup and butter in heavy 2-quart saucepan and boil for 5 minutes.
Do not stir! Remove from heat and stir in baking soda and cream of tartar.
Mix well and pour over Crispix and nuts.
Stir to coat.
Spread in large, buttered roaster.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Stir and break into pieces.
Cool completely and store in covered container.
(Good for popcorn, too.)

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Use an ungreased cookie sheet.
For soft chewy cookies, check at 8 minutes.
Let set on pan 1 to 2 minutes before placing on rack to cool.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Soften cream cheese and butter; mix well.
Stir in flour. Mix; cover and refrigerate.
Chill about 1 hour.
Shape into small balls, about 1-inch.
Press into the mini muffin tins.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef with onions; drain.
Mix sauce mix, water and tomato paste.
Add Italian seasoning, Worcestershire, oregano and red pepper.
Let simmer 20 minutes.

title: luscious lemon squares
directions: Stir together flour and powdered sugar; blend in butter. Press into 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes until light brown.
Beat eggs; stir in sugar and lemon juice. Pour into baked pastry lined pan.
Return to oven and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Chill.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and fold in Cool Whip.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put layer of whole graham crackers and then layer of pudding. Alternate layers, ending with graham crackers on top.
Spread chocolate frosting on top.
Chill.

title: grandmother michaels' icebox rolls
directions: Mix together warm water and yeast.
Let stand while mixing sugar, egg, shortening and salt.
Cream well and add yeast mixture.
Add 4 cups flour and beat with electric mixer.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Blend together cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Fold in Cool Whip, marshmallows and fruit.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
This needs to thaw a little while in order to serve. Time depends on weather.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Heat milk and margarine.
Beat eggs real good.
Mix sugar and beat.
Add flour and vanilla and beat.
Add hot milk and margarine.
Beat well.
Add 2 level teaspoons baking powder.
Beat thoroughly for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Top with your favorite frosting.

title: tortellini vegetable salad made easy
directions: Cook tortellini (firm); drain and cool.
In a large bowl combine red pepper, broccoli, carrots, olives and tortellini (when cool).

title: ranch style ribs
directions: Place meat in large casserole or ovenproof dish.
In mixing bowl, combine all other ingredients, blending well.
Pour over meat, being careful to spoon on every piece of meat.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour, covered with foil.
Remove foil or cover and bake 30 minutes longer (making 1 1/2 hours total cooking time).
Serves 4.

title: dilly cucumber salad
directions: Place cucumbers in large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients except dill weed.
Pour over cucumbers and mix gently.
Sprinkle with dill weed.
Cover, refrigerate at least one hour.
Mix lightly before serving.
If desired sprinkle with snipped parsley. Makes 8-10 servings.

title: apricot bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift first 3 ingredients into a bowl; set aside.
Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add nuts, coconut and flour mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Press 3/4 of the mixture in the bottom of a 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Spread jam over mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut in bars.

title: pat o'brien's new orleans style hurricane punch
directions: Mix red passion fruit cocktail mix, lemon juice and rum together.
Pour over crushed ice.
Chill glasses before serving. Garnish with orange slice and cherry.

title: broccoli pasta
directions: In heavy skillet, combine oil, butter, onion and garlic and saute for 5 minutes or until garlic is golden.
Whisk in flour. Then gradually stir in the cream.
Cook stirring until thickened. Stir in Parmesan cheese and remove from heat.
Cut broccoli into small pieces and then steam until tender, about 6 minutes.
Cook ziti according to package directions; drain.
Combine ziti and broccoli with sauce.
Toss gently until coated.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Garnish with the tomatoes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt sugar in 1 1/2 quarts of water; add salt, pepper, garlic juice and oleo.
Let come to boil; add barbecue spice and catsup. Boil 15 minutes more.
If too thick, add more water.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt together.
Add at least 1/4 cup of milk.
Scald remaining milk and add sugar mixture.
Cook until thick.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Break up spaghetti and mix all in greased 2-quart or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 15 more minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bubble mix
directions: *Must be Joy or Dawn for best results.

title: tomato sauce for canning
directions: Peel tomatoes; grind and chop onions and peppers.
Add tomatoes with all other ingredients.
Cook slowly for 2 hours, stirring frequently.
Place in jars and hot pack to seal.

title: lite turkey sausage soup
directions: Bring water, stewed tomatoes, spinach, carrots, onion, bouillon and pepper to a full boil in a large saucepan.
Drop in bite size pieces of uncooked sausage stirring occasionally.
Stir in macaroni.
Simmer 10 minutes or until macaroni is tender. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese if desired.

title: banana muffins
directions: Beat egg, oil and milk.
Stir in bananas.
Mix dry ingredients together and stir in banana mixture until flour is moistened. Fill muffin tins 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Bake about 20 to 25 minutes in 400° oven.
Yield: 12 medium muffins.
Exchange per muffin: 1 muffin = 1 Bread and 1 Fat.

title: 5 can casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing and margarine.
Cover bottom of 2-quart (9 x 13-inch) casserole dish with half of stuffing mix.
Mix soups, milk, broth, chicken, peas, celery and onions.
Pour into casserole.
Cover with remaining stuffing/margarine mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 20 minutes before serving. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Wash rice thoroughly.
Add the other ingredients and pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake from 1 1/2 to 2 hours in a slow oven (250° to 350°), stirring several times.
The mixture should not boil.
Serve hot or cold.

title: shortcake biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine.
Add milk.
Knead 13 to 15 times.
Roll out 1-inch thick.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: sweet and spicy fried rice
directions: Boil or steam rice until done.
If using meat, season to your liking. Chop or dice onions, celery, carrots and garlic.
Saute in oil, using a big skillet.
A wok is better.
Add soy sauce.
Add meat and cook.
When meat is 3/4 done, add rice, hunan sauce, cumin and honey.
Stir and mix well. Add tomato.

title: pretzel cheesecake
directions: Place pretzels and margarine in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Cream together sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread on pretzels and refrigerate.
Mix jello, juice and cornstarch (whisk cornstarch in to prevent lumps).
Heat over medium heat until slightly thickened.
Add frozen raspberries or strawberries and pour over whipped topping. Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: crisp onion-roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In shallow baking pan, spread potatoes. Mix all ingredients together and pour over potatoes and turn to coat thoroughly.
Bake, stirring occasionally, 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Double recipe for 5 pounds potatoes.
Be sure to spray pan with Pam before placing potatoes in pan.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake 40-45 minutes.

title: thanksgiving dressing
directions: Place all of the ingredients in a bowl and mix.
Add sage or poultry seasoning to flavor.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients; mix well.
Makes about 2 1/2 gallons.

title: six-cup dessert salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill.
Serve on lettuce.
Makes about 5 cups.
For less calories, use plain yogurt instead of sour cream.

title: peanut butter bon bons
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add Rice Krispies; mix.
Roll into balls and dip in chocolate sauce.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and then debone it.
Mix and warm all can foods in pot.
Shred cheese in separate bowls.
Slice tortillas in fourths.
Add chicken pieces to pot of cream.
Stir well.
Layer a 9 x 13-inch dish with all ingredients in the following order: tortilla slices spread out on bottom, cream mix, cheese, tortillas, cream mix and last of cheese.
Bake on 350° for 25 minutes and until cheese on top melts.

title: dinner party pork loin
directions: About 4 hours before serving preheat oven to 325°.
Sprinkle roast with garlic salt.
On rack, in shallow open roasting pan, place meat; insert meat thermometer in center.
Roast 3 to 3 1/2 hours until thermometer reads 170° internal temperature.
During last 20 minutes, generously brush roast with barbecue sauce.

title: pecan fruit cake
directions: Mix the fruit and nuts in 1 cup flour.
Cream the butter and lemon juice.
Add sugar gradually.
Add beaten eggs in thirds. Add dry ingredients in fourths.
Add fruit.
Bake at 275° for 4 1/2 hours with a pan of water in oven.

title: japanese curried chicken
directions: Rub chicken with salt and fry in hot oil until golden brown. Remove from pan. Fry onion and garlic. Add turmeric, coriander and cumin. Fry for 1 minute. Add laos, lemon grass and chili. Return chicken to this mixture. Add coconut milk and cook uncovered until the chicken is tender.
Serves 6.

title: cookies and cream pie
directions: Let ice cream start to thaw. Stir and pour ice cream into pie crust.
Top with chocolate or hot fudge syrup.
Put in freezer for 2 hours.
Remove from freezer.
Let stand about 5 minutes before serving.

title: orange coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a bundt pan well.

Mix sugar, nuts, and orange rhine. Take cream cheese and cut into equal pieces for the number of biscuits you have (about 16). Take each biscuit, flatten out a little and place one piece of cream cheese in the center.
Fold the biscuit around it and pinch together making a crescent shape.
Take each biscuit dip into melted butter, then dip into sugar mixture.
Place into bundt pan. Complete this process until all biscuits have been coated and put into bundt pan.
Pour remaining sugar mixture on top.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown on top.
Invert cake on plate and let cool for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: breasts of chicken supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and paprika.
Flour lightly.
Melt butter in skillet; saute chicken until golden on both sides; transfer to casserole.
Saute onions and green pepper in butter remaining in skillet for 5 minutes or until onions are transparent.
Add to casserole.
Add water and Sauterne.
Cover; bake in preheated oven for 1 hour.
Stir in sour cream; bake until sauce is hot.
Serves 6.

title: pasta e fagoli
directions: Put oil in a large pot and brown onion and garlic.
Remove from oil.
Add tomatoes.
Add basil, parsley and salt and pepper. Cook over low heat for 1/2 hour.
Add beans and heat through. Add the cooked ditalini noodles right before serving.
Mix well and enjoy.

title: pineapple ham crescents
directions: Drain pineapple well, reserving juice.
Reserve 2 spears for sauce. Chop and set aside.
Unroll crescent rolls. Wrap ham and cheese around pineapple.
Place at widest part of crescent and roll up.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden.

title: veggie bars
directions: I use food processor to chop and grate broccoli, cauliflower, carrots and cheese.

title: corn salad
directions: Add ingredients to corn. Mix with 2 to 3 tablespoons mayonnaise.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Boil sugar and vinegar for 1 minute.
Cool.
Mix all drained vegetables together.
Pour sugar/vinegar mixture over vegetables. Cover and marinate overnight.

title: jezebel
directions: Mix and let set.
Use over 2 or 3 blocks of cream cheese.

title: sour cream dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In skillet melt butter.
Add chopped onion and cook until slightly soft.
Stir in garlic and cook 1 minute longer.
Add beef cubes and cook until red is gone from meat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add Worcestershire sauce, bouillon cube and water.
Adjust heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, slice mushrooms and saute in 2 tablespoons butter in another small skillet.
Stir into meat mixture just before serving.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat about 5 minutes.
Do not boil!
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: fried chicken
directions: Fill Dutch oven or deep fryer 1/3 full with shortening.
Heat to 350°.
Combine flour and seasoning in plastic bag.
Dip chicken pieces in buttermilk, then into flour mixture.
Fry in hot shortening 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy; add all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until brown.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop nuts until the size of rice.
Add butter and flour, mix thoroughly.
Spread on bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
(Dip fingers in flour to help spread crust.) Bake 15 to 20 minutes until edges are brown.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: veg-cheese lasagna
directions: In 10-inch skillet, heat margarine over medium heat until bubbly and hot.
Add mushrooms and saute, stirring occasionally, until mushrooms are lightly browned and cooked through, 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and set aside.

title: true love dinner for two
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, mix soup, onion, rice (with flavor packet), mushrooms and curry powder.
Stir in water and wine; top with chicken breasts and cover.
Bake one hour in 350° oven .
At the end of one hour, your dinner is ready, but if the evening is progressing well, just turn the oven to low.
Like true love, dinner will wait forever and be there when you want it.

title: potatoes with cheese
directions: Cut potatoes into thin slices but don't cut all the way through.
Put potatoes on a baking dish; sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.
Remove pan from oven and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake another 10 to 15 minutes or until slightly brown and cheese is melted.

title: zucchini appetizer - barbara's
directions: Heat oven to 350.
Grease 9 X 13 pan.
Mix all ingredients - spread in pan.
Bake about 25 minutes.
Cut into squares. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Mix Bisquick, baking powder, egg, salt and pepper with enough water to make a stiff batter.
Add grated zucchini.
Drop by teaspoonfuls in hot oil.
Cook until brown.

title: heavenly tomato cake
directions: Cream together
margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift together cocoa, flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Combine tomato juice, hot water and marshmallows; add to batter.
Add vanilla.
