Batter will be thin and marshmallows will come to top. Pour into 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Bake in 350° preheated oven to 35 minutes.
Ice while hot.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs in a large mixing bowl.
Add sugars, oil and grated zucchini.
Mix in vanilla and nuts.
Add all the dry ingredients at once and mix well.
Pour into greased bread pans and bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 4 medium size loaves.

title: cajun cake
directions: Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured, at 300° for 50 minutes.
Batter will be very thin.

title: angel food bars
directions: Combine angel food cake mix and pie filling.
Do not mix too much.
Add coconut and nuts.
Spread in a greased and floured 10 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with powdered sugar glaze.

title: beet salad(insalata barbabietola)
directions: Cut off all but 2 inches of beet tops.
Cut root end to 1-inch on bottom of beets.
Place
beets
on baking pan, lined with foil and bake for 1
hour
at
Check
to make sure they are tender; if not, return
to
oven for a little longer. When beets are cooked,
cool
and
peel.
Slice
into 1/4-inch thick slices or wedges and
place
in
glass bowl with onions. Add eggs to beets, if
desired.
Mix
rest
of ingredients and pour over beets.
Let marinate at least 5 hours.
Makes 3 to 4 servings. These will last up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain fat and set aside.
Blend together chili and tomatoes.
Chop up garlic.
Add flour to ground beef; blend in garlic.
Add water to desired thickness, then gradually add in chili, tomatoes and salt to taste.
Allow to simmer 10 to 20 minutes or to desired thickness and enjoy!!
Spread in layer form over prefried tortillas, layer of cheese and onions and chili.
Followed by 1 to 1 1/2 ladles of chili sauce.
Place total dish into oven 10 to 15 minutes.
Bake at 300°.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Heat ingredients and pour mixture over browned ribs.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough out in a pizza pan.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 10 minutes.
Take out of oven and let cool.
Mix together cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Pour on cookie dough.
Mix together diced fruit with glaze.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: creamy corn chowder
directions: Cut kernels from cobs (approximately 3 cups). Reserve 3 cobs. In Dutch oven, cook bacon over medium heat until browned. Drain on paper towels. In fat in Dutch oven, add onion and jalapeno and cook over low heat until tender (not brown) 6 to 8 minutes. Add garlic; cook 1 minute. Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Cook, stirring 1 minute. Stir in broth, half and half, potatoes and reserved corn cobs. Heat to boiling over high heat. Reduce and simmer 10 to 15 minutes until potatoes are tender. Discard cobs; stir in corn and heat through. Transfer to tureen; stir in tomatoes and bacon. Garnish with basil, if you desire.

title: hot chicken dip
directions: Mix with mixer. Place in greased dish and cover with grated Colby cheese. Heat until bubbling (30 min.) Serve with crackers. (Can use sharp or mild cheddar cheese.)

title: chicken in phyllo
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Halve chicken breasts and pound flat. Melt butter.
Layer 4 sheets of phyllo, buttering each sheet.
On each chicken breast, sprinkle 1 tablespoon shallots and 1/4 teaspoon sage.
Lay 1 ounce cheese on each breast and roll up. Place breast in the middle of the phyllo at one end; roll once. Fold in sides, brush with butter and continue rolling and buttering as you go.
Lay all on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 25 minutes until browned.

title: grandma's date bread
directions: Lightly grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Preheat oven to 350°. Dissolve soda in water.
Add dates; cool.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, flour and date mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into pans and bake 45 minutes.

title: eggless baked rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, until rice is tender.
Stir several times during the first hour of baking.

title: yogurt cups
directions: Mix flour, oleo and sugar until crumbly.
Sprinkle in water, 1 teaspoon at a time, stirring until dough forms.
Press about 3 tablespoons of dough in bottom and up the sides of each of 4 ungreased 6 ounce custard cups to within 1/2-inch of top.
Bake until golden brown at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Remove from cups with a small metal spatula; let cool completely.
Fill each cup with 1/3 cup of yogurt.
Garnish with fresh fruit if you like.

title: spicy corn salsa
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a nonaluminum bowl; add cilantro, if desired.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours, stirring often.
serve with tortilla chips or as a relish with grilled beef or chicken.
Yields 6 cups.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Beat eggs well and combine with next three ingredients, beating well.
Pour in a crust and let chill.
Mix the whipping cream, powdered sugar, nuts, vanilla and pineapple together.
Put this on top of other mixture.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: overnight meringues
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until foamy.
Very gradually, add sugar and beat until guile stiff.
Fold in flavorings by hand, then stir in nuts and drops.
Place plain white or brown paper on cookie sheet and drop meringues by teaspoon.
No need for much spreading. Preheat oven to 350°.
Place meringues in oven and immediately turn heat off.
Allow to remain in oven overnight or all day.
Don't open that oven door!!!

title: louisiana dirty rice
directions: Saute
celery,
onion
and
green pepper.
Add meat and brown lightly.
Cook rice.
Combine all ingredients and place in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mix.
With a wire whisk or beater, mix until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Open cans of pineapple; drain off juice.
Add pineapple to pudding as it thickens.
You can serve immediately, or let chill for 15 minutes.
May be topped with whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: fudge marble brownies
directions: Prepare fudge brownie mix.
Spread 1/2 brownie mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese and 5 tablespoons butter; beat together.
Add sugar, eggs, flour and 3/4 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until smooth.

title: chicken potatoes croquette
directions: Fry chopped onion and chicken with butter.
Add salt and pepper.
Mash potatoes.
Mix mashed potatoes, fried onion and chicken.
Make mixture into small balls.
Put on flour, then in egg and milk (mixed well), then in bread crumbs.
Fry the balls in vegetable oil until they get light brown (350° to 400°).

title: cinnamon buttermilk coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, salt, cinnamon and shortening until you have a mixture like corn meal.
Set aside 3/4 cup of this mixture for topping and the 1/2 cup nuts.
Then add egg, buttermilk and soda to remaining mixture.
Mix only until dry ingredients are well moistened.
Pour into 9-inch greased pan and cover with the topping.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cold carrot soup
directions: In large saucepan or Dutch oven, saute vegetables in oil until onions are clear but not browned.
Add broth and bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until carrots are tender. Remove from heat and puree in blender.
Cool.
Add orange juice and chill.
Just before serving, add milk and seasoning.
(Serves 4-6.)

title: chicken and spaghetti(club member: nicholas)
directions: Boil chicken with salt to taste until tender. Remove from broth and cube. Cut up bell pepper, onion and garlic bud.

Cook in butter until tender. Boil spaghetti in broth until done. Add all ingredients, except cheese. Mix well. Pour into baking dish. Sprinkle grated cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Yields 8 servings.

title: braised beef tips over rice
directions: Melt shortening in large skillet.
Brown meat on all sides. Stir in consomme, wine, soy sauce, garlic and onion salt.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Blend cornstarch and water.
Gradually stir into meat mixture.
Cook, stirring until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown beef with onion and pepper.
Simmer with remaining ingredients to blend flavors.

title: holiday oven barbecued chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium saucepan, combine all sauce ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: play dough
directions: Mix flour, salt, water, oil and cream of tartar.
Cook for 3 minutes stirring constantly and fast.
Pour out on waxed paper and add food coloring to dough and knead.
Knead like bread until it is not sticky.
Store in plastic bags or covered jars.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until done; drain.
Cut cheese into cubes.
Put macaroni and cheese into crock-pot and milk until it reaches top of macaroni.
Cook on high for 2 to 3 hours.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream shortening until light and fluffy; add cheese.

Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture and mix well. Put dough through cookie press using ribbon design plate; or form dough into small balls about 1 inch in diameter; put on baking sheet about 1-inch apart.
Place pecan half on each, if desired. Bake in moderate, 350° oven for 15 minutes for balls, 10 minutes for straws.

title: brickle bars
directions: Combine egg, cake mix and oleo.
Mix until crumbly.
Press into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: melt in your mouth waffles
directions: In mixing bowl, combine the flour, baking powder and salt. Combine egg yolks, milk and oil.
Add to dry ingredients, beating just until blended.
Carefully fold in stiffly beaten egg whites, leaving a few puffs of egg white.
Do not overmix.
Bake in preheated waffle baker.
Makes 3 (9-inch) waffles.

title: lemon mousse
directions: Put graham cracker crust in a large square Tupperware container and place in freezer while preparing the filling. Chill can of milk.
Pour into a large mixing bowl and place in freezer until crystals form around edge.
Beat until like whipped cream.
Then slowly add a cup of sugar and 1/2 cup lemon juice. Pour into crust and put into freezer until frozen.
Cut into squares when serving.

title: biscuit recipe
directions: *For buttermilk biscuits: Substitute about 1 cup of buttermilk, less 2 tablespoons.

title: skillet cookies(candy)
directions: Beat eggs in skillet.
Add sugar and oleo.
Cook slow until melted, about 5 minutes.
Add dates and cook 10 minutes.
Take off fire, add pecans, Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Cool and roll into balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage in pan big enough to hold sausage and potatoes. When brown, add in the peeled and diced potatoes. Cook through until hot. Layer in bottom of greased 13 x 9 pan. Layer green chiles and cheese. Sprinkle salt and pepper to taste. Spread grated cheese over the top. Mix the eggs and sour cream with mixer and pour mixture. Bake at 350° until center is firm. Takes about 35 to 45 minutes. Serve with salsa.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cook ground meat and onion until done.
Stir in can of drained whole kernel corn, tomato sauce, rice, steak sauce, salt and pepper.
Spoon into steamed peppers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim any excess fat from steak; cut steak into 1/4-inch thick diagonal slices.
Heat a large skillet until very hot.
Add 1 tablespoon of butter and swirl to coat bottom of skillet.
Pan-fry beef strips, a few at a time, 1 minute on each side or until steak is done as you like it and all strips are fried, using more butter as needed.
Keep warm.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken. Remove from broth. Add spaghetti to broth and cook 4 to 6 minutes.
Let stand until spaghetti absorbs broth. Combine pimento, soup, salt, pepper, milk and chicken pieces. Layer in casserole dish the chicken mixture and spaghetti. Repeat.
Top with bread crumbs and cheese. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: graham cracker fudge
directions: In pan, bring to boil (rolling) the sugar, milk and oleo, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Boil 9 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove and stir in chocolate chips, vanilla, flour, cracker crumbs and nuts.
Turn into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: german sweet chocolate cake with coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cool. Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat after each addition. Add chocolate and vanilla.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Combine vegetables; add salt and water.
Let stand overnight, then drain.
Heat vinegar, sugar and seeds to boiling.
Add vegetables.
Bring to boil; cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.
Makes 5 pints.

title: quick apple crisp
directions: When spread with cream cheese or cottage cheese, this moist loaf makes a delicious snack or sandwiches to serve with tea or to accompany salad.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute the onions and green pepper in the salad oil until they are tender.
Add the ground beef.
Cook until the beef is brown. Stir in the tomatoes, uncooked rice, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: kentucky buttermilk cake
directions: On wax paper, combine flour, salt and baking powder.
In large mixing bowl with mixer on medium, beat butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
In measuring cup, mix baking soda with water; add buttermilk.
With mixer at low speed, alternately beat buttermilk and flour mixture into butter and sugar mixture until well combined.
In medium mixing bowl with mixer on high, beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Fold whites into batter.
Divide batter evenly into prepared pans (greased and floured).
Bake 20 minutes in preheated 350° oven until pick inserted comes out clean. Remove from pans and cool completely on wire rack.
Fill center and frost with buttercream frosting.

title: cornbread and chilies
directions: Beat eggs, corn, milk and oil.
Add all dry ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onion and green pepper for 5 minutes in the butter.
Add tomatoes and rice, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes more.
Season to taste.
Makes 5 servings.

title: crescent roll cheese bars
directions: Beat until blended the cream cheese, 1 egg yolk, 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Press 1 package of crescent rolls in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cream cheese mixture over dough.
Place the second package of crescent rolls over the cream cheese.
Beat the egg white until frothy; spread on top.
Mix 1/3 cup sugar, cinnamon and chopped walnuts.
Put over the frothy egg white.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream the butter, syrup, sugar and eggs.
Add milk and vanilla.
Gradually work flour into mixture until stiff enough to roll (not too stiff).
Roll out and cut into shapes.
Bake in a moderate oven until brown.

title: jello fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple, reserving liquid.
Drain mandarin oranges.
Combine box of pudding and 1 3/4 c. of reserved pineapple and fruit cocktail juice.
Cook until thick.
Chill to lukewarm.
Combine pudding with fruit and chill completely.
Fresh strawberries or fruit can be added as well.

title: swedish nut ball
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add nuts and flour.
Roll into small balls.
Bake for 1 hour in a 275° oven.
When cold, roll in confectioners sugar.

title: applesauce
directions: Peel and core apples; slice thinly.
Place in large bowl; cover with water.
Microwave in covered dish for 11 1/2 minutes. Add sugar and cinnamon; blend until smooth.
Place in jars to store.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix well
and
store in jars.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons for each cup with boiling water.

title: asparagus venetian
directions: Cook and drain asparagus.
Blend onion soup mix with melted butter or margarine.
Arrange asparagus in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Drizzle with the butter-onion mix.
Sprinkle on both cheeses.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 8.

title: grandma's potato salad
directions: In the top of a double boiler over boiling water, heat water, butter and vinegar.
In a bowl, beat eggs; add sugar and cornstarch.
Add to butter mixture.
Cook and stir constantly until thick, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Remove from the heat and allow to cool. Stir in salad dressing.
Fold in the whipped cream.
In a large bowl, toss potatoes, onion, green onions, salt and pepper. Pour the dressing over and mix gently.
Chill. Garnish with cooked eggs and sprinkle with paprika.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Prepare pie crust and partially bake for 8 minutes at 350°. Melt 3 teaspoons butter in skillet.
Add onion, salt and broccoli. Cover; simmer 5 minutes.
Beat eggs, cream, salt and nutmeg; add cheese and stir.
Pour into pie shell and dot with remaining butter and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place in 8 x 8-inch casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can be made the night before and refrigerate overnight.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into 2-greased pie pans. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes it's own crust.

title: pork roast
directions: Combine all seasoning and rub over surface of roast.
Pour 1 cup of hot water in roast pan and cover roast in pan.
Cook until tender and fork comes out clean.
Remove roast from oven and let stand 10 to 20 minutes before slicing.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour.

title: taco dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread cream cheese on bottom of pie plate.
Add chili on top, then sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese (whole package) on top of that.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortillas.
Goes great with margaritas!

title: little wiener sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together except wieners.
Heat slowly for 10 minutes.
Drop sliced wieners into sauce.

title: mexican munch
directions: Combine pork and beans, cheese spread and green onions.
Heat until cheese spread is melted.
Stir in tomato.
Serve warm with taco or corn chips.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and form into balls.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: dump fruit salad
directions: Dump in large bowl strawberries, pie filling and pineapple. Mix gently.
Add bananas.
Mix gently.
May be served with a dollop of Cool Whip or plain.
Refrigerate after mixing.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream margarine and sugar on medium speed for 5 minutes.
Add eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture until well blended.
Combine 8 ounces sugar and cinnamon. Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Place in ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. These cookies puff up at first, then flatten out with a crinkled top.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pie filling or pineapple into pan.
Mix with spoon, then sprinkle cake mix over top until you have used all of it.
Cut margarine up on top of cake mix.
Bake in 350° oven until brown and cake mix is done.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients until creamy.
Soften cream cheese slightly.
Beat into the butter mixture with milk and vanilla. Beat in remaining ingredients.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, soda, baking powder and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Add shortening, bananas, eggs, buttermilk and vanilla. Beat until smooth. Stir in pecans.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or two round cake pans. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes if in layers or 35 minutes if in a rectangular pan.

title: fresh tomato salsa
directions: *Select ripe tomatoes (8 to 12 depending on size).

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar together. Let stand while mixing dry ingredients, then mix with apples. Add eggs, oil, vanilla and nuts. Mix well. Pour in 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and more cinnamon on top before baking. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes until done.

title: chicken lynn
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender; pull off bone and cut in small pieces.
Mix sour cream and soup together; add chicken. Pour into casserole dish.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes in rounds thinly.
Fry in oil until soft and tender on inside and crispy on the outside with a golden-like color.
Sprinkle with salt while hot.

title: ham and cheese strata
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease an 8-inch square baking dish. Spread 1 side of bread slices with mustard. Arrange 4 slices, mustard side up, over bottom of prepared baking dish. Top with half the ham, broccoli and cheese. Cover with remaining bread, mustard side down, slices overlapping. Top with remaining ham, broccoli and cheese. Whisk milk and eggs until well blended; pour over bread. Bake 40 to 45 minutes until puffed, edges of bread are golden brown and knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: oven apple butter
directions: Pour everything into a large roasting pan and mix thoroughly. Bake at 300° for at least 3 to 4 hours until as dark and as thick as desired.
Makes approximately 15 pints.
I usually can the extra.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Sift together sugar, salt and flour.
Set aside.
Put in saucepan:
butter, cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil and pour over first mixture, stirring well.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into large greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Toast pecans in butter in oven.
Mix cornstarch and sugar. Add milk and cook over direct heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Chill the whip cream until stiff.
Fold in chilled mixture and Edwards pecans.
Pour into freezing tray of automatic refrigerator and freeze.

title: smores
directions: Take the Hershey bars and break them into twos.
Get 4 marshmallows and stick in between two graham crackers.
Bake in oven for 5 to 10 minutes.
Eat!

title: harvard beets
directions: Cook beets until tender; cool slightly.
Peel and dice.
Blend sugar, salt and cornstarch in another pan.
Add vinegar; stir until mixed.
Cook until thick and smooth.
Stir constantly.
Add butter and onion.
Stir; pour over beets (heat if desired).
Makes about 6 servings.

title: baked chicken
directions: Split chicken in half.
Place in baking pan.
Add all ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with crackers.
This is best if you let set in refrigerator for several hours before serving.

title: edith's pound cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder 3 times and sit aside.
Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until brown.

title: chris' chili
directions: Chop peppers and boil until tender.
While boiling peppers, brown ground beef and onion in skillet; drain.
Mix together in large pot the peppers, beef, beans, tomato juice and chili seasoning.
Cook for approximately 30 minutes.
Good served with sweet pickles, olives and Cheddar cheese.

title: apple cranberry french toast
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter, and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in a 13 x 9 baking dish.
Add apples and cranberries, toss to coat well. Spread apple mixture evenly over bottom of baking dish.
Arrange slices of bread on top. Mix eggs, milk, vanilla and the remaining cinnamon until well blended.
Pour mixture over the bread, soaking and bread completely. Cover and refrigerate 4 to 24 hours.
Bake covered with aluminum foil in a preheated 375 degree oven for 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 more minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand 5 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix
first
ingredients and bring to boil and cook 1 minute.
Cut
vegetables
into bite-sized pieces.
Pour cooled mixture over vegetables and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Stir, in a large skillet, over medium-high heat, the chicken, onion and garlic, in oil, for about 10 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan in oven.
Mix baking mix, paprika, salt and pepper; coat chicken.
Place skin side down in pan.
Bake 35 minutes.
Turn; bake about 15 minutes or until done.

title: holiday (fruit) cake
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Cream the butter with the sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Mix together the flour, baking powder and salt. Add gradually to creamed mixture. Add vanilla and almond.
Dredge fruit and nuts with 1 cup flour.
Add to first mixture. Bake for 3 hours.
Makes a large cake.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Mix together; add 5 drops of red food coloring; put in large bowl and set overnight.
Keep cool in refrigerator before using.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add chili powder and salt and pepper to taste.
Soften tortillas in oil or in the microwave.
Fill each with 1 spoon of meat, cheese and onions.
Roll up and place, side by side, in a large greased casserole dish.
When ready to bake, add sauce.

title: zucchini chive dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
Serve with veggies or chips or both.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Put all ingredients in a kettle.
Stir to break up ground chuck.
Simmer until meat is done and chili is the desired thickness.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Blend ingredients in blender.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: buttermilk pecan chicken
directions: Whisk buttermilk with egg in a shallow bowl.
Combine breadcrumbs, paprika, salt, pepper and pecans on a separate plate or sheet of wax paper.
Dip chicken in buttermilk mixture, then place in breading; turn to coat both sides.
Heat oil and butter in a large non-stick skillet over medium-high heat; tilt skillet to coat bottom.
Add chicken and cook 3 to 5 minutes per side or until browned and crusty.
Remove from skillet when internal temperature of chicken reaches 165 degrees.
Serve immediately.

title: scrambled eggs
directions: Break eggs into small mixing bowl, being careful not to get any egg shell in the eggs.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Beat egg mixture with fork.
Place margarine in skillet; heat over medium heat until margarine is melted.
Pour egg mixture into skillet. Scramble with fork or spatula until eggs look fairly dry.

title: italian vegetable pizza squares
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Heat oil in nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add broccoli, cauliflower, carrot and garlic; cook 2 to 6 minutes until tender-crisp, stirring often.
Remove from heat and stir in green onions.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine sweetened condensed milk and key lime juice in a large bowl.
Beat heavy cream to stiff peaks.
Fold into milk mixture until blended.
Scoop filling into prepared crust.
Freeze until semi-frozen, at least 4 hours.
Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes before serving.

title: bread sticks
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Knead about 5 times.
Pour most of margarine into a cup and spread dough in the pan.
Pour melted butter on top.
Cut with pizza cutter into stick shapes.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Let stand in refrigerator 24 hours.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine and put in greased casserole.
Sprinkle with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin loaf
directions: Combine in large bowl all ingredients except the Crisco, sugar and eggs.
In a second bowl, cream the sugar, eggs and Crisco together.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with 1 1/2 cups pumpkin, beginning and ending with dry mixture.
Pour into pans and bake 1 hour.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Put rice on bottom of roaster and cover with onion soup and 1 can water.
Place chicken on top of rice and pour chicken soup, mixed with 1 can water, over top.
Bake 2 hours, uncovered, at 350° or until chicken is tender.

title: pizza dip
directions: In a small bowl mix cream cheese, sour cream, oregano and garlic powder.
Spread mixture in a 9-inch round baking pan. Spread pizza sauce on cheese mixture.
Sprinkle pepperoni, green onions, oregano and green peppers on top of the sauce.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Return to oven for another 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
(Can be prepared ahead of time and refrigerated until ready for baking.)
Serve with white corn chips and sliced green peppers for dipping.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all together and blend well.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve red hots in boiling water. Stir in raspberry or red jello. Stir well to dissolve. Add applesauce. When partially set, add celery and ground nutmeats. Serves 8 to 10.

title: brown edge cookies
directions: Combine flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Cream butter with sugar.
Add egg and milk.
Mix wet and dry ingredients; stir in vanilla.
Shape into walnut shaped balls. Space on a pan and flatten with a fork dipped in cold water.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until edges are tan, not brown!

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender and blend on high until all combined.
Pour into buttered 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: meat and potatoes quiche(kesh)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a 9-inch pie pan, stir together vegetable oil and grated potatoes.
Press evenly into pie crust shape.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until it begins to brown. Add the grated cheese, chicken, ham or sausage and onion in layers.
In a bowl, beat together the remaining ingredients.
Pour over cheese and meat; return to oven and bake at 425° for about 30 minutes or until lightly browned and knife inserted in from edge comes clean.

title: good brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° in a greased and floured 8-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine first three ingredients and spread on cookie sheet. Spread taco sauce on top of mixture.
Spread onion, lettuce, chopped tomatoes and shredded cheese on top of mixture.

title: green stuff
directions: Heat cocktail.
Add jello and mix.
At room temperature, add cream cheese.
Mix until blended with mixer.
Add Cool Whip and mix.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.

title: meat loaf bracciole
directions: Add enough water to mushroom liquid to make 1/2 cup.
In bowl, combine beef, 1/2 cup bread crumbs, egg, mushroom liquid, garlic powder and salt.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Combine; then press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: christmas morning cheese cloud(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Place 6 slices of buttered bread in buttered dish. Place 1/2 cheese and meat over bread. Add 6 slices of buttered bread, then rest of meat and cheese. Beat eggs. Add milk, onion and seasoning to eggs. Pour this over layered bread and meat. Place in refrigerator overnight. Bake at 350° in preheated oven 1 hour. Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together.
If too stiff, you may add a little milk.
Add pecans, chocolate chips, raisins and M&M's, whatever combination desired.
Drop on a cookie sheet; bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 dozen.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Mix in electric mixer at low speed, then at high speed 3 or 4 minutes.
Put in greased cake pan.
Place cake in cool oven and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and sprinkle with lime.
Add enough water to cover.
Allow to set overnight.
Rinse several times in cold water.
Cover and let set 4 hours in clean water.

title: cauliflower fritters
directions: Boil or steam cauliflower until cooked.
When cool, separate into flowerets.
Discard tougher ends of stalk and main stalk. Mash cauliflower with fork.
Beat in eggs, parsley, garlic and seasoning.
Form into patties and fry in oil until golden brown. Turn once.
A delicious change from potatoes or rice!

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour with soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and sugar into bowl.
Beat eggs until thick and light in color.
Add pumpkin, oil and water to beaten eggs.
Beat together. Turn mixture into the bowl in which the dry ingredients have been sifted.
Mix until smooth.
Place in 3 greased and floured loaf pans and bake for 1 hour or until done.

title: zucchini provencal
directions: Saute onion in oil in a skillet until tender.
Stir in zucchini, tomatoes, green pepper, garlic and seasonings; cover and cook over medium heat 10 to 12 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Transfer to a serving dish and sprinkle with cheese and parsley.

title: italian bean soup
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients in microwave for 15 minutes and add chicken stock, tomato sauce, salt, pepper and basil.
Cook additional 10 to 15 minutes until vegies are tender.
Add a good handful of egg noodles and navy beans.
Cook until noodles are done; serve with Italian cheese sprinkled on top.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Salt to taste.
Combine cooked ground beef, pizza sauce, milk, grated cheese, noodles, oregano and garlic powder in large baking dish.
Mix well.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours or longer.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: that cherry stuff
directions: Mix all together and chill in refrigerator.

title: cheddar hash browns
directions: Save enough cheese to sprinkle over top.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in glass pan at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Thoroughly mix pineapple and pudding mix.
Add marshmallows and fold in whipped topping.
I usually double this recipe.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Melt margarine and add sugar.
Stir well.
Add rest of cake ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 30-35 minutes.

title: sweet potato dinner rolls(makes 32 rolls)
directions: Combine yeast and water in blender.
Process for 30 seconds and let set for 5 minutes.
In a large bowl, sift flours together.
To yeast in blender, add sugar, salt, margarine, eggs and 1 cup of the flour mix.
Process until smooth.
Scrape down sides.
Add sweet potato and blend again.
Pour the blender mixture into the remaining flour in a big bowl.
Stir until well mixed to make nice soft dough.

title: snack crackers
directions: Place crackers in a large bowl.
Mix cooking oil, red pepper and Hidden Valley mix.
Pour over crackers.
Stir every 5 or 10 minutes until all oil is absorbed into crackers.
Store in tight container or Ziploc bag.
Can be frozen.
Serves 25.

title: hobo bake
directions: Prepare beef into moderate sized patties.
Place one patty on moderate size piece of tinfoil.
Add salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Throw in sliced carrots, onions and potatoes and close tinfoil.
Bake at 350° for one hour, or until patty is baked through.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Cream together margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients and mix, then stir in grated zucchini.
Pour into greased cake pan, 9 x 13-inch, and top with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° to 350°, depending on your oven, for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: potato patties
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix thoroughly.
Lightly dust hands with flour; shape into patties.
Oil skillet, if desired. Cook patties over medium heat until brown.
Flip and cook on remaining side.

title: petite cheesecakes
directions: Use vanilla wafer for crust.
Place wafer in each muffin tin lined with paper baking cup.

title: cool-rise sweet dough
directions: Measure flour; set aside.
Combine 2 cups flour, undissolved dry yeast, sugar and salt in a large bowl.
Stir to blend well. Add softened oleo.
Add hot water all at once.
Beat to blend well.
Add eggs and 1 cup more flour.
Beat well, until thick and elastic.
Stir in remaining flour gradually, with a wooden spoon. Use just enough flour to make a soft dough that leaves sides of bowl.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, flour, yolks of eggs, salt and milk.
Cook until thick.
Add flavoring and pour into baked pie crust.

title: tamale corn bread pie
directions: Saute onions in oil over medium-high heat until limp.
Add beef and cook just until brown.
Drain off liquid.
Place meat in large bowl.
Add beans in gravy, corn, tomatoes, green chilies, chili powder and salt.
Mix well.
Divide mix between two 2-quart oblong baking dishes.
Cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours or freeze 3 months.

title: m & m cookies
directions: Cream sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Mix flour, soda and salt.
Blend dry ingredients to creamed mixture; mix well.
Stir in M&M's.

title: hawaii's royal tea
directions: Bring 1 quart water to full rolling boil in saucepan.
Remove from heat and pour over tea. Stir and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir again and strain into pitcher containing 4 sprigs mint, sugar and remaining 1 quart cold water.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Cool tea. Remove mint, then chill, covered, several hours or overnight. Stir in lemon and pineapple juices.

title: delmonico potatoes
directions: In a 5-quart saucepan, make a roux over medium heat by melting butter and stirring flour until smooth.
Gradually stir in half and half, salt and pepper until smooth.
Reduce heat to low.
Add white Cheddar cheese and Parmesan cheese, stirring constantly, keeping consistency smooth.
Add diced potatoes, folding in gently until well covered and blended.
Allow to cook over low heat a few minutes.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat; place in a shallow 6 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with yellow cheese.
Place in hot 400° oven.
Bake until cheese melts.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dirty rice
directions: Bake in covered dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: rhubarb marmalade
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar. Put over low heat until sugar dissolves. Add Jell-O, mixing well. Let boil 10 minutes. Remove from heat. Put in jars.

title: cran-apple sparkler
directions: In medium saucepan, bring water and cranberry juice to a boil.
Add cinnamon apple herbal tea bags; cover and steep 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags; chill.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale.
Serve in ice filled glasses.
Makes about 5 (8-ounce) servings.

title: yogurt popsicles
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container.
Process until smooth.
Pour into popsicle molds.
Freeze until firm.
Unmold onto serving plates.
Yields 6 servings.

title: crumbler tart cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pie filling until well-blended (by hand).
Divide dough in half.
Spread one half by hand over ungreased 9x13 pan.
Spoon filling over dough.
One can per half of pan.
(I use 2 or 3 flavors).
Crumble other half of dough over top.
A grater may be used to crumble topping, if desired.
While working with first dough, put other in freezer--will grate much easier.

title: cheese ring
directions: Combine all ingredients, except preserves. Mix well. Chill. Mold into ring. Serve with strawberry preserves in center of ring and crackers around ring.

title: fudge sauce ala barbara
directions: Melt and stir together the chocolate and oil or butter.
Cook the sugar and milk to a full boil for 1 minute.
Combine.
Add vanilla and nuts after cooked.
Refrigerate.
Reheat as needed.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: In large saucepan, steam vegetables separately over boiling chicken broth until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes for each batch. Transfer to heated serving dish.
Warm salad dressing and spoon over vegetables.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: If using fresh sweet potatoes, cook until tender, 25 to 35 minutes.
Drain.
Cool slightly.
Peel and cut into chunks. Place in a 2-quart baking dish.

title: pink dessert
directions: Sprinkle Jell-O over cake squares.
Pour strawberries over cake mixture.
Freeze.

title: rice with chicken and cheese
directions: Chop onion and cook in oil until tender and lightly browned. Add chicken broth.
Heat to boiling and add rice.
Lower heat. Cover and cook about 25 minutes until rice is tender.
Add chicken and cheese.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Add salt and pepper.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt
butter until completely melted.
Add brown sugar; mix. Add
egg
at a time.
Add flour; mix well.
Let cool; then
add chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Pour into a baking pan. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: fruitcake
directions: Cream the cheese, oleo and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, then vanilla.
Add 2 cups flour and baking powder.
Into fruit and walnuts, put 1/4 cup flour.
Fold floured fruit into batter.
Bake 1 hour 10 minutes at 325° in a greased and floured tube pan.
Let cake cool in pan 25 minutes, then remove.

title: praline party mix
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Cook for 2 minutes more, stirring constantly.
Pour over cereal mixture.
Stir well.
Pour on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Stir and bake for 8 more minutes.
Pour on wax paper to cool.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream cocoa, butter and sugar.
Stir in whole egg; mix well. Alternately add flour and applesauce.
Stir in raisins, baking soda and spices.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for approximately 50 minutes in 375° oven.
Serve warm or cold and with whipped cream if desired.

title: herb baked fish
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, melt the butter in preheated 350° oven for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients and pile on hamburger buns.
Wrap in foil and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Good to freeze and bake later. Makes 8 small buns.

title: eclair cake
directions: Bring water and oleo to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour quickly until ball forms.
Add one egg at a time, mixing well by hand.
Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let crust cool.
Whip cream cheese in bowl.
Prepare pudding according to package.
Add cream cheese to pudding and beat.
Spread cheese mixture on crust.
Put Cool Whip on top and drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Put in refrigerator to set until time to serve.

title: popovers
directions: Mix salt and flour; add milk gradually to make a smooth batter using mixer on low speed.
Beat whole eggs until light and add to mixture.
Add butter.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Turn into "hissing hot" buttered iron cupcake tin.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes beginning with hot 450° oven.
Bake at 450° for 11 minutes, 400° for 11 minutes and 350° for 12 minutes, decreasing gradually to moderate oven (350°).

title: dressing
directions: Crumble breads up; add enough milk to moisten.
Add remaining ingredients and saute until onion and celery are tender.
Place in big casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 2 hours.

title: knobby apple cake
directions: Beat together butter and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Stir dry ingredients into the mixture.
Stir in chopped apples, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 8 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill.
Serve with vegetables.

title: hawaiian sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes just until tender; peel.
In medium bowl, mash potatoes.
Stir in pineapple to taste, 2 tablespoons butter, salt and pepper.
Spoon into 1-quart ungreased casserole.
Combine remaining butter with bread crumbs, brown sugar and allspice. Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven, 45 minutes.
Approximately 6 servings, 360 calories each.

title: sour cream coconut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and lightly flour a 10 inch Bundt pan or tube pan. In a small bowl, stir together the sour cream and coconut.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the cake mix, butter, eggs, water, and coconut flavoring.
Beat with an electric mixer on medium speed for about 3 minutes or until well blended. Stir in the sour cream and coconut mixture.
Pour the batter into the prepared pan.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into the center of the cake.
Allow the cake to cool in the pan for about 10 minutes. Turn out onto cake plate and allow to cool slightly before slicing.

title: hobo dinner(delicious and quick; low calorie)
directions: Make meat into 4 equal patties.
Place patties on sheet of foil.
Place vegetables on top, then strip of bacon.
Seal foil. Cook for 45 minutes on grill or in the oven.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk and water.
Layer in baking dish Tater Tots, soup mix, onion and cheese.
Repeat once, and top with mushrooms. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
If taking to a party, layer lettuce, tomatoes and pepper in bowl; cover with plastic wrap and place hamburg and cheese on top.
Keep taco chips in separate bag. Toss when ready to serve.
This prevents salad from becoming soggy.
This makes a large amount.

title: spicy ham sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook over moderate heat until thick, about 10 minutes.
Use for ham, pork or duck.

title: glazed apricot nectar cake
directions: Combine 1 lemon flavored 2 layer cake mix, sugar, apricot nectar and oil in large bowl; beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Pour batter into greased, floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° one hour or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool on rack, right side up, 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: ice cream sandwich cake
directions: 1st Layer:
Place 4 to 6 ice cream sandwiches in bottom of dish.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Drizzle chocolate syrup on top. Sprinkle with nuts (optional).

title: trisha's corn pudding
directions: Mix margarine, flour, sugar and salt over medium fire until well mixed. Add milk and water. Stir constantly until well mixed. Add corn and mix well with whisk. Remove from heat. Add beaten eggs and mix with whisk.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pan-fried catfish with cornmeal crust
directions: Place catfish fillets in buttermilk in shallow dish. Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Remove catfish from milk; sprinkle with salt.
Dip in cornmeal to coat both sides.
Heat oil in a large skillet over moderately high heat.
Add catfish.
Reduce heat to moderate; turn fish over carefully; cook 3 minutes or until browned and cooked through.
Carefully transfer to serving plates.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Mix with soup, sour cream and onions.
Put 2 to 3 tablespoons in the tortillas; top with cheese.
Roll tightly.
Mix a little broth with remaining chicken mixture.
Pour over enchiladas; top with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: crepe suzette
directions: In a large, flat skillet over medium heat, add butter and sugars; more brown sugar will yield a darker sauce.
Melt down sugars until they form a "caramel."
Add orange and lemon juices slowly to taste.
Sprinkle grated orange peel into mixture and lightly dust sauce with flour to thicken.
Fold in crepes, four per person, and cook until saturated with sauce.
Add Grand Marnier liqueur, about 1/4 cup, and carefully flame.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.
Serves 4.

title: jello cranberry salad
directions: Make Jell-O using 3 cups of hot water to 2 packages of Jell-O. Grind cranberries and oranges and mix into Jell-O.
Put in refrigerator to set.

title: homemade shortcake
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients with milk to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan, covered loosely with foil.
Cut wedge into bowl and top with fresh, sweetened strawberries or peaches and whipped topping.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: In jelly roll pan stir melted butter and brown sugar.
With fork mix in flour and nuts.
Distribute over bottom of pan (crumbs).
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, stirring once.
Let cool.
Prepare fruit.
In large mixing bowl beat egg whites to soft peaks, gradually adding the 1 cup sugar.
Add strawberries along with lemon juice.
Beat on high speed until triple in volume and stiff peaks form (about 20 minutes).
Fold in whipped cream. Arrange part of crumb mixture on bottom of 12 x 8-inch pan.
Add egg mixture.
Sprinkle remainder of crumbs on top.
Freeze.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer on cookie sheet, pie plate, flat dish, etc.
Use as tortilla dip.

title: easy divinity
directions: First, put Marshmallow Creme in bowl and let set.
In a small saucepan, combine sugar, salt and water.
Bring to soft ball stage, then pour mixture into Marshmallow Creme and beat with mixer until stiff peaks are formed.
Then stir in vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let set until firm.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer 15 minutes.
Good on chicken, beef, pork and wild game. Have a great barbecue.

title: mary's coconut pie(makes two pies)
directions: Mix together.
Pour into two deep dish unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: egg rolls
directions: Of course, you can use your favorite meat and vegetables as ingredients.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Saute ground beef until done and brown.
Wash and drain to remove grease.
Put back on heat, add salt and pepper.
Mix corn kit, corn, egg and onion.
Add Cheez Whiz and beef.
Mix well until Cheez Whiz is melted.
Pour into 9 x 12 x 2-inch well-greased pan. Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until brown.

title: gone all day stew
directions: Mix together soup, water and flour until smooth.
Combine with remaining ingredients in a covered roasting pan.
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
Serve with French bread to soak up gravy.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add flour, eggs, milk and vanilla.
(Lemon juice is optional.)
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Preheat oven to 450, then bake at 350 for 35 minutes.
Filling should be set and golden brown.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and add sauce and soups.
Make three layers of tortillas or crumble most of the package of chips on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Layer meat sauce, followed by a layer of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: good luck punch
directions: Combine grape juice, pineapple juice and sugar with 8 cups of cold water in 2 gallon container.
Add ginger ale.
Serve in punch bowl with ice ring.

title: banana oatmeal bread(diabetic recipe)
directions: Cream together margarine and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, soda and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with bananas and milk.
Add raisins, oatmeal and nuts.
Spoon batter into an 8 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Mix well 3 cups of hot water in jello mix.
Add blueberries and pineapple (do not drain).
Let chill.
Soften cream cheese to room temperature.

title: apple cake(very good, easy)
directions: Use large bowl and stir by hand.
Combine eggs and sugar.
Add oil, flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add nuts, raisins and apples.
Batter will be thick.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan, lightly greased.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool; drizzle on a glaze.
Powdered sugar with milk or powdered sugar mixed with boiling water.

title: luscious salad
directions: Drain and save juice.
Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add drained pineapple.
Chill until slightly thickened, about 1 1/2 hours.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add pineapple juice.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Mix in jello.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown
ground
beef,
onion
and
bell pepper.
Add soy sauce, salt
and
pepper.
Drain
well.
In 2 quart casserole dish, spread can of bean dip.
Top with meat mixture then pour taco sauce
over meat.
Top with cheese.
Next spread chopped tomatoes, then
green
onions.
Cook in oven at 325°.
Can be served as casserole and is great as dip served with chips.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Mix remaining ingredients together and put in casserole.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Add seasonings, butter	and
milk
to well mashed potatoes. When thoroughly blended, stir in beaten egg yolks, then fold in beaten egg	whites,
turn
into a dish, cover top with marshmallows and bake at 400° until marshmallows are brown.

title: crock-pot ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: Put half of ham, potatoes, onions and cheese in crock-pot. Sprinkle with salt and pepper, then add remaining half of ingredients.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Place fryer breasts and broccoli in layers in baking dish. Top with soup.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: summer potluck potato and green bean salad(very pleasant change)
directions: In a small saucepan, cover the quartered potatoes with salted water.
Bring quickly to a boil, then turn the heat back to medium and cook until tender, about 8 minutes.
Drain; immediately plunge into cold water to stop cooking.
Drain again.
Pat dry on paper towels and put in large salad bowl.

title: rosita fatler's baked chicken
directions: In baking dish, place chicken in single layer.
Drain and rinse sauerkraut; add to chicken with apple and onion.
Add wine, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Add small amount of water if dry after 1/2 hour.
Cover for last half of baking.

title: golden pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs with sugar; mix well. Add salt, vanilla, cornstarch, melted butter and corn syrup.
Mix well. Stir in pecan pieces or make a decorative top with halves.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Reduce to 325° for 45 minutes.
Bake until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean. Refrigerate.
Freezes well.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix hamburger, bread crumbs, egg and seasonings.
Make into patties or meatballs and fry.
Drain grease.
Add cream of mushroom soup, mixed with 1 can milk.
Pour on hamburger; let simmer for 15 minutes, or until soup thickens and flavor has gone through the meat.

title: k-bars
directions: Measure corn syrup and brown sugar into large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved and mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and raisins.
Add cereal.
Stir until coated.
With back of spoon, press mixture evenly and firmly into 13 x 9-inch pan, sprayed with Pam.
Let cool, cut into 20 bars.

title: homemade chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and buttermilk.
Beat well.
In small bowl, mix cocoa, soda, vanilla and hot water.
Add to first mixture.
This will seem to be thin, but it isn't.
Bake in 3 layers.
Frost with fudge frosting.

title: county fair baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 5

title: monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle pecans in the bottom of a well-greased 10-inch bundt pan. Set aside. Combine sugar and cinnamon in medium mixing bowl. Cut biscuits into quarters and roll each piece in sugar. Layer in bundt pan. Combine brown sugar and melted butter. Pour over dough. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cool 10 minutes in pan, then invert onto serving platter.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: tasty pretzels
directions: Mix first four ingredients together in a bowl.
Pour mixture over pretzels in roaster.
Stir.
Heat in oven at 225° for 10 minutes.
Stir and heat for another 10 minutes.
You can substitute oyster crackers for pretzels.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in about 1 cup chicken broth.
Add soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes, then diced chicken.
Dip corn tortillas in chicken broth just to soften a little.
Layer corn tortillas in casserole dish, then soup mixture and grated cheese until all is used.
Cheese is the last layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp cornbread
directions: Combine eggs, corn and oil; add cheese and mix.
Stir in corn meal, baking soda and salt; add shrimp, onions and jalapeno peppers and mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: beefy beans
directions: Combine ground beef, celery and onion in a large skillet. Cook until meat is browned and vegetables are tender. Drain mixture well.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: holiday pumpkin or banana bread
directions: Blend sugar and oil on medium speed of electric mixer and beat well.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add pumpkin or bananas and continue mixing at medium speed.
Add condiments and continue mixing at low speed.
Add flour, baking powder and soda to mixture.
Pour in two 9 x 2-inch greased loaf pans and bake at 325° for 65 to 70 minutes.
Test with toothpick for doneness. Serve warm or cold.

title: homemade bath crystals
directions: Pour Epsom salts into a metal or glass bowl.
In a separate cup mix glycerine, several drops of food coloring and perfume. Blend well.
Slowly add liquid mixture to Epsom salts, stirring until thoroughly mixed.
Store in a tightly sealed container.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pit cherries.
Cut up bananas and oranges.
Add marshmallows. Cook juice, sugar and egg together until thickened.
Cool and add to fruit mixture.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight. Before serving, sweeten whipped cream to taste and fold into fruit.

title: jogging in a jug
directions: Mix in a gallon jug.
Drain 2 ounces in morning and drink 2 ounces at night.
Lowers cholesterol.
Lowers blood pressure.
Is the equivalent of jogging three miles every day.

title: date nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates, shortening, sugar and salt; let cool.
Add remaining ingredients and beat by hand with wooden spoon.
Pour into greased and floured bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: pancake cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Using a 1/4 cup measure, drop batter in

title: citrus-strawberry punch
directions: Mix and chill in freezer until mushy, stirring every 20 minutes or so.
Makes about 6 quarts.

title: venison baked round steak
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Trim meat; cut into serving-sized pieces. Pound to about 1-inch thickness with meat mallet. On a sheet of wax paper, mix flour, salt and pepper. Dip

steaks in flour mixture, turning to coat. In large skillet, melt butter with vegetable oil over medium-high heat. Add steaks; brown both sides. During browning, may need additional butter and oil. Put steaks in large baking dish. Sprinkle with onion. Top each steak with 1 tablespoon brown sugar and catsup. Add beef broth to drippings in skillet. Cook over medium heat for about a minute to loosen any browned bits. Add to baking dish. Cover with foil. Bake about 45 minutes. Remove foil during last 10 to 15 minutes of baking. If meat appears dry, add small amount of broth and bake a few minutes longer.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter, sugar and peanut butter over low heat, stirring. Add Rice Krispies; stir until thoroughly coated.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Melt chocolate over a double burner.
Dip formed balls into melted chocolate.
Place on cookie sheet covered with wax paper. Refrigerate until chocolate hardens.

title: uncooked vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light colored.
Add sugar gradually until mixture thickens.
Add remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly. Freeze in a 1 1/2-gallon freezer.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer as listed.
You can place chips on bottom or just start stacking on a dish.
Let stand at least 6 hours in refrigerator.

title: chow-chow
directions: All vegetables need to be chopped.
Mix together.
Bring vinegar, water, sugar and salt to a boil.
Add vegetables and simmer 3 minutes.
Pack in jars and cook in hot water bath 5 minutes.
Makes 11 or 12 pints.

title: hot wassail
directions: Simmer apple juice and cinnamon 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 5 minutes more.
Serve hot.

title: peppy peppers
directions: Remove seeds from peppers.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Fill each pepper with approximately 1/3 cup rice mixture; place in shallow baking dish.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: smothered cabbage
directions: Cut the cabbage into quarters and remove the core.
Cut each quarter in half and then slice into 3/4-inch slices.
Wash and spin or pat dry.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook cut up squares and onion in boiling water for 5 to 8 minutes.
Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots. Fold in onions and zucchini.
Combine with margarine.
Grease casserole and spread 1/2 of stuffing mix on bottom of a 7 x 12-inch pan.
Spoon vegetable mixture over this.
Sprinkle rest of stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or hot throughout.

title: sloppy joes with rice
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper in skillet.
Drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, bring water and salt to boil.
Stir in rice. Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Serve meat over rice.
Garnish with shredded Cheddar cheese, if desired.

title: italian meat balls with sauce
directions: Mix all together.
Make into meat balls.
Broil under broiler until done.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Whisk eggs.
Add chocolate and remaining ingredients in order given.
Mix with wire whisk.
Last add pecans.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°
or until done.

title: e-z peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Pour peaches in on top of butter.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together and pour over peaches and butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Saute onion, celery and mushrooms until soft.
Cook cornbread and let cool.
Crumble into a bowl.
Mix all other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together (after egg is beaten).
Roll into about 1-inch balls; place on cookie sheet and press crisscross with fork.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: screwdriver cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bundt pan.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, pudding mix, 3/4 cup orange juice, vodka, oil and eggs.
Beat until smooth, and pour into bundt pan.
Bake for 45 minutes, or until toothpick inserted into middle of cake comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes in pan, then turn out onto wire rack.
Glaze with orange glaze.

title: baked beans, potatoes and franks
directions: Place
a layer of the pork and beans at the bottom of an ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Then add a layer of potatoes.
Then a layer of hot dogs.
Repeat layers.
Top with ketchup, salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: goulash
directions: In a large pot, brown ground beef with chopped onion; drain fat.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce, whole tomatoes and drained mushrooms.
Cook macaroni and add to the sauce.

title: sausage hash brown bake
directions: Brown and drain sausage.

Combine cheese and next 6 ingredients. Fold in hash browns. Spread 1/2 mixture into greased casserole dish. Top with sausage and rest of potato mixture. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover. Bake 10 minutes or until heated through.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour 1/2 into pan and bake 15 minutes.
Over low heat, combine caramels, milk and 1 stick of margarine.
Slowly heat until caramels melt and solution is thick (stir continuously).
Pour mixture over cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour remaining cake mix on top and bake 15 to 20 minutes until done.

title: egg bake
directions: Cook bacon and drain and crumble it.
Sprinkle evenly in baking dish.
Beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and dry mustard together; pour over bacon. Add bread cubes, pimentos and mushrooms. Sprinkle with chives. Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.
To check, use a butter knife.
If it comes out clean, it is done. Makes 10 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together sugar, oil and eggs.
Add pumpkin, flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and baking soda; blend well.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mandarin rice salad
directions: Mix rice, oranges, celery, green pepper and 1/4 cup almonds in a medium size bowl.
In a small bowl blend mayonnaise, lemon juice, seasoned salt and pepper.
Add to rice mixture and toss well.
Chill.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Brown onion in butter; combine cream of chicken soup, mushroom soup, chicken broth and green chilies.
Add pieces of chicken and mix well.
In a baking dish place a layer of tortilla chips, a layer of chicken sauce and a layer of grated cheese.
Repeat the layers until the casserole is filled.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: halloween punch
directions: Mix well and garnish with orange slices.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Beat eggs, margarine, sweetener and vanilla together.
Sift flour with soda, cloves and cinnamon.
Add to first mixture.
Fold in raisins, applesauce and nuts.
Pour into a Bundt pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Divide cake into 25 equal portions.
Each portion equals:
1 bread, 1 1/2 fat and 1 fruit exchange.

title: microwave stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes as directed by your microwave.
Cut thin slice from the top of each potato. Scoop out inside leaving a thin shell. Add remaining ingredients except 1/4 cup cheese and paprika to potatoes.
Mash until no lumps remain.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown chops in pan that can be put in oven (with Crisco) on both sides.
Remove from pan and stir in onion and Minute rice until lightly browned.
Add soup.
Stir and place chops on top. Bake 45 minutes in a 325° to 350° oven.
Serve with tossed salad and French bread.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt and baking powder in a large mixing bowl.
In a small bowl, combine oil, eggs and strawberries.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve sugar and Kool-Aid in water.
Add tea and pineapple juice.
Add cold water to make 1 gallon.
Shake well.

title: green wonder salad
directions: Put vegetables in bowl and mix together 1 cup sugar and 3/4 cup vinegar, 1 1/2 cups thinly sliced celery and 1 teaspoon salt. Mix all together and pour over vegetables, stir and refrigerate overnight in covered container.

title: greek cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl and make a well in the center. Put in margarine and yogurt.
Mix lightly by hand, pulling flour from sides of bowl into the well until flour is incorporated and dough is soft and pliable.
Roll small pieces of dough into short, cigar-size shapes and turn tapered ends into S shape.
Arrange cookies on lightly greased baking sheet.
Brush tops with egg/water mixture; sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes until golden.
Cool and store in cookie tin.

title: excellent peanut butter pie
directions: Spoon 1/2 cup fudge topping into bottom of pie crust. Gently spread half of the whipped topping over fudge topping; place in freezer for 10 minutes. Pour milk into large bowl; stir in peanut butter until smooth. Add pudding. Beat with wire whisk for 2 minutes or until smooth. (Mixture will be thick.) Immediately stir in remaining whipped topping. Spoon over layers in pie crust.

title: ham and beans with dumplings
directions: Cook ham until very tender.
I like to cook mine all day in the crock-pot with a little water.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together and make into a loaf or loaves.
Mix soups and milk.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Potatoes and carrots may be added, too!

title: weight watcher's casserole
directions: Saute onions and beef.
Add tomato sauce, spices and mushrooms.
Squeeze liquid from spinach and mix with cottage cheese.
Cut Mozzarella into strips.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until cheese melts and is bubbly.

title: christmas red satin punch
directions: Mix together and serve cold.
Makes 30 cups.

title: busy day stew
directions: Mix soups together.
Add 1 can water.
Place all ingredients in casserole.
Bake 2 to 3 hours at 325°.
Serve over any pasta. "Simple and delicious."

title: grated pumpkin bread(yield: 1 loaf)
directions: Cover raisins with water to plump.
Beat eggs thoroughly and mix in sugar, oil, pumpkin and vanilla.
Sift together remaining ingredients.
Mix into pumpkin mixture, beating well.
Drain raisins and stir into the batter; pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on rack for 15 minutes before turning out of pan.

title: sweet and sour pork (chicken)
directions: Combine 3 tablespoons pineapple juice with water, cornstarch, soy sauce, vinegar and pepper flakes.
Set aside.

title: snowball cake
directions: Add the water, pineapple juice, pineapple, sugar and salt to the dissolved gelatine.
Jell until partially set.
Beat the Dream Whip and fold into first mixture.
Break angel food cake in pieces; mix well with gelatine mixture.
It will take a large bowl to mix in.
Let set overnight.
Whip 1 package of Dream Whip for top.
Cover with coconut and maraschino cherries.

title: easy cobbler - peach, cherry, apple
directions: Melt butter and pour in the bottom of a 9 x 11-inch baking pan.
Make batter of 1 cup sugar, flour, powder powder, salt and milk.
Mix and pour batter over melted butter.
Spoon in fruit with juice.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over the batter.
Do not stir. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: steve's chocolate chinese cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips in microwave in a glass bowl.
Add noodles and peanuts.
Spoon mixture onto waxed paper and cool.
Keep in refrigerator.
Makes about 7 dozen cookies.

title: grilled peaches with raspberry puree
directions: Combine raspberries and lemon juice in container of blender. Cover and process until smooth.
Strain raspberry puree, discarding seeds.
Cover and chill.
Place peach halves, cut side up, on heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon.
Spoon evenly into center of each peach half.
Sprinkle with rum flavoring and dot with margarine.
Fold foil over peaches and seal loosely. Place grill rack over medium coals.
Place peach bundle on rack and cook 15 minutes or until peaches are thoroughly heated.
To serve, spoon 2 tablespoons raspberry puree over each grilled peach half.

title: fig turnovers
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and cook slowly until thick.
Cool. Roll biscuits as thin as possible.
Place a tablespoon of mixture on half of the biscuit.
Moisten edges and fold other half over the filling.
Pinch edges together; prick top.
Place in hot oven at 450°.
Brown as you would biscuits.
Makes 6 servings.

title: *microwave pan gravy
directions: Put fat and flour into a 4-cup glass measuring cup.
Stir until smooth.
Microwave on High power 5 to 7 minutes, stirring twice, until mixture turns golden and loses its raw flour taste. Stir in juices.
Microwave on High, stirring twice, until gravy bubbles fast and thickens, 4 to 6 minutes.
Taste.
Add salt and pepper.
Adjust consistency with more stock or broth as desired.

title: brown sugar cookies(soft)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make balls size of walnut.
Place on greased cookie sheet and press with fork (dipped in cold water). Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Be sure to watch these.
Seven minutes is usually enough. Do not allow to brown.

title: creamy lemon pineapple mold
directions: In bowl, pour boiling water over gelatin.
Stir until Jell-O dissolves.
Gradually beat hot Jell-O into cream cheese until cream cheese melts and mixture is smooth.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 8-cup mold, lightly brushed with salad oil.
Chill until firm.
Makes about 12 servings.

title: spanish chicken and rice(aros compoio)
directions: Put all the ingredients in large pan.
Cover, cook in oven at 350° for 1 hour (until water is gone).

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done. Shred chicken and place in bottom of casserole dish. Cook Stove Top stuffing as directed on the box. Spread stuffing on top of chicken (do not mix).
Mix soups together in a separate bowl and spread on top of stuffing layer. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until soup mixture is slightly browned.
Add Durkee onions to top of casserole and bake until they are browned.

title: easy tacos
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes in 400° oven or until brown.
Cook ground beef.
Drain.
Stir in taco mix and water.
Cook slowly 10 to 12 minutes.
Spread on crescent rolls and add cheese (I use Velveeta) on top.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Pour liquid off oranges. Use this liquid in cake mix later.
Mix oranges into cake mix. Bake in 3 prepared pans.
After cooling, use the following icing.

title: diabetic big batch muffins for freezer
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add Sugar Twin, syrup, oil, soda, baking powder and spices.
Alternate flours with coffee and milk.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Melt bacon grease in 10-inch skillet. Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour in skillet and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Reduce heat to 400°.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Microwave butter in an 8-inch round dish about 30 seconds to melt butter.
Scrub potatoes but do not peel.
Cut each lengthwise into 8 pieces.
Dip into melted butter; arrange peel side down in baking dish.
Combine cheese, salt and paprika.
Sprinkle evenly over potatoes.
Cover with paper towel.
Microwave at High for 10 to 11 minutes or until potatoes are almost done, rotating dish once or twice.
Let stand a few minutes to finish cooking before serving.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Cream together the shortening, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add the egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend in the dry ingredients gradually; mix thoroughly.
Shape by rounded teaspoonfuls; roll into balls.
Roll in sugar; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and place a solid chocolate candy kiss on top of each one, pressing down so that cookie cracks around the edge.
Return to oven; bake 2 to 5 minutes longer.

title: frosty grapes
directions: Wash grapes and drain.
Place in bowl with lid.
Empty jello mix into bowl.
Place lid on bowl and shake, coating grapes with jello powder.
Freeze in bowl.

title: old fashioned peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in baking dish.
Combine self-rising flour and 1 cup sugar.
Cut in 1/4 cup butter.
Stir in milk.
Cover peaches with batter.

title: holiday eggs
directions: Saute green pepper and onion.
Remove crusts from bread; butter both sides.
Line 9X13 pan with 8 slices of bread.
Mix cheese, pepper, onion and mushrooms and spread HALF of that mixture over bread.
Layer with remaining 8 slices of bread and cover with remaining cheese mixture.
Mix together eggs, milk, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt & pepper; pour over bread and cheese layers.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: apple-raisin muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl.
Make well in center.
Stir together buttermilk, applesauce, egg whites and oil in a small bowl.
Pour mixture into well of dry mixture.
Stir just until moistened.
Gently fold in apples and raisins. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Mix butter and graham cracker crumbs together and press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer remaining ingredients in order.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while hot.

title: microwave ham and cheese rolls
directions: Mix margarine and mustard together and get warm.
Slice rolls and brush both sides with butter mixture and finely chopped onions. Slice entire top of package of rolls.
Leave bottom layer in pan. Spread with slices of ham and cheese.
Put top layer of rolls on top, leave in foil pan and cover with Saran Wrap.
Freeze.
Bake in microwave 15 to 20 minutes when ready to serve or 350° in oven for 5 minutes.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Cut meaty spareribs into servings. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place in a roasting pan and cover with onions.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste occasionally, turning spareribs once or twice.
Remove cover from pan during the last 15 minutes of baking.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
Blend bread crumbs with cheese, parsley, butter, garlic and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Fill the mushrooms with this mixture.
Pour 2 tablespoons olive oil in the bottom of the baking pan and place the mushrooms in the pan, stuffed side up.
Pour 4 more tablespoons olive oil over the mushrooms, being sure all are well covered with oil. Bake about 20 minutes at 375° or until mushrooms are tender and tops are golden brown.

title: butternut squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 1 1/2-quart casserole with Pam. In large bowl combine all ingredients.
Pour into dish.
Bake until set, 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: In bottom of 8-inch pan, place rhubarb, 1 cup sugar, marshmallows or orange slices.
Pour first 8 ingredients that have been mixed together on top of rhubarb, sugar and marshmallows or candy and bake in 350° oven until cake is done.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix everything except corn oil in blender, then add oil slowly in small amounts and blend until thick.
Store in refrigerator.

title: all-game dressing
