directions: Clean meat good of all blood, then soak overnight in cold salt water.
Drain good next morning.
Then flour, salt and pepper good.
(All may be mixed together.)
Brown in deep fat in skillet for about a half hour, making sure both sides are good and brown, then take squirrel and put in a roaster, adding garlic, either powder or solid form.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream
shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add flour and soda; add mashed bananas and nuts.
Stir in vanilla. Grease and
flour	loaf pans, whatever size you like.
Divide batter equally.
Bake
in slow oven at 325° for 1 hour.
This makes 2 large or 3 small loaves.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: soft stir-drop sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs with fork until well blended. Stir in oil, vanilla and lemon rind.
Blend in sugar until mixture thickens.
Measure flour by dip-level-pour method.
Mix flour, baking powder, and salt, blend into oil mixture.
Drop by tsp. about 2-inch apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Gently press each cookie flat with bottom of glass that has been moistened and dipped in sugar.
Bake 8-10 minutes.
Remove immediately from baking sheet.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Put in heavy saucepan and cook until melted and thickened. Cool.
Put in jars for gifts.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chocolate dipped snowballs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Butter and flour baking sheet.
In med. bowl combine coconut and cornstarch, set aside.

title: butterscotch nut baked apples
directions: Combine sugar, butter and syrup.
Add pecans.
Place in shallow baking dish; top with apples, cut side down.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes, basting twice.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and 1/2 package taco mix.
Fry beef with 1/2 taco mix; drain.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Mix.
Add 2 tablespoons plus 1 teaspoon mixture for each cup of boiling water.

title: debbie's chicken pan pie
directions: Boil chicken.
Cool and pick off bones.
Put in baking dish. Salt and pepper.
Add soup and broth.
Pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing by directions.
Place on chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until brown.
One can of Veg-All can be added.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix together molasses, sugar and oil.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Sift together flour, ginger, cloves, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Add gradually to mixture.
Last, add boiling water.
Batter will be thin.
Bake 40 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: spinach squares
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix ingredients together and spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: crab dip #2
directions: Bring to room temperature, cream together and bake, until starts bubbling, at 350°.
Serve on crackers.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream together shortening and peanut butter.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients gradually, mixing thoroughly.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove cookie sheet from oven; place candy kiss on each cookie so cookie crackers around the edge.
Return cookies to oven and bake for 2 to 5 minutes longer.

title: veal ball stew
directions: Mix all ingredients, except veal, cinnamon and sweetener. Place over low heat.
Cook until vegetables are tender but crisp.

title: any fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter or margarine in baking dish.
Mix sugar, milk and flour.
Pour into dish on top of melted butter.
Spoon in fruit. Bake at 350° until golden brown, approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: turkey cassoulet
directions: In a large saute pan, cook onion in butter until soft and translucent.
Add broth, bay leaf, salt and thyme.
Drain and discard liquid from beans and add beans to pan.
Stir in tomato paste and mix well.
Add turkey cubes and smoked sausage pieces. Turn into a 2 1/4 to 2 1/2 quart stove-to-table casserole dish. Cover and bake in 350° preheated oven for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake for an additional 10 to 15 minutes until hot and bubbly. Serve with a crusty French bread and an assortment of cheese and fresh fruit.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jeff davis pie
directions: In a large skillet, mix dry ingredients well.
Add egg yolks to a cup of milk and mix well, then add to dry mixture with the remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick over medium heat.
Be sure to stir while cooking.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with meringue and brown in oven about 3 minutes, or top with Cool Whip.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon and crumble.
Mix all ingredients into salmon. Pour in buttered loaf pan or dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, adding mushrooms and onions to your taste. Drain.
Cook noodles as directed and drain.
Mix soup with ground beef. Add to noodle mixture.
Place in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Pour 1/2 cup of milk over mixture.
Bake at 350° until bubbling.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Spread rice in oblong (9 x 13-inch) Pyrex dish.
Place chicken on top of rice.
In another pan, heat soups; pour over chicken. Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken and rice.

title: gazpacho(cold vegetable soup)
directions: Finely chop, but do not mince, the onion.
Set aside. Coarsely chop the pepper, cucumber and garlic. Put half the pepper, cucumber, garlic and tomatoes in a blender.
Add half the tomato juice, olive
oil, and vinegar.
Blend just until the vegetables are medium chopped, but thoroughly blended.
They should be neither too chunky, nor pureed.
Transfer the vegetables to a large bowl.
Place the remaining half of the pepper, cucumber, garlic, and tomatoes in the blender.
Add the remaining tomato juice, olive oil and vinegar, and blend as before. Add to the bowl with the first half.
Stir in the reserved chopped onion, Tabasco, black pepper, and salt.
Chill until ready to serve. When ready to serve, sprinkle each serving with chopped parsley and pass the croutons.
Yield 8 servings.

title: meringue
directions: Combine 1/4 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan. Stirring constantly, add water and cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute; cool completely.

title: carrots elegante
directions: Cook carrots in 1/2-inch boiling water for 8 minutes.
Drain. Turn carrots into a 1-quart baking dish.
Stir in raisins, oleo, honey, lemon juice and ginger.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 35 minutes.
Stir occasionally; spoon into serving bowl. Sprinkle with almonds.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mama's parmesan chicken
directions: Bone chicken and season with garlic powder; set aside.
Mix together bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Dip chicken into egg batter; drain slightly.
Place chicken into bread crumbs.
In frying pan, pour moderate amount of Crisco cooking oil; fry chicken lightly, slightly browning both sides.
In casserole dish, bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cover dish with foil to seal in juices.

title: iron men cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Beat in egg and molasses.

Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture. Mix all ingredients together. Roll into a ball; cover and chill mixture for at least 2 hours. You may also chill the dough overnight. Roll dough 1/8-inch thick for crisp men; 1/4-inch thick or thicker for soft fluffy guys. Cut with floured cutters. Usually I make them round (about 1 1/2 to 2-inches). Or you can cut them into gingerbread-men. I make the guys with a cutter about 2 to 3-inches high. Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, depending on the thickness of the cookies. I always double the recipe. These guys age well and keep nicely. They are great to freeze.

title: hobo ribs
directions: Simmer strips, covered, in boiling salted water in a kettle 1 hour or just until tender; drain.
When ready to grill, thread strips, accordion-style, onto long skewers.
Mix catsup, barbecue sauce and corn syrup in a small saucepan.
Brush part over ribs. Place on grill about 6 inches above hot coals.
Grill, turning and brushing often with remaining sauce, 20 minutes or until richly glazed.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender and cut into medium chunks.
Cook rice with seasoning as directed on box.
Mix together soup, pimento, beans, water chestnuts, mayo, salt and pepper.
Add chicken and rice; mix and pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown beef and add wine; simmer until wine is cooked up.
Add all ingredients, except hot roll mix, to meat.
Cover with water; simmer until potatoes are well done, about 2 hours.
Serve with bread sticks.

title: oil pastry
directions: Mix flour, salt and oil.
Add 3 tablespoons cold water.
Divide dough, slightly larger ball for bottom crust.
Roll out between wax paper.
Peel off top wax paper and lay bottom paper with crust over 9-inch pie plate.
Peel off wax paper and fit crust into plate. Trim and flute or if using top crust also, flute and trim after placing over filling.
Bake.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Chop shrimp before adding to mixture.

title: dirty rice
directions: Put butter in black skillet until melted.
Add rice and cook on high until rice browns.
Add water.
Reduce heat.
Place lid over it and simmer until done.

title: fried biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add milk and mix well.
(May have to add a few more drops of milk if too dry.) When dough is firm, pat out on well floured flat surface to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Slice into pieces 3/4-inch.
Fry in 1/2-inch deep hot oil.
Brown both sides.

title: gingerbread people
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together and set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar together in a bowl.
Combine the dry and moist ingredients together.
Roll out with rolling pin and use cookie cutter or give your child part of the dough to create a person on waxed paper.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 325° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Open oven slowly.
Makes approximately 1 1/2 dozen.

title: blueberry-sour cream torte
directions: Combine berries, sugar, tapioca, peel and spices.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Turn into crust.

title: rosie's vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Serve with green pepper, green onions, broccoli, cauliflower, etc.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Boil raisins in small saucepan with 3/4 cup water.
Mix sugars, eggs and shortening.
Add raisins and water.
Add all dry ingredients.
Spoon onto cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together cautiously.
Beat eggs and milk until frothy.
Add sugar and salt.
Mix with melted chocolate and butter.
Fold in nuts.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and peanuts in a 2 quart microwavable container.
Stir to mix.
Microwave on high for 4 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave for an additional 3 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir.
Microwave for another 2 minutes. Remove from microwave. Quickly stir in the baking soda. Do not overstir.
Pour immediately onto a well buttered baking sheet. Allow to cool completely.
Break into pieces.

title: grandma smith's pecan pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add beaten eggs, flour or vinegar, salt, extract and syrup.
Stir well. Add pecans.
Pour in unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° until golden brown, approximately 1 hour.

title: grannie's no cook fruit cake
directions: Mix together crackers, pecans, walnuts and dates.
In double boiler, heat milk and marshmallows until marshmallows are melted. Pour over the cracker mixture.
This will be real stiff and will need to be mixed by hand.
If necessary, you may want to add a little Pet milk.
Mix well.
Pack in loaf pan lined with wax paper.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mary ann's 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle rest of ingredients over margarine, graham cracker crumbs, chips, coconut and nuts. Drizzle Eagle Brand over top. Do not stir. Bake at 350° about 25 minutes. Cut into bars.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt oleo, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Pour over cereal.
In a brown sack, shake powdered sugar and cereal together.
Store in airtight container.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until thawed.
Drain.
Place broccoli in casserole dish.
Mix soup, cheese and mayonnaise in bowl.
Spread over broccoli evenly.
Crush crackers.
Spread evenly over cheese mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: aunt e's sweet potato supreme
directions: Cook yams 6 minutes on High in 1/2 syrup in microwave.
Drain. Whip potatoes and butter until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients and continue whipping until fluffy again.
Put in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: kathy's flo's dessert
directions: Mix well and press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: nan's meat loaf
directions: Mix together hamburger crumbs, egg and cheese.
Form into loaf.
Put in pan and bake 30 to 45 minutes.
Drain grease.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over loaf.
Sprinkle with 1 to 1 1/2 cups Mozzarella cheese.
Bake another 30 to 45 minutes.
Cheese should be slightly browned on top.
Serves 6.

title: corn relish
directions: Cook 15 minutes; pack in jars and seal.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt Milky Ways and 1 stick of butter; set aside and let cool.
Cream together sugar and 1 stick butter.
Add eggs.
Mix soda with buttermilk and add alternately with cake flour.
Add Milky Way mixture until creamy, then vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Let cool in pan 30 minutes, then cover with icing.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cover cabbage leaves with boiling water and let stand until limp; drain.
Combine the next 7 ingredients.
Place equal portions of meat mixture in the center of each cabbage leaf.
Roll up and fasten with toothpicks.

title: flaky pineapple squares(unleavened)
directions: Cut butter into flour.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Heat pineapple, sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Roll 1/2 of dough into flat pan.
Spread cooled filling and cover with rest of dough, rolled out a little.
Bake until brown, cool and sprinkle top with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix ingredients as listed and beat well with electric mixer. Pour into greased and floured cake pans.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cool layers 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: rutabaga casserole
directions: Dice peeled rutabagas and cook until tender in small amount of water; drain.
Fry bacon crisp; set aside.
Saute onion in bacon grease.
Add onion, bacon, soup, parsley and pepper to rutabagas. Salt to taste.
Simmer slowly until all flavors are well blended.

title: nonnie's cookies
directions: Cream cold margarine for about 5 minutes. Add sugar gradually. Add vinegar and vanilla. Mix baking soda to flour and add to margarine mixture. Blend in nuts. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 15 minutes in 325° oven (middle rack). Makes approximately 48 cookies.

title: fruit cake dark
directions: Mix as listed.
Bake in tube pan at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours until done.
Put a pan of water on bottom rack.

title: poppy seed dressing(makes 1 quart)
directions: Put onion in blender; liquify.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt and dry mustard.
Blend.
Add oil a little at a time and blend.
Just before finishing blending, add poppy seed.
Store in refrigerator. Shake well before using.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook juices, water, cornstarch and sweetener until thick. Cool.
Add fruit in quantities to suit your taste.
Serve cold.

title: crazy crust recipe
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Spread batter thinly on bottom and thickly on sides of a 9-inch or 10-inch pie pan that has been lightly greased and floured.
Bake at 425°.
Use this crust for the Barbecued Beef Dinner.

title: triple-layer jam cake
directions: Beat the first 6 ingredients at low speed with an electric for 1 minute.
Scrape down sides, and beat at medium speed 2 more minutes until well blended, stopping to scrape down sides, if needed.
Pour batter evenly into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 23 minutes or until cakes are light brown and spring back when lightly pressed with your fingers. Cool in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely on wire racks.

title: ungarische goulasch suppe
directions: Saute onions over medium high heat in a Dutch oven until translucent, but not brown.
Add meat and brown until almost cooked.
Reduce the liquid in the pan until almost gone, being careful not to scorch.
Once reduced, add tomato paste, paprika, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent burning.
Add remaining seasonings and cover with enough water to just cover the meat.
Simmer for 1/2 hour and adjust seasonings to taste.

title: yams
directions: Place in skillet and let cook on medium heat until it forms a syrup.

title: fat-free carrot pineapple muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda and cinnamon.
Stir and mix well.
Add pineapple with juice, prune puree, egg whites and vanilla.
Stir until moistened.
Fold in carrots and pecans. Coat muffin pans with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes.

title: lamb barley soup
directions: Melt butter in large pan; add lamb, onions and celery and cook until lamb is lightly browned, stirring often.
Pour off most of the fat.
Add carrots, peas, bay leaves, barley, water, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring often.
Add parsley. Serve piping hot.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix and cook sugar, Carnation and butter to soft ball stage. Be sure it's at that stage.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat together thoroughly and pour onto greased cookie sheet.

title: pennsylvania dutch potato filling
directions: Brown onion in oil.
Mix potatoes, eggs and bread together. Pour milk on top.
Add onions, salt and pepper.
Mix all well.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Fry meat in hot oil.
Add mushrooms, rice, green onion and soy sauce.
Fry over low heat 10 minutes.
Add 1 well beaten egg; cook and stir 5 minutes more.
If color isn't dark enough, add a little more soy sauce.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: old fashioned coconut pie
directions: Blend sugar and butter.
Add eggs, vanilla, vinegar and coconut.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: deb's breakfast corn bread
directions: Arrange sausage links in 8-inch square glass baking dish. Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Pour off any accumulated fat.
Drain tomatoes, saving juice.
Add tomatoes and corn to sausages, prepare muffin mix as directed on package, using eggs and 2/3 cup tomato juice for the liquid.
Pour over ingredients in baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 30 minutes or until corn bread is done. Cut into squares or spoon out to serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook on top of stove until thickened.
Pour into a loaf pan and bake at 375° until browned, about 1 1/2 hours.
Grease pan lightly.

title: apple bread
directions: Make a well in the center. Blend eggs, vanilla and oil well. Pour into the dry ingredients. Mix well, then stir in apples or can of sliced apples. Blend well. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tested done.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Drain macaroni (or noodles).
Heat soup, milk and cheese until cheese melts.
Then mix with other ingredients.
Put into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake about 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly at 400° to 425°.
tags: cream of chicken soup or celery soup

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In a skillet, cook mushrooms in butter until tender.
Stir in flour; gradually add the chicken broth.
Cook, stirring constantly until sauce comes to a boil.
Remove from the heat; stir in cream, parsley, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Fold in chicken and spaghetti. Turn into a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: beefy corn bread
directions: Saute 1 1/2 pounds of ground meat until light brown.
Drain and set aside.
Add drippings into 1 cup yellow corn meal, milk, eggs, salt, soda and creamed corn.
Mix well.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of yellow corn meal into a greased iron skillet.
Pour half of the corn meal batter in the skillet.
On top of the batter, sprinkle the following: all the meat, chopped onion, shredded cheese and jalapenos.
Pour rest of batter on top.
Cook in a 350° oven for about 50 minutes.
Serve with salad.

title: japanese casserole
directions: Grate carrots, potatoes and onion.
Spray a nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Saute onion until transparent.
Mix ground chuck or turkey, carrots, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Shape into meat balls.
Cook meat balls in a sprayed skillet until brown. Place cooked meat balls in a single layer in a large baking dish. Mix soup and milk together.
Pour mixture over meat balls; bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 355°.
Grease and flour loaf pans.
Beat eggs; add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Cream together.
Add sifted dry ingredients and then stir in nuts.
Mix well.
Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: crabbies
directions: Split English muffins and heat in 350° oven until lightly toasted.
Mix remaining ingredients; spread on muffins.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes at 350°.
Cut into quarters.

title: greenbrier grilled chicken salad
directions: Boil and chop eggs.
Chop celery and carrots (finely).
Cut tomatoes into wedges; thinly slice cucumber.
Grill and slice chicken.
Chop lettuce.

title: lemon gelatin salad
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water, then stir in pineapple and chill until partially set.
Add sour cream and stir.
Fold in carrots and cheese.
Pour in 9-inch square pan and chill until set.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: brisket
directions: Mix soups and ketchup.
Spread over frozen brisket.
Wrap tightly in heavy-duty foil.
Bake at 250° to 275° for 8 hours. Serve with Minute rice and a frozen vegetable for a quick dinner.

title: cooked carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots and drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Add soup, salt, pepper and cheese.
Pour over carrots.
Place in greased casserole.
Put buttered bread crumbs on top (or stuffing).
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Pierce skin of eggplant several times; arrange eggplant on paper towel on glass oven tray.
Heat 6 to 9 minutes until eggplant is almost tender.
Let cool, then peel, if desired, and slice into 1/2-inch pieces.

title: lazy day casserole
directions: Place sliced potatoes in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer meat and onion.
Mix 1/2 can vegetable soup and 1 can mushroom soup. Pour over mixture, then rest of vegetable soup.
Put lots of grated bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cherry squares
directions: Grease and flour 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Combine oleo and sugar; cream together. Add eggs and beat well. Stir in flour gradually. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Pour into pan.
Score into 24 sections. Spoon 2 to 3 cherries into each section. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Remove. Drizzle with glaze or serve with topping.

title: chicken-treat
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add spinach, cover and cook until wilted.
Add salt and pepper.
Preheat oven to 375°.
With chicken, smooth side down, pound lightly to 1/4-inch thickness.
Place 1/4 of cheese, 1/2-inch wide strip of pimento and 1/4 mixture of spinach on each breast half.
Roll each half lengthwise.
Place in baking dish with 1/4 cup broth.
Cover and bake 20 minutes.
Puree remaining pimiento with 1/4 cup broth.
Spoon over chicken before serving.
Makes 4 servings. Contains 256 calories.

title: honey wheat bread
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the water and let set 5 minutes.

title: hearty ham casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Place in bowl and mix with other ingredients except potato chips.
Pour mixture into buttered 2-quart casserole dish and top with potato chips.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350° until thoroughly heated.

title: tupsicles
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well, then add cold water.
Stir and pour into ice cube trays.
Insert popsicle stick in center when slightly frozen.
Freeze.

title: peanut butter ice cream
directions: If you use sugar, you will have to guess at the amount (just sweeten to suit your taste).
Mix well and pour into a 1 gallon freezer and fill with 1% milk.
Freeze and eat.

title: crunchy parmesan chicken
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Melt butter. Dip chicken in butter. Roll in dry mixture and place in shallow pan.
Do one piece at a time.
Sprinkle any remaining dry mixture over coated pieces. Pour remaining butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: happy dogs
directions: Combine brown sugar, bourbon and ketchup in a large saucepan. Add the wieners and simmer 3 hours.
Make enough for a crowd.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix water, yeast and sugar until foamy.
Add oil, salt and flour, a little at a time.
Dough should be a little sticky.
Put in oiled bowl.
Let rise 1 hour.
Knead.
Make your rolls; let rise again for 1 hour.

title: orange nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs one at a time. Add rest of ingredients. Bake at 275° for 2 hours.

title: island banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 4 x 8-inch loaf pan.
Combine both types of flour, brown sugar, baking powder and spices; mix well.
In separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Beat with fork until blended.
Blend together.
Place mixture in prepared pan.
Bake 35 minutes until center is done.
Cool on wire rack.

title: russian dressing chicken
directions: Dissolve soup mix in water.
Add other ingredients.
Place 4 chicken breasts in casserole.
Cover with sauce.
Cover and cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Stir together and let rise while you mix remaining ingredients.

title: pioneer corn stew
directions: Saute onion and green peppers in butter over low heat until tender in 5-quart Dutch oven or stew pan.
Add beef and cook slowly until beef browns.
Add corn, tomato soup, sugar and salt. Simmer gently until the stew is thoroughly heated.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Cook chicken in water; cool.
Remove chicken from broth. Remove fat.
Chop chicken into small pieces.
Place chopped chicken, water and broth in 6-quart kettle.
Add corn and parsley to chicken.
Crumble noodles into kettle and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until hot.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and roll into balls.
Heat the currant jelly and the chili sauce over low heat until well mixed. Pour over the meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate icing
directions: In a small bowl, blend powdered sugar, cocoa and milk.
Mix well.

title: pizzaburgers
directions: Grind meat and cheese in food processor.
Heat next 5 ingredients.
Cool these ingredients, then add the ham and cheese. Spread onto a bun.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Simmer beef in crock-pot on high 1 hour.
Add V-8 juice and cook 6 hours.
Add potatoes and vegetables to heat through.

title: cauliflower-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed.
In saucepan combine soups and cheese.
Combine with vegetables, put in casserole.
Stir in 1/2 onion rings, 1/2 on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken-n-noodles
directions: Cook chicken in water in big pan.
Combine seasonings, carrots and celery; cook with chicken until chicken is tender.
Remove all chicken from the water, set aside.
Bring water that chicken was cooked in to a boil.
Water might have to be added for enough. Add noodles when water is rolling boil.
When noodles are cooked add shredded chicken.

title: oriental chicken
directions: In skillet over medium heat, add broccoli, pepper and ginger. Cook until tender.
Add gravy, oil and chicken.
Serve over rice.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Remove skin from
chicken and wash.
Place in deep bowl and cover with milk.
Soak 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Beat eggs with 1/2 cup milk.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Remove chicken pieces from milk.
Coat with flour mixture.
Dip in egg mixture.
Again, coat with flour.
Place in preheated oil in heavy pan.
Cook over medium heat until golden brown and juices run clear when stuck.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Saute margarine and onion for 2 to 3 minutes.
Mix all of the rest together, then add the onion.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach fandango
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add mushrooms.
Season with salt, pepper, oregano and garlic.
Place unthawed spinach on top of meat mixture.
Cover and let steam until thawed.
Stir in soup and sour cream.
Place in an 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Top with the Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Bake, uncovered, 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spanish paella
directions: Combine flour, 1 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Coat chicken with flour.
In skillet, brown chicken in hot oil for 20 minutes.
Transfer to large kettle.
Add next 9 ingredients and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Add artichokes, shrimp and clams.
Simmer, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Will make 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Saute celery and onion in butter. Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°. When done, put cheese on top and let melt.

title: icebox banana cream pie
directions: Whisk milk and pudding for 2 minutes. Add sour cream and 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip. Mix well.
Place half of banana slices in crust; top with half of pudding mix. Repeat layers, then spread with remaining Cool Whip. Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Heat chicken and consomme in pan over slow heat.
Remove and mix all ingredients in order given.
Season to taste and mix well. Put in casserole.
Cover with crushed potato chips and cheese. Bake in oven at 450°
for 15 minutes until warm.
Serve.

title: spring vegetable casserole
directions: Lightly butter a 10-inch souffle dish.
Cut tender parts of asparagus into thin slices.
Lay on bottom of baking dish. Sprinkle with pepper.
Spread prepared onions on the asparagus. Next, spread a layer of shredded cabbage.
Press down to level the vegetables.
Stir salt into cream and pour over layered vegetables.
Combine cheese and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over top of casserole. Dot with chilled butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: ham and creamy potato scallops
directions: Cool and peel potatoes; slice into 1/4-inch thick slices. Spread in greased 2-quart casserole dish.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
For filling, combine 2 tablespoons cake mix, pecans, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Mix well and set aside.
Combine the remaining dry cake mix, sour cream, oil, sugar, water and eggs in large mixer bowl. Beat for 2 minutes at high speed.
Turn 2/3 of batter into pan; sprinkle with filling.
Spoon remaining batter over filling mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer.

title: chocolate fudge(microwave)
directions: Lightly butter a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine sugar, butter and milk in 2-quart glass measure.
Cook on High for 11 to 12 minutes or until a small amount dropped in cold water forms a soft ball (234° on microproof candy thermometer).
Stir in chocolate or peanut butter pieces and Marshmallow Creme until mixture is thoroughly blended.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.
Delicious.

title: orange sweet rolls
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Beat egg, then add orange juice.
Add to dry ingredients.
Blend with fork until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Knead for 30 seconds.
Roll into rectangular shape 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle with orange sugar.
Roll up jelly roll fashion and slice into 1-inch lengths.
Put each slice, cut side down, on greased rind mold.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: crock-pot pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Put in crock-pot.
Combine rest of ingredients and put on top of chops.
Cook for 4 to 6 hours. Serve on cooked rice.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: Combine last 4 ingredients and chill at least 1 hour.
Mix all just before serving.
(For a lower carb version, use Splenda in place of sugar and omit the noodles.)

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Cook rice and chicken noodle soup in 4 1/2 cups water for 7 minutes.
Combine all ingredients and place in casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese straws
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Let butter come to room temperature. Cream butter and cheese together.
Add salt and cayenne pepper and work in flour.
Cover and chill about 1 hour.
Roll out on lightly floured board about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut in sticks with a sharp knife or pastry wheel, about 1/2-inch wide and 4-inches long.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt cheese in soup.
This sauce is very good poured over broccoli, green peppers, etc.

title: beef 'n corn casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Add cream cheese and soup, mixing well.
Stir in corn, pimento and seasonings; pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits; cut each in half, forming 20 half-circles.
Place biscuits, cut side down, around edge of casserole.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until biscuits are browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together all but melted butter and put in a greased 8-inch baking dish.
Pour over top the melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chopped livers
directions: Cover livers with water.
Add paprika and simmer until no pink shows in liver.
Drain; cool slightly.
Saute onions in butter to a light brown.

title: pineapple cheese balls
directions: Thoroughly blend cream cheese and Cheddar cheese. Fold in pineapple, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Chill several hours. Divide in half. Shape into balls.
Roll in nuts.
Chill overnight. Serve with crackers. Yields 2 cheese balls (1 pound each).

title: bean and carrot salad
directions: Place vegetables in a shallow dish.
Combine vinegar, sugar, salad oil and salt; pour over vegetables.
Cover dish and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onion in the 2 tablespoons of oil.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil and then simmer for 20 minutes. Great for chicken.

title: braised beef
directions: Cube meat and dredge in flour.
Mince onions and garlic. Saute meat, onion and garlic in the oil until brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer gently for 2 hours, until tender, stirring frequently.
If necessary, add more water or wine when sauce cooks down.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Mix the flour, seasoned salt and pepper together.
Lightly salt and pepper the pork chops.
Dip them in the flour mixture. Fry in a small amount of oil until crust is brown and meat is done.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Blend together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Add oatmeal, vanilla and chocolate chips.
(Dough is crumbly).
Drop a teaspoonful on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 9 dozen.

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Heat milk.
Blend in flour, cream cheese, Roquefort cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Cook broccoli until barely tender.
Drain and place in 3-quart casserole.
Pour cheese sauce over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Top with bread crumbs; dot with butter and return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Saute garlic, onion, green pepper, celery and mushrooms in butter, about 5 minutes.
Add Minute rice and brown slowly for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add bouillon and boil for 5 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: colonial tea
directions: Mix together and store in a covered container.
To use: Dissolve 2 teaspoons in 1 cup of hot water.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In saucepan, combine butter, sugar and milk. Stir well and bring to a boil. Drop in cut up marshmallows (easier to melt). Continue boiling and stirring for 3 minutes. Immediately remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and vanilla. Pour into an 8 x 8 buttered square pan. Cool thoroughly, then cut into 1-inch squares. Keep in the refrigerator.

title: sweet chili sauce
directions: Boil for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove the bag from the other ingredients and can.
Stir often.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Peel baked potatoes and cut into cubes.
Combine all ingredients, except paprika, in greased casserole dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or at least 3 hours.
When ready to use, sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place potatoes in pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover with onions.
Mix sour cream and chicken soup together.
Spread mixture over potatoes and then top with cheese.
Sprinkle the corn flakes over top and pour melted butter over entire mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli, cauliflower and carrot medley.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Combine Velveeta cheese and milk in a small saucepan and heat until melted, stirring constantly.
Add cream of mushroom soup and heat thoroughly.
Pour over vegetables.
Top with French fried onions and bake at 350°, uncovered, for 20 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter.
Place apple mixture into an unbaked pie shell; dot with butter.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in a 425° oven.

title: italian beer batter veggies
directions: Let beer stand at room temperature until flat (45 minutes). Mix dry ingredients.
Add yolks, oil and beer.
Beat until smooth. Add egg whites (fold in).
Dip veggies in batter.
Cook in hot oil (375°) until golden brown.
Drain and serve warm.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together; pour into greased bread pans and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: raspberry and cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Spray bottom and sides of a 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In large bowl combine flour and 1/2 cup sugar.
Using a pastry blender or fork, cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.

Reserve 1 cup of these crumbs. To remaining crumb mixture add baking powder, baking soda, sour cream, vanilla and almond extract and 2 egg whites; blend well. Spread batter over bottom and 2 inches up sides of greased and floured pan.
Butter should be about 1/4-inch thick on sides.

title: potato chip dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
May be mixed with an electric mixer.

title: squash carrot casserole
directions: Layer crackers in bottom of a greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Mix cream cheese, soup, eggs and butter in a large bowl. Stir in drained squash, carrots and onion.
Spoon into baking dish. Sprinkle with stuffing mix and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken breast piquant(serves 3 to 4)
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together except the chicken.
Place chicken in a casserole and pour the mixture over the chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour or 1 hour and 15 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: beef casserole
directions: Peel potatoes, onions and carrots.
Chop in small pieces in bottom of baking dish.
Add part of salt, pepper and thyme. Spread beef over top of vegetables.
Pour over tomatoes; add remaining salt and seasoning.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple rolls
directions: Sift and measure flour, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Cut the shortening into the flour mixture until it resembles a coarse meal.
Add milk and stir with fork until stiff dough is formed. Turn onto lightly floured board and knead 20 seconds to shape. Roll dough lightly 1/2 inch thick into a rectangular shape.

title: lemon poppy seed pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter well two 9 by 5 by 3 inch loaf pans and dust with flour, shaking out the excess.

In a bowl with an electric mixer, cream the butter, then add 1 1/2 c. sugar a little at a time, and beat until light and fluffy.	Beat in one egg yolk at a time, then add remaining ingredients one at a time, mixing well.
Fold in egg whites gently but thoroughly into the batter.
Divide the batter between the loaf pans and bake for 1 to 1 1/4 hours, or until cake tester inserted in the center of each loaf comes out clean.
Let cool in the pan for 5 minutes and invert onto rack to cool completely.

title: brown bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add egg and Crisco
mix with hot water.
May be baked in greased cans (baked beans) or small bread pans.
Bake at 350° until done.
Test with toothpick. When it comes out clean, bread is done.

title: houlahan's spinach salad
directions: Wash and drain spinach.
Tear into small pieces.
Cover with chopped or sliced mushrooms.
Sprinkle bacon over spinach.
Mix bacon drippings with vinegar and sugar.
Pour over top of spinach mixture.
Top with croutons.
Bon appetit!

title: fantastic feta chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Drizzle with 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Sprinkle with oregano and pepper; top with cheese.
Drizzle with remaining 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Bake 45 minutes or until cooked through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Combine shortening, magarine and sugar.
Cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Sift dry ingredients together three times.
Mix flour, milk and vanilla alternately to other ingredients.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients and spices; add sugar and oil, mixing well.
Beat in eggs; add carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Bake in three 10-inch round layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Spray a large roasting pan with Pam.
Put corn curls in pan. Blend oleo, syrup and brown sugar in saucepan.
Boil 5 minutes and add baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour over corn curls. Mix. Bake at 250° for 1 hour, mixing every 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together except French fried onions.
Let set in refrigerator 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Put French fried onions on top and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: easy coffee cake
directions: Night before, place frozen rolls in well-greased Bundt pan. Sprinkle with pudding.
Melt butter; add nuts and brown sugar. Pour over rolls.
Let raise on counter overnight (8 to 10 hours). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove while hot.

title: green congealed salad
directions: Mix jello into hot water, add marshmallows and stir until dissolved.
Add cold water and let begin to set.
Cream together cheese and mayonnaise.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Stir into jello. Return to refrigerator until set.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, salt and onion.
Drain.
Mix squash, cream of chicken soup, chestnuts, sour cream, carrot and onion.
Melt margarine with stuffing mix.
Make a layer of stuffing, then cover with squash mixture; top with remainder
of stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix and let set a few minutes for oatmeal to soak up a bit of moisture.
Bake on a hot skillet as you do other pancakes.
Serve with butter and warm syrup.

title: crunchie pecan cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugars, egg and flavoring; beat about 3 minutes. Sift dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture. Add pecans and stir in. Shape in long roll. Chill several hours. Slice thin and bake on ungreased tin at 400° for about 10 minutes. Dough will keep in refrigerator several weeks. Makes 3 dozen.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Can be sprinkled with confectioners sugar or may be frosted with chocolate icing.
Decorate with large halves of walnuts.

title: eggplant jeanette
directions: Peel, dice and cook eggplant in salted water.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, egg, onion and cheese with eggplant.
Place in greased casserole and cover with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter and bake at 350°.
(The more we ate the better we liked it.)

title: chicken bake
directions: Stir stuffing crumbs, contents of seasoning packet, 1 1/2 cups of hot water and margarine just until moistened. Place chicken in 12 X 8 inch baking pan. Mix soup and sour cream or milk. Pour over chicken and top with stuffing mix. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until chicken is cooked through. Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican squash
directions: Boil squash and onion until tender and drain.
Mix in cheese and peppers.
Pour into baking dish.
Cover with crackers or buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: great frosting
directions: Melt chips and shortening over water.
Remove from heat. Stir in
sugar
and
milk.
Beat until smooth.
Let cool 1 to 2 minutes.
Frost cake or sheet cake.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine Shoepeg or white corn, green beans, celery soup, onion, green pepper, celery and sour cream.
Add salt and pepper. Mix all ingredients well and put into casserole.
Mix 1 cup bread crumbs with 1/2 cup melted butter.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add a little dill before mixing and when sauteing bread crumbs in butter, add a bit of thyme.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Mix well the first 7 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans in a 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: spiced citrus warmer
directions: In a 4-cup measure, stir together orange juice, cranberry juice cocktail, water, honey, 3-inch stick cinnamon, whole allspice and whole cloves.
Microcook, covered, on High for 8 to 10 minutes or just until boiling.
Continue to cook, covered, on Medium for 5 minutes.
Strain to remove spices.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: In bottom of casserole dish, place a layer of sliced potatoes 1/2-inch thick, cooked until tender.
Put 1 layer of Vidalia onions, cut same size, over potatoes.
Add 1 layer of Velveeta cheese.
Between each layer, pour large amount of Ranch dressing. Make as many layers as desired.
Recipe as written makes 4 to 6 serving.

title: eggless cake
directions: Cook sugar, shortening, water, raisins and dates until it boils.
After this cools, add sifted dry ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: banana pops
directions: Mix ingredients in a medium bowl.
Divide among 6 four-ounce paper cups.
Freeze until firm.
Peel back paper, eat and make monkey sounds!

title: sour cream-lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, lemon rind, lemon juice, egg yolks and milk in heavy saucepan; cook over heat until thick.
Stir in margarine and cool mixture to room temperature.
Stir in sour cream and pour into pie shell.
Cover with whipped cream.
Store in refrigerator.
(You may use Cool Whip for whipped cream; it isn't as rich.)

title: anthony's apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, spices, and a dash of salt.
Mix with apples.
Fill bottom crust with apple mixture.
Dot with butter. Add top crust.
Cut slits.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400 for 50 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients; brown and drain sausage.
Layer sausage and potatoes in baking dish.
Pour on soup mixture, then eggs and milk.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: gravy
directions: Saute onion.
Stir in tomato paste and garlic, basil, parsley, fennel seed, salt and pepper.
After a few minutes, stir in crushed tomatoes.
Then you put in boiling water.
When it comes to a boil, lower heat and let cook for 3 hours or to desired thickness.

title: asparagus and cheese soup
directions: Using a food processor, puree together the potatoes, asparagus, milk and sour cream.
Pour into a saucepan with the chicken or vegetable stock and heat gently.
Add the Cheddar cheese to the pan; add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with crusty bread. Serves 2.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar; add oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mix all dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add nuts.
Stir this with large spoon.
Put in 8 x 8 greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Easy, but good.
Serve plain or with ice cream.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except buttermilk and eggs, until crumbly; save 1/2 cup.
Add buttermilk and eggs to remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pan. Sprinkle the 1/2 cup mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Good with lemon sauce.

title: roast pork-crispy crust
directions: Combine all ingredients, except roast, and rub roast with the mixture.
Cover roast and refrigerate 4 to 8 hours.
Roast, uncovered, at 325° for 2 1/2 to 2 3/4 hours until meat thermometer registers 170°.

title: barbecue chicken legs
directions: Combine catsup, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, soy sauce and dry mustard in a bowl.
Baste 2 pounds chicken legs with 1/2 of the mixture; broil for 20 minutes.
Turn and baste with remaining sauce.
Cook until well done.

title: better than robert redford cake
directions: Use Bundt pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: enchiladas verdes mexicanas
directions: Remove chicken from bones and shred with fingers into strips. Heat tomatillos in a pan to lightly fry.
Remove from heat and put in blender along with garlic and onion.
Add 1/4 cup water if too dry to blend properly.
Heat oil in pan; when hot, lightly fry (not long) tortillas in oil.
Place tortilla on plate and fill in center with chicken and cheese; pour green sauce, approximately 2 tablespoons, on top of chicken and cheese.
Roll up and place the filled tortilla, seam side down.
Continue until all tortillas are filled and rolled.
Top entire casserole of enchiladas with remaining sauce and cheese.
Bake until bubbly, about 30 minutes, at 350°.

title: grape-nuts mincemeat
directions: Combine all ingredients in kettle.
Cook over low heat for 2 hours or until thick as any mincemeat.
Pack at once in hot pint jars.
If you wish to make a larger amount, you may increase amounts by 2 or 3.

title: orange vinaigrette
directions: Whisk the orange juice and vinegar in a small bowl until mixed.
Whisk in the mustard, then gradually whisk in the oil. Continue to whisk until slightly thickened.
Season to taste with pepper.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Prepare meat mixture. In large skillet, heat oil on medium heat. Add beef. Cook until brown, stirring often; drain off any fat. Stir in tomato sauce and taco seasoning mix, then remove meat from heat and set aside. Rinse and drain kidney beans. Toss with 1 cup of the shredded cheese.

title: glazed walnuts
directions: Boil sugar, orange juice and grated orange until forms soft ball in water.
Add 3 cups whole nut meats.
Beat until cloudy. Drop on wax paper.

title: ginger cold tea(home remedies)
directions: Add all ingredients to 1 glass hot water. Drink before going to bed
to work off cold and flu.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, cocoa, cloves, nutmeg, ginger and cinnamon.
Measure oil and honey in same cup (honey slips out if measured after oil).
Add oil, honey, applesauce, raisins, dates and nuts to dry ingredients; mix well.
Pour batter into two 8-inch square pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 15 minutes longer.
Cool slightly and turn out on cake rack to cool completely.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir onion in sour cream.
Place half the bread in pan.
Top with sauerkraut, then corned beef, sour cream and half of the cheese. Top with remaining bread. Drizzle with melted margarine, then remaining cheese.
Bake at 350°, covered for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Mix with chicken broth and bake. Use boiled eggs in giblet gravy, along with giblets, 1 cup dressing mix and chicken broth.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Toss lightly together.
Place in casserole.
Cover with Chinese noodles.
Let stand several hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese last 15 minutes. Allow 1 hour if taken from refrigerator.

title: seaburgers
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
Place fish fillets in a single layer in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon souffle atop.
Combine crushed crackers, wheat germ, and Parmesan cheese; sprinkle over all.

title: leta's cream cheese loaf
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine, 1 egg and nuts very well.
Pat in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: vegetable dip(low calorie)
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Yields approximately 1 1/2 cups.
One tablespoon equals 75 calories or 1 1/2 fat exchanges.

title: baked rice
directions: Mix all ingredients in a buttered baking dish.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Rice comes out perfectly.

title: hush puppies
directions: Fry in real hot oil.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Combine dressing mix and oil.
Add dill weed, lemon pepper and garlic salt. Pour over crackers. Stir to coat.
Place in warm oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together; roll dough into balls about the size of a walnut, then roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: zucchini garden chowder
directions: In Dutch oven or soup kettle over medium heat, saute zucchini, onion, parsley and basil in butter until vegetables are tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in water. Add bouillon and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes, milk and corn; bring to a boil. reduce heat; cover and simmer for 5 minutes or until corn is tender.
Just before serving, stir in cheeses until melted.
Add sugar and garnish with parsley if desired.
Yields 8 - 10 servings.

title: leftover meat pie
directions: Cook vegetables in just a little water until tender.
Add leftover meat (cut up) and gravy; simmer.

title: crunchy party mix
directions: In a small saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, chili powder, garlic salt, salt and pepper sauce.
Keep warm.
In a large bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Stir in butter mixture to coat.
Spread in large roasting pan.
Bake in a preheated oven at 300° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
tags: bite size crispy rice square cereal

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Combine pork, soy sauce, and salt; stir well. Dredge pork in flour; dip in beaten egg. Dredge again in flour. Pour oil around top of preheated wok, coating sides; allow to heat at medium high (325°) for 1 minute. Add pork; stir fry 4 to 5 minutes or until browned. Remove from wok; set aside. Drain off oil, reserving 1 Tbsp. drippings in wok. Add onion and green pepper; stir fry 30 seconds. Add pork, tomatoes and pineapple; stir fry 4 to 5 minutes. Stir in sweet and sour sauce; cook until bubbly. Serve over rice.

title: spanish rice hot dish
directions: Cook rice, rinse and drain.
Saute onions and green pepper in oil until tender.
Add ground beef, fry until tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir all together and place in casserole.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
For large family use 1 1/2 cups rice, 1 1/2 pounds ground beef, whole can peas, whole jar olives and whole green pepper.

title: best strudel dough
directions: Mix ingredients except apples and knead on floured board until it doesn't stick to hands.
Do not use excess flour.
Place large tablecloth on table.
Sprinkle flour over cloth.
Divide dough into 2 equal parts.
Grease each part with a little oil.
Wait 1/2 hour, then roll dough out with rolling pin like for pie, not too big (about 10-inch circle). then wait 20 minutes.
A must!!
After 20 minutes, roll one ball of dough out thin or dough will stretch easily if you want.
Don't let dough stand too long or it will crack.
Spread melted butter over dough, then sprinkle bread crumbs all over dough.
Place sliced apples inward about 4-inches or so and spread over dough.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over apples to taste.
You may add raisins or nuts or both.
Turn edge of dough in with hands and then roll into log with tablecloth.
Seal ends. Place on greased cookie sheet (you may spray sheet with pam) in an "S" shape and slit top in 2 or 3 places for steam to escape (this avoids sogginess).
Brush with melted butter and bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: barbecued franks
directions: Brown onion in oil.
Add remaining ingredients except franks. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add franks and simmer 15 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Melt margarine and add to dressing; set aside.
Combine vegetables.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Add this to vegetables, then add stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a greased baking pan.
Sprinkle with canned onion rings or grated cheese on top.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: killer corn bread
directions: Mix all together and pour into greased 8 by 13 in. pan and bake at 350° for 40 min.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Add cocoa mixture.
Mix well.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion until browned.
Add kidney beans and taco sauce.
Let simmer while you make a salad using lettuce, tomato, onion and pepper.
Combine beef mixture and salad; toss.
Garnish with crumbled Doritos chips.

title: chicken with prosciutto and cheese
directions: Slice halves of chicken breast lengthwise, making 4 slices. On waxed paper, roll chicken in Parmesan cheese.
In skillet, heat butter to foaming and saute chicken about 2 minutes on each side. Lay slice of Prosciutto, then slice of cheese on each strip of chicken and secure with a toothpick.

title: cinco de mayo bean dip
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients, except chips. Heat until cheeses are melted and beans are bubbling.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 3 cups dip.

title: western stew
directions: Bring to boil everything except potatoes and cornstarch. Reduce heat; simmer in covered pot for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes; cook for 30 more minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/2 cup cold water.
Add to cooked ingredients; bring back to boil for 2 minutes to thicken.
Good to cook ahead and take on a camping trip or to have in cold weather.

title: mexicali vegetable soup
directions: Cook beef and onion in large saucepan until beef is browned; drain.
Add broth, beans, zucchini, carrots and seasoning mix. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook, covered 15-20 minutes.

title: turkey tornado spaghetti sauce
directions: Place brisket in boiling water to cover.
Add pickling spice and simmer 3 1/2 to 4 hours or until tender.
Do not overcook. Remove brisket from pan and let stand 15 minutes.
Place in baking pan and cover surface of beef lightly with prepared mustard.
Let stand 10 minutes until mustard penetrates meat.
Spread jelly over brisket and sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until glazed.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: christie's favorite m&m's cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugars and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Sift together flour, soda and salt. Gradually add to creamed mixture, mixing until well blended.
Drop by measuring tablespoonful onto greased cookie sheets.

title: easy taco dip
directions: Press cream cheese into bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish evenly. Pour on no-bean chili.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Heat in oven or microwave until bubbly.
Serve with taco or Doritos chips.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs; add flour, salt and sugar, sifted together.
Beat 5 minutes or more.
Add milk; beat 5 minutes longer.
Melt butter in skillet.
Pour in butter. Sprinkle batter evenly with grated apples.
Bake in 425° oven for 8 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 15 to 18 minutes longer, until pancake is puffed and golden.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and confectioners sugar.
Cut in wedges and serve with jam or preserves.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: lillian's cranberry salad
directions: In food processor, grind cherries, orange and cranberries. Place in large bowl.
Add sugar and mix well.

title: spoon burgers
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add hamburger and mix well.
Add other ingredients and simmer until thick.
Serve on heated buns.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add onions and saute until clear. Add thawed, chopped broccoli and stir.
Add soup; stir and simmer a few minutes.
Add cheese and stir.
Add cooked rice and stir. If you think it is too thick, thin with a little water.
Freeze or refrigerate or bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: beer fried fish
directions: Mix beer, butter and beaten egg yolk.
Add flour and corn starch.
Beat egg whites until peaks form and add to mixture.
Use as batter for frying fish or chicken.

title: strawberry short cake
directions: Make cake mix according to directions.
Grease a 9 x 13 pan. Line bottom of pan with marshmallows.
Pour prepared cake mix over this.
Sprinkle dry Jell-O over this.
Evenly spoon strawberries over Jell-O.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crabmeat souffle
directions: In a buttered 2-quart shallow casserole, layer the bread cubes, cheese and then the crabmeat.
Repeat layers.
Combine beaten eggs, milk and salt and pour over layers.
Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
Pour melted butter over top and sprinkle with chopped pimento, if desired.
Set casserole in a pan of water and bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: individual pineapple upside-down cakes
directions: Melt together in skillet until bubbly the first 2 ingredients. Mix cake mix according to package directions.

Cover the bottom of a tuna can with 1 tablespoon of the brown sugar mixture. Place a pineapple slice on top of brown sugar, then place a maraschino cherry in the middle of the pineapple. A few walnuts can be placed around for added taste. Pour 1/2 cup of cake batter on top of pineapple. Bake in 350° oven 15 to 20 minutes; turn upside down on cookie sheet to cool. Makes 12 to 15 cakes.

title: terrific tagliarini
directions: Brown beef, onions and garlic in oil.
Add remaining ingredients except 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Mix.
Place in 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole.
Cover and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Uncover; top with cheese.
Bake for 5 minutes longer.
Yields 12 servings.

title: grape-nuts custard pudding
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add sugar, salt, vanilla, nutmeg, cinnamon and milk.
Stir in the Grape-Nuts.
Place in a greased casserole dish, in a pan of water, in 350° oven for 1 hour or until custard is set. (The water should reach at least 1-inch up on the dish.)

title: marinated bean salad
directions: Marinate all but onion and croutons overnight.
(Marinating the onion separately will enhance their flavor but not overpower the other veggies.)
When ready to serve, toss croutons with veggies in an attractive salad bowl.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Cook pineapple juice, flour, sugar and egg over low heat until thick.
Stir and mix pineapple, marshmallows and pecans.
Stir in cooled, cooked mixture.
Whip cream; fold in mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: macaroni with meat sauce
directions: Heat fat in a 10-inch skillet.
Add onion and garlic; cook until onion is soft, not brown.
Add meat; break into small pieces.
Cook and stir until lightly browned.
Add next 7 ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Cover; simmer 45 minutes.
Add mushrooms; heat to boiling.
Arrange macaroni on a platter.
Pour sauce over macaroni.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: for smoking meat sauce
directions: Mix and put on meat.

title: squash dressing
directions: Melt butter and saute onions.
Mix remaining ingredients, add onion and blend well.
Spray casserole dish with nonstick spray. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and brown.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add enough mayonnaise to blend vegetables together.
Chill before serving.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Stir all ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: Rinse wild rice; soak in 1/2 cup water overnight.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix together all ingredients.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: olive and egg spread
directions: Combine flour, water, mustard, 1 egg, sugar, vinegar and a little salt in saucepan. Cook until thick. Add hard-boiled eggs (chopped) and your olives.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix Raisin Bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt in a very large bowl.
Add beaten eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Mix gently with a wooden spoon.
Refrigerate overnight.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Use mix as desired.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt chocolate and oleo together.
Add sugar and cool.
Add remaining ingredients and pour in pie shell.
Bake in oven at 325° for 40 minutes, then top will crack.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: easy spinach bake
directions: Thaw and drain spinach and mix with soup and sour cream. Spread into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Enjoy as a side dish with any meal.

title: cabbage for a king
directions: Cook cabbage in salted boiling water for 5 minutes.
In 2-quart casserole, layer half of cabbage and half of bread mixed with butter and half of cheese.
Cover with half of sauce.
Repeat layers with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit cake
directions: Chop fruits, dates and pecans.
Mix everything together.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 250°. Cool in pan for 2 hours.
This makes a large cake.

title: wacky cake(no egg)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Make 3 indentations in these dry ingredients.
Put one of each liquid into each hole. Over all pour one cup cold water.
Mix well.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes one layer or 12 cupcakes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Brown hamburger in skillet.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Remove from heat and combine rest of ingredients. Add in a 2-quart casserole half of noodles, cheese sauce and then remaining noodles.
Add hamburger/tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: orange mandarin salad
directions: Sprinkle cottage cheese with jello.
Add crushed pineapple. Add mandarin oranges (cut in half).
Add Cool Whip.
Stir and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: party mix
directions: Mix all ingredients
in
a
roasting pan. Put in a 250° oven. Stir every	15
minutes
until well heated.
Remove from oven. Cool and store in airtight tins.
It won't last long.

title: best shortcake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into an 8 x 8-inch ungreased pan. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and beat until well blended.
Add eggs, beating after each.
Sift dry ingredients. Mix milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately to creamed mixture.
Turn into well-greased and lightly floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Add ingredients to a bowl in this order:
lettuce, cauliflower, and crumbled bacon.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese and crab meat.
Put into a serving dish and top with the cocktail sauce and serve with crackers.

title: strawberry glaze pie(with flaky pastry shell)
directions: Hull, wash and thoroughly drain berries; crush enough to make 1 cup, leaving the rest whole.
Combine crushed berries with water, sugar and cornstarch.
Bring to a boil, cook over low heat for 2 to 3 minutes or until clear, stirring occasionally to prevent lumping. Add butter, tint to desired shade and cool slightly.
Line baked pastry shell with whole berries, pour glaze mixture over making sure all are covered.
Cool; just before serving, garnish with whipped cream.

title: surprise cake
directions: Pour cake mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then beat egg, cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add chocolate chips and mix well. Spread over cake mixture and bake according to package directions. Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool or frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, sugar and salt.
Add oil and eggs, beating one at a time.
Beat until creamy.
Add pineapple, carrots and nuts.
Pour into pan and bake for 55 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: lo fat homemade rolls
directions: Stir ingredients together in order given. Refrigerate 12 hours. Roll out and let rise 2 hours before baking at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add onion.
Saute until onion is clear.
Add thawed broccoli cuts and cream of mushroom soup.
Simmer 6 to 7 minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz and cooked rice. Pour mixture into casserole dish and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rice salad
directions: Make rice per package directions.
Chill. Add all ingredients and mix well.
Mix liquid saved from artichoke hearts with 1/2 cup mayonnaise and 1/4 teaspoon curry powder.
Pour over rice mixture. Chill and serve.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients very well until mixture looks like lumpy Bisquick (approximately 5 minutes).
Roll into balls; place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: fudge nut brownies
directions: Mix butter,
brown
sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well until creamy.
Add
flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix together and add oats.
Use 2/3 mixture in 10 x 16-inch pan.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla together.
Add dry ingredients to mixture.
Makes two loaves.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
In blender, mix together cranberry sauce, orange juice and lemon juice on low-medium speed. Pour into Jell-O.
Add undrained pineapple.
Chill until firm. Top with Pineapple Salad Dressing.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Stir ingredients together; cover and chill.

title: brown betty
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl.
Turn into 11 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.

title: microwave instant rice
directions: Mix in 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and microwave on High 4 to 8 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Add frozen berries and orange juice. Then add pineapple with juice. Chill until set.
Serves 12.

title: seafood casserole
directions: In a large
bowl, mix first twelve ingredients, seasoning it with black	pepper.
Place	the
mixture
into
a
x 13-inch casserole dish.
Garnish
with
paprika.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Top
it
with
a	can of onion rings and return it to the oven for an additional 10 minutes.

title: orange coffee cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Spread marmalade on bottom.
Sprinkle nuts on marmalade.
Dip biscuits in butter, then in mixture of cinnamon/sugar.
Space biscuits evenly around pan (stand on ends). Drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Turn onto serving plate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender and save broth.
Remove bone and skin; cut up chicken.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Melt margarine in a baking dish.
Coat dish well.
Pour remaining margarine in mixture.
Put mixture into a baking dish.
Bake about 45 minutes (350° to 375°).

title: 6 minute pecan pie
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in pecans. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: spicy tomato aspic
directions: Prepare jello, using only 1 cup boiling water. Put tomatoes into blender and pulse for 2 to 3 seconds, just enough to break up the fiber. Add to jello. Add chopped vegetables. Spray 9 x 9-inch pan lightly with Pam. Pour in mixture. Chill until firm. "Frost" with equal parts of mayonnaise and sour cream. Sprinkle with dill weed.

title: pappy's chili
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Combine all ingredients except chili con carne.
Cover with water.
Cook at a boil for 1 hour.
Simmer 1 hour.
When almost done, add chili con carne.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Make into small balls.
Bake for 10 minutes or until brown at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: shrimp pilaf
directions: Steam shrimp according to directions on Old Bay seasoning. (I substitute about half of the vinegar with water.)
Peel and store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Heat oleo, lemon juice, wine and garlic salt in a skillet; add shrimp and saute until good and hot and liquid is almost gone.
Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to package directions.
Make a nest with the rice.
Put shrimp in the center.

title: swiss cheese bread
directions: Trim crust off bread sides and top only.
Leave bottom on. Cut 1-inch slices into bread diagonally, don't cut through bottom. Combine all ingredients and mix.
Put half of mixture between the slices and the rest on top and sides.
You can cut the bread in half if you want.
Make a boat from foil and a loose piece on top that you will cover the bread the last 5 minutes only.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.
May be made ahead and frozen or 1 day ahead and refrigerated.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Put rice in cake pan or small roaster.
Put pork chops on top. Pour soup on top of all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin honey wheat bread(makes 18 servings)
directions: Combine flour, wheat germ, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and baking soda in large bowl. Combine eggs, pumpkin, honey, oil and milk in medium bowl. Add to flour mixture. Stir just until blended. Spread into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Sprinkle with nuts; gently pat into batter. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan for 10 minutes; remove to wire rack to cool completely.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat well the vegetable oil, sugar and egg. Add flour and mix until almost smooth. Makes about 6 to 8 large pancakes.

title: fresh strawberry ice cream
directions: Mash the strawberries and mix with the sugar; add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Then mix the pudding, whipping cream and half and half thoroughly.
Add strawberry mixture to pudding mixture, then stir in the Eagle Brand milk and sweet milk.
When thoroughly mixed, pour into ice cream freezer.
Freeze and eat!

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: In skillet, brown meat.
Drain and crumble.
Add onion, soup (not water), green chilies and Ro-Tel or salsa.
Heat thoroughly and simmer.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, place layer of tortilla chips and cheese.
Pour meat filling mixture over chips and cheese.
Place another layer of chips; top with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese melts on top.
Serve with side dish of corn, beans, etc.

title: mexican skillet cornbread casserole
directions: Combine cornmeal, soda, salt, corn, milk and oil in bowl.
Set aside.
Cook ground beef until brown; drain well.
Set aside. Pour 1/2 cornmeal mix in greased 10-inch skillet (cast-iron is best).
Sprinkle evenly with ground beef; top with cheese, onion and pepper.
Pour remaining batter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: tostado casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add 1 1/2 cups tomato sauce and taco mix. Line bottom of baking dish with 2 cups corn chips.
Crush remaining corn chips and set aside.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces; mix with soup, broth and vegetables.
Pour
into
a	greased baking dish.
Mix with milk and
mix.
Pour
on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate waffle cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar; beat in egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Blend in chocolate.
Add flour; mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls, 1 inch apart, onto preheated waffle iron.
Close lid and cook 1 minute.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Double the recipe for about 3 dozen cookies.

title: potato pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until center is set.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Sprinkle chicken with garlic powder and chicken seasoning.
Wrap bacon around chicken breast.
Be sure to overlap bacon strips.
A toothpick may be used to secure bacon strips.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
To brown bacon both sides, turn chicken breast.
After chicken is done, place cheese of your choice on top to melt.
Bake chicken in a covered pan.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Brown the onion in 1/2 stick butter.
In a large bowl, mix potatoes, soups, cheese, sour cream, salt and onion.
Put in a 3-quart baking dish.
Melt 1/2 stick butter.
Mix with bread crumbs and sprinkle on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Break into pieces.
Place one crust in pie pan.
Add chicken.
Pour 1 jar chicken gravy and 1 can drained Veg-All into crust.
Place top crust on pie and pierce. Bake one hour at 350°.
Fast, easy and delicious.

title: mexican rice dinner
directions: Cook onion and bell pepper in a small amount of oil.
Add ground meat and brown.
Drain off fat.
Mix together ground meat mixture, rice, half the cheese and jalapenos to taste.
Put in large casserole dish.
Top with crumbled bacon and remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and dish is heated through, uncovered.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Heat 1/4 cup oil in skillet with sesame seed and almonds until almonds are brown.
Cool.
Add the rest of the oil, soy sauce, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir until sugar dissolves. Pour mixture over cooked noodles and chicken.
Mix well. Refrigerate overnight.
Add greens just before serving.

title: linguine primavera
