directions: In a nonstick skillet over medium heat, cook broccoli, carrots, onions, Italian seasoning, garlic and pepper in liquid Butter Buds or chicken broth for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add tomato; cook 1 minute more or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Toss with hot linguine, Egg Beaters and Parmesan cheese.

title: tabouli(the queen of lebanese salads)
directions: Wash parsley well.
Drain and shake out excess moisture.
Soak crushed wheat in water in a large mixing bowl for 2 minutes. Drain well.
Set aside while preparing other ingredients.

title: west indies salad
directions: Divide chopped onion in half and spread half over the bottom of a large mixing bowl.
Place crab meat over onions.
Spread balance of onion over crab meat.
Salt and pepper to taste. Pour over all in this order: oil, vinegar and lastly the ice water.
Cover and place in refrigerator to marinate from 2 to 12 hours.
When ready to serve, toss lightly but do not stir.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water and set in jell form.
When mixture has thickened, fold in crushed pineapple, cranberry sauce, celery and nuts (if desired).
Pour in mold and set.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in oil until tender-crisp.
Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
To syrup, blend vinegar, brown sugar, water, soy sauce and cornstarch.
Add to sauteed vegetables and cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is thick and clear.
Add pineapple and heat thoroughly.
Yield:
1 1/2 to 2 cups.

title: oyster stuffing
directions: Drain and chop oysters, reserving the liquid.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add celery and onion and cook until tender, but not browned.
Combine oysters, celery, onion, bread cubes, parsley, salt, poultry seasoning and pepper; mix well.
Moisten stuffing with oyster liquid if necessary.
Bake in lightly greased casserole at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until heated through.
Makes enough for a 10 to 15 pound turkey.

title: ranch muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well and set aside.
In medium bowl, stir together flour, oats, baking powder, baking soda, salad dressing mix and nuts.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk to egg mixture.
Stir until just combined.
Spoon batter into greased or paper-lined muffin pans, filling each cup two-thirds full. Bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: strawberry crumb cake
directions: Bake
cake
by
directions on box in oblong pan.
While cake is
cooling,
put sugar in strawberries and stir.
After cake is cool,
crumble
up
in pan.
In a large bowl or punch bowl,
put a
layer
of crumbled cake, then add 1/4 of strawberries
and
a layer of Cool Whip.
Do this until cake, Cool Whip and strawberries are used.

title: lemonade cookies
directions: Cream butter and 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs, beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour and soda.
Add alternately to the creamed mixture with 1/2 cup lemonade concentrate.
Drop dough from a teaspoon 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Brush cookies lightly with remaining lemonade, sprinkle with sugar.

title: swiss broccoli soup
directions: In a 2 qt. saucepan, saut onion in butter until tender.
Stir in gravy, milk and broccoli; heat slowly stirring often.
Add cheese, salt and pepper; heat until cheese is melted stirring often.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: chocolate tweed cake
directions: Finely grate chocolate.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add the 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Beat until stiff.
Set aside.
Cream together thoroughly butter and sugar.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with milk beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
After each addition, beat until smooth.
Blend chocolate into batter.
Carefully fold egg white mixture into batter.
Pour into 3 (8-inch) round cake pans or 2 (9-inch) pans. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until toothpick in center comes out clean.
Cool slightly.
Turn layers out of pans.
Cool thoroughly on wire rack.
Frost with whipped cream.
Melt chocolate chips.
Stir water in until smooth.
Drizzle over cream, letting some drip down sides.

title: muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in bowl.
Add oil and milk, making a smooth batter.
Beat in eggs.
Put in muffin tins.
Bake in oven at 400° for about 20 minutes or until brown.
Makes about 12 small muffins.

title: yummy chicken
directions: Coat fryer pieces with flour.
Place in casserole.
Mix Coke, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce and pour over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break capellini into pieces and cook according to package directions.
Drain and cool.
Mix the other ingredients together and toss with the capellini.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and pat dry chicken pieces.
Place sour cream and bread crumbs in separate bowls.
Dip each chicken breast in sour cream, then in the bread crumbs.
Place chicken on a greased baking sheet and bake for 1 hour.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Place berries into pie shell.
Mix sugar, flour and water together, making sure sugar melts.
Pour over berries.
Place margarine over mixture.
Top with pie shell.
Make several gashes in top crust for steam to escape.
Bake at 425° for about 35 minutes or until brown.
Frozen pie shells may be used.
Allow to thaw.

title: angus barn chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate. Mix with other ingredients which have been blended together. Pour into pie crust and bake 35 minutes at 350°. Top with whipped cream.

title: dill vegetable dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Chill several hours.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: aunt joan's marinade
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour over steak, chicken, pork chops or any meat.
Marinate overnight, rotating meat occasionally.
Grill on barbecue.
Enjoy!

title: alabama ice cream pie
directions: Prepare pastry shells. In large skillet, melt butter or margarine; stir in coconut and pecans. Cook and stir over medium heat until coconut is golden, about 6 to 8 minutes. Cool. In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese with an electric mixer until smooth; gradually

beat in sweetened condensed milk on low speed. Fold in whipped topping. Spoon in 1/4 of the mixture into each pastry shell; drizzle each with 1/4 of the caramel topping and sprinkle with 1/4 of the coconut mixture. Repeat layers. Cover and freeze 5 hours or until firm. Serve or freeze, covered, for up to 2 weeks. Let stand at room temperature 5 minutes before serving, if frozen.

title: stuffed eggplant roll-ups
directions: Wash eggplant.
Remove stems and peel. Slice lengthwise and dredge through flour.
Dip into egg and fry in olive oil until golden brown.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Place a slice of Mozzarella in the middle of each slice. Add a scoop of Ricotta and roll up eggplant slices.
Place, seam down, in a greased shallow baking pan and top with a little marinara sauce. Bake at 350° for 15 to 30 minutes. Garnish with parsley and grated cheese. Great served with pasta on the side.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crepes
directions: Beat ingredients together.
Pour approximately 1/5 to 1/4 into hot greased frying pan.
Spread batter to all edges by tipping the pan until it reaches all the edges and the batter is covering the whole bottom of the frying pan.
When the batter appears to no longer be runny (approximately 2 to 3 minutes), turn the crepe over to cook the other side.
Should yield 4 to 5 crepes, depending on the size of the crepe or frying pan.

title: madeira rice with peas and almonds
directions: In large saucepan, melt 1 teaspoon butter over medium heat. Add almonds and stir 2 to 3 minutes, until lightly browned. Remove from pan and reserve.
Add 2 tablespoons butter and saute onions until tender, 5 minutes.
Add Madeira wine; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Add rice, broth, water, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and cook 15 minutes.
Stir in peas; cover and cook 5 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid has been absorbed.
Sprinkle with toasted almonds.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Bake pie crust and let cool.
Cover bottom of pie shells with banana slices and cover the bananas with pecans.
Mix pineapple, sugar and flour.
Cook these 3 ingredients until thick on low heat.
Cool and pour over bananas and nuts.
Sprinkle coconut over this mixture.
Spread Cool Whip on top and chill.

title: potato chip cookies(very yummy!)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fruit filling coffee cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla.
Mix together flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix butter/sugar mixture and flour mixture together.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and spread half the batter; spread one can pie filling over the batter.
Spread remaining batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
(Powdered sugar frosting can be streuseled over the top.)

title: dill pickles
directions: Place a generous layer of dill, 1 clove of garlic and 1/2 tablespoon mustard seed in bottom of jars.
Pack cucumbers; add more dill.
Fill jars 1/2-inch from top with brine.
Process 5 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: hush puppies
directions: In mixing bowl, mix first 8 ingredients thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Deep fry until well browned.

title: christmas candy peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, sour cream, corn syrup, butter and salt; slowly bring to boil.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cover and boil without stirring for 3 minutes to dissolve all sugar crystals. Uncover and boil on medium heat to 240°.
Remove from heat and let stand 15 minutes.
Do not stir!

title: deviled ham sandwich filling
directions: Mix together in electric mixer.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
For party sandwiches, this makes a loaf and a half of finger sandwiches or small open-face sandwiches, decorated with slice of olive.

title: chocolate milk shake
directions: Mix ingredients in a blender.
Pour in glass and let set for 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: cream filling
directions: Heat milk.
Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in the hot milk and beat well.
Cook until very thick and smooth.
Add egg yolks and cook for a few more minutes.
Cool, then add vanilla.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, butter and buttermilk.
Mix well and add chocolate that has been melted over hot water.
Blend well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; stir into other mixture.
Bake in prepared 9-inch tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: chicken fiesta pizza
directions: Cut chicken into thin strips.
Saute chicken in oil until no longer pink.
Add taco seasoning along with water.
Spread salsa on crust.
Sprinkle the chicken over the salsa.
Top with green onions, green pepper and black olives.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese over entire mixture.
Bake according to crust package instructions.

title: tropical fruit salad
directions: Mix and drain fruit good.
Let sit in refrigerator overnight.

title: easy english trifle
directions: First Layer:
Thin sandwiches of cake and preserves arranged on bottom of glass bowl, sprinkled with half of the sherry and topped with half the raisins (or peel) and then covered with half the pudding.

title: yummy carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and store.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, sugars and eggs.
Sift together and stir in the flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix thoroughly. Press and mold into a long smooth roll, about 2 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill until stiff (several hours or overnight).
With a thin sharp knife, cut into thin slices (1/8 to 1/4-inch).
Place slices a little apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until lightly browned.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: chili rellenos bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown beef and onions, stirring until meat loses its red color.
Drain off grease, if necessary.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.

title: peanut brittle(total cooking time:  18 to 20 minutes)
directions: Place sugar, corn syrup, water, salt and peanuts in 2-quart microproof bowl or casserole.
Cook on High (maximum power) 5 minutes, then stir.
Cook on High (maximum power) 13 to 15 minutes, or until syrup separates into threads.
This is the hard crack stage or 300° on a candy thermometer.
Stir several times during the last few minutes.
(Do not leave thermometer in oven while cooking.)
Stir in butter, baking soda and vanilla just until light and bubbly.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Spread. Cool and break into pieces.
Makes 1 1/4 pounds.

title: breaded zucchini
directions: Peel and slice zucchini.
Slice it in rounds about a quarter-inch thick.
Prepare a dish with eggs, salt and pepper and garlic powder.
Add Parmesan cheese, oregano and parsley.
With a fork, beat this into a batter.
Dip the zucchini slices into the egg batter.
Have a dish ready with the bread crumbs.
From the egg batter, dip the zucchini into the bread crumbs.
With a little olive oil in skillet, fry each slice of zucchini, making it a golden brown on each side.
If you have egg batter leftover, you can dip bread and fry, which is very good.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes in salt water until tender.
Drain. Peel, cool and dice.
Place in a 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch greased baking dish.
Melt butter; blend in flour.
Add milk and cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add salt and half the grated cheese.
Stir until cheese melts. Pour this sauce over the potatoes.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 25 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: orange milk drink
directions: Whirl in blender for 20 seconds until smooth.

title: cheese pie
directions: Cook bacon (or sausage); drain.
Mix eggs, milk, cheese and bacon together.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: sweet potato nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Combine Crisco and sugar in large bowl.
Beat at low speed until blended. Increase speed to medium; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well; add sweet potatoes and mix well.
Combine flour, nutmeg, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Add to mixture alternately with water.
Mix well at medium low speed.
Add nuts, vanilla and raisins; spread mixture in loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 60 to 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Layer cooked and boned chicken in baking dish.
Combine soup and broth together and pour over chicken.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes with peels on.
Cool, peel and dice.
Chop onion. Dice and fry bacon.
Add to potatoes with parsley; salt and pepper to taste.
Add sugar, flour and mustard to bacon drippings and blend.
Add vinegar and water; boil until thickened.
Pour over potatoes and serve immediately.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix dry pudding with pineapple. Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well and chill.

title: misaquatash(american indian succotash)
directions: The ancient dish was just beans and corn cooked together with bear fat.
Sometimes meat or fish was added and later salt and pepper.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat at medium speed 1 minute.
Turn into greased 9 x 5-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: sweet and nutty cheese ball
directions: Combine and mix well.
Form into ball and roll in crushed nuts.

title: rice porcupines
directions: Mix ground meat and rice.
Add salt and pepper and form into balls, about 1/2-inch in diameter.
Place in baking dish.
In skillet, saute onions and bell peppers in 1 tablespoon butter. Add tomato sauce.
Season with salt and pepper and pour over meatballs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: elmer's blonde brownies
directions: Combine melted margarine, brown sugar and egg.
Beat well. Sift together remaining ingredients and add to sugar mixture. Blend in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: hamburger and bean casserole
directions: Saute bacon.
Add onion and ground beef.
Stir until browned. Add other ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: praline peanut butter pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Blend filling ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°. Bake 30 to 35 minutes longer.
Filling should appear slightly less set in center than around edge.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Cut in shortening. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add yeast and buttermilk to dry ingredients and stir with a fork to form a soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface and knead briefly.
Store in tightly sealed plastic bag in refrigerator.
Pat dough.
Do not let rise at any time.
Bake at 425° on greased cookie sheet until lightly browned.
Dough lasts a week and yields a dozen biscuits per day.

title: graham cracker fruitcake
directions: Beat eggs and add all ingredients.
Pour into two loaf pans lined with foil and bake at 275° for 45 minutes.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Spread	1
cup Cool Whip in bottom; freeze for about 10 minutes.
Spoon
jam over whipped topping.	Gradually add milk to peanut
butter
in	bowl,
blending.
Add pie filling mix. Beat at low speed until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Fold in rest
of topping.
Spoon
into pie shell.
Freeze until firm. Garnish with additional topping and nuts, if desired.

title: creamy macaroni and cheese
directions: While macaroni cooks to tenderness, make sauce as follows. Melt butter, stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Then add milk slowly.
Add diced cheese and cook at low temperature until cheese melts.
Put drained macaroni into a casserole dish and pour cheese sauce over it.
Top with paprika or Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix marshmallows on low heat along with 1/2 cup of the drained pineapple juice.
Add jello and stir well, let cook, whip the topping mix as directed on package, add cottage cheese, whipped topping and nuts, if desired.
Leave in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: chicken bake
directions: Sprinkle chicken with garlic salt and pepper. Dilute soups with 3/4 cup water; pour in pan on top of rice.
Place chicken on rice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, covered.

title: orange cream jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water & cool until lukewarm.

Beat cream cheese & sugar until smooth. Blend in milk & then add jello. Blend until smooth. Add juice & a few oranges. Mix well then mold over night. Decorate with rest of oranges. Put in a bundt pan. Spray pan with Pam if not coated.

title: onion sourdough bread
directions: Prepare dough starter.
Mix 1 cup flour, sugar, salt and yeast in large bowl.
Mix milk and margarine in saucepan.
Heat over low heat until liquid is very warm (120° to 130°).
Add to dry mix and beat 2 minutes on medium.
Add 1 1/2 cups starter and 1/4 cup flour.
Beat on high 2 minutes.
Stir in more flour to make soft dough.
Turn out on light floured board; knead until smooth and elastic 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and grease top. Cover.
Rise in oven until double (1 hour).
Punch down; turn on floured board.
Divide 1/2.
Cover.
Let rest 15 minutes.
Place on greased sheets sprinkled with cornmeal.
Cover.
Let rise until double (1 hour).
Mix egg white and water.
Brush mixture over loaves.
Top with caraway seed.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on racks

title: pickled refrigerator onion rings
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; strain mixture and discard spices.
Pour strained hot mixture over onions.
Cover and chill overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix together sugar and flour; add eggs, butter, pecans, chocolate bits (melted) and vanilla.
Pour into frozen pie crust and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Best served slightly warm with whipped cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: butterfinger pie
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Fold in whipping topping.
Crush candy bars; fold 1 cup into cream cheese mixture.
Spoon into crust.	Sprinkle the rest of candy crumbs on top of pie.
Refrigerate 2 to 4 hours before slicing.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Boil sugar, butter, milk, cocoa and vanilla for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter and oats.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let set to cool and firm.

title: chili con queso
directions: Boil ingredients 3 to 4 hours until very soft.
Add savor salt, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
When mixture is completely blended, add 1 can chopped green chili and cheese.
Let cheese melt.
Keep warm.
Serve as a dip or over rice or chicken or scrambled eggs. Can be frozen.

title: daphne's chocolate pie
directions: Mix together the sugar and flour.
Add the milk and cook in double boiler until thick, about 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and add beaten egg yolks.
Mix cocoa with enough boiling water to make a paste.
Add paste to mixture in double boiler.
Return to heat and cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla. Cool and pour in baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Brown in 325° oven.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flavoring until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat.
Continue beating at high speed for 10 minutes.
Fold in flour (do not beat).
Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: corn bread or muffins
directions: Beat the eggs thoroughly. Add the milk and melted butter. Sift together the flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt and add the first mixture. Bake at 375° about 25 minutes.

title: chinese spinach
directions: Cut fresh spinach stems into 1-inch pieces; tear leaves into bite-size pieces.
Cook spinach.
Drain well.
Heat oil, sugar and soy sauce in skillet; add spinach, water chestnuts and onion. Cook, tossing lightly, for 2 to 3 minutes or until spinach is coated and heated.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Sort and wash cranberries.
Wash orange and apple.
Cut orange in sections; leave peeling on.
Section apple and core.
Do not peel.
Put all through food grinder.
Add pineapple and sugar.
Put in covered container.
Keep in refrigerator.
It keeps a long time. Age enhances the taste.

title: polish sausage
directions: Slice sausage into 1/2-inch slices. Mix all ingredients, cover and simmer 1 hour.
Uncover and cook (simmer) 30 minutes.
Let set 24 hours before serving.

title: miniature ham quiche
directions: Let cream cheese and butter soften at room temperature; blend together.
Stir in flour.
Roll in a ball and chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Shape into muffin tins like pie crust. (Do not grease tins.)

title: onion rings
directions: In medium bowl, combine 1 1/2 cup flour, paprika, salt and baking powder.
With wire wisk, stir in beer until batter is fairly smooth.
Set batter aside.
Cut onions across into 1/3-inch thick slices and separate into rings.
Put remaining flour in plastic bag.
Heat 2 inches of oil to 375°.
Drop handful of onion rings into plastic bag and toss until coated.
Dip floured rings into batter and fry handful of rings in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: fresh orange chicken
directions: Season chicken well with salt and pepper. Saut in butter over medium heat until golden brown on all sides. Add onions and saut until soft. Transfer to shallow baking pan. Cover with mixture of orange peel, orange juice and wine. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes or until tender, turning during baking. Place chicken on serving platter. Keep warm.

title: banana oatmeal muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg and buttermilk. Mix together oats, flour, baking soda, salt and allspice. Add to creamed mixture and stir in bananas. Spoon into greased muffin pans or papers 2/3 full. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 12.

title: cracked black pepper rice
directions: Wash and drain rice.
Bring water, lemon juice, 1/2 teaspoon butter and bay leaf to a full boil in a large pan over high heat. Stirring constantly, pour in rice in a slow stream.
Cook, uncovered, in briskly boiling water 12 to 15 minutes or until rice is just tender and fluffy.
Turn rice into a strainer and drain. Let cool 1 to 2 minutes.
Pick out bay leaf and spoon rice onto a serving platter.
Stir in remaining butter, salt and black pepper. Toss gently to mix.
Chill or let cool to room temperature. Garnish with citrus wedges.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: soulful souse
directions: Clean thoroughly and place hog jowl, pig's ears and pig's feet in a very large pot (8 to 10 quarts).
Add water to cover and bring to a boil.
Lower flame and skim surface until clear.
Add remaining ingredients and let simmer for 3 to 4 hours or until the meat can be easily removed from the bones.
While still warm, remove bones from broth and meat.
Cut meat into small pieces. Season souse with salt, black pepper, vinegar and crushed hot pepper.
Add some stock, then place in a mold. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight. Unmold, slice and serve as cold cuts or cut into fingers also as an appetizer.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients until thick; then add 1/3 stick butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring.
Pour over favorite crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar to each egg white. Pour over mixture and brown.

title: brenda's meatloaf
directions: Mix ground beef with milk and rice; blend well and shape into a loaf. Place loaf in a greased casserole dish. Pour water over top. Bake at 350° for 45 - 60 minutes.

title: modern version - italian wedding soup
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and form into TINY meatballs, about 1/2 inch in diameter.
Bring the 6 cups of well-seasoned chicken broth to a slow boil in a 3-qt.
Pan.
(Can use three 14 oz. cans broth and season with onion powder, garlic powder, celery salt, salt & pepper to taste.)
Add meatballs and cook until done. Remove meatballs with slotted spoon.
Add the riso (pasta) and cook till almost done, about 5 min.
Add the cut up bok choy, escarole, or spinach.
If using bok choy, add the cut up white part a couple minutes earlier; then add the cut up green part for just a minute or two until wilted.
Add the meatballs back to the soup pot, heat and serve.
You can add 1 - 2 Tbsp more of grated cheese to the finished soup.
It is the secret to the flavor.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef and drain. Add the rest of ingredients and bring to boil. Cook on medium heat until vegetables are done.

title: nut cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add vanilla.
Measure all the other ingredients in the sugar box.
Bake in tube pan for 2 hours at 300°.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook all vegetables in large pot of water about 20 minutes or until tender.
In same pot, add water and milk, salt and pepper; thicken with flour mixed with water to form paste.
Stir in soup mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Stir often and watch so won't boil over.
A dash of hot sauce is good also.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Combine egg, onion, soup and mayonnaise.
Place layer of broccoli, cheese and sauce.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Drizzle butter on top.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: custard
directions: Stir until sugar is dissolved. Put in casserole dish. Sprinkle nutmeg over top. Set casserole in pan with 2-inches of water. Bake
medium heat at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: stir fry supreme(makes one serving.)
directions: Rice should be prepared according to package instructions so that it is ready when Wok cooking is finished. Limit amount of salt used in rice since soy sauce also contains salt. Note, Wok cooking is done at high heat. Pour cooking oil into Wok. Turn to high heat setting. While heating, swirl oil around bottom and lower sides of Wok to coat it. When oil is hot, pour in onions and garlic. Stir for 1 to 2 minutes. Place onions and garlic in a nearby bowl or plate. Pour about 1 tsp. soy sauce into Wok and immediately add meat. Stir for 1 to 2 minutes or until meat is lightly browned throughout. Once done, place meat in a nearby bowl or plate. Using caution, slowly, pour 1/4 to 1/3 cup of water down sides of Wok. Add other vegetables to Wok. Quickly stir them in the water, then situate vegetables along side of Wok and out of the water. Cover Wok and let vegetables steam for 2 to 3 minutes. Vegetables should retain some of their "crunchiness". Once steaming is complete, immediately add meat, onions, and garlic to the vegetables in the Wok. You may add more soy sauce if desired. Stir the entire contents for approximately 1/2 to 1 minute. Place in serving bowl, and serve over plate of brown rice. Sprinkle noodles on top.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, powdered sugar and margarine.
Add oil, vanilla and eggs; mix well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir dry ingredients into sugar mixture; chill overnight. Shape dough into 1 inch balls.
Flatten with glass dipped in water and then in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° until light brown, 6 to 8 minutes.
May be decorated with colored sugar.

title: black beans
directions: Cook until tender.
Add additional water if necessary.
Add 4 teaspoons of salt or less, according to taste.

title: bernadine's coffee cake
directions: Mix the flour, sugars, salt, nutmeg and oil well and take out 3/4 cup of the mixture and reserve for the topping.
To remaining mixture add egg, sour milk or buttermilk, soda and baking powder. Mix well until all lumps are dissolved.
Spread in a fairly shallow pan, greased and floured.
Sprinkle with topping, then with cinnamon and chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Bake at 350° for approximately 12 minutes on a cookie sheet.

title: chicken divan
directions: Precook chicken.
Bone.
Remove skin.
Place in oiled casserole over uncooked broccoli.
Mix soup, seasonings, mayonnaise, cheese and 1/4 cup cooking liquid and place on top. Top with bread crumbs which have been mixed with melted margarine. Bake at 375° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: pork tenderloin with dill sauce
directions: Trim all visible fat and cut each tenderloin into 6 pieces crosswise.
Flatten each piece to 1/2-inch in a large frying pan. Cook mushrooms in margarine over medium heat for 3 minutes, covered.
Then 3 more minutes, uncovered.
Drain liquid.
Remove mushrooms, cover and reserve.

title: tuna chips casserole
directions: Mix drained tuna with undiluted soup, milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Microwave 4 to 5 minutes on High power.
Sprinkle cheese and potato chips on top of hot casserole.
Serves 4.

title: chinese slaw
directions: Brown almonds and seeds.
Break noodles and bake on cookie sheet 15 minutes at 250°.
Mix cabbage, broccoli and onions in a bowl.
Add noodles, almonds and seeds.

title: peach cobbler pie
directions: Heat peaches until boiling.
Remove from heat and add 1 cup of sugar.
Melt
butter
in large pan you can cook pie in. Stir together
flour,
sugar,
baking
powder, salt and milk. Pour batter
into pan with butter after it has cooled slightly and spread,
but
do
not
stir.
Then pour hot sweet fruit on top. DO
NOT
STIR!
Bake at 425° until golden brown. Can use any juicy fruit or cherries.

title: spiced tea
directions: Steep tea and cloves in the 6 cups of water for 20 minutes. Add the remaining ingredients.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add melted oleo, egg yolks and milk. Stir until smooth.
Add lemon juice and grated rind.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake for 25 minutes or until done.

title: green potatoes(6 servings)
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Butter skins and make shallow slits around the middle as if you were cutting the potatoes in half lengthwise. Bake at 400° until done.

title: microwave baked apple
directions: Core apples and make a slit in skin all around the middle of each apple to prevent skin from bursting.
Place apples in small microproof baking dish.
In small bowl, melt butter on High 10 seconds.
Stir in sugar, cinnamon and raisins.
Fill each apple with sugar mixture.
Add water to dish.
Cook, covered, with plastic wrap on High for 4 to 5 minutes.

title: sausage soup
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add water to cover.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and parsley.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: pineapple chicken stir fry
directions: Cut chicken into 1/8 inch slices.
In bowl, stir chicken, soy sauce, sherry, and ginger.
In skillet over medium high heat, cook vegetables in hot oil until tender, stirring frequently.
Return vegetables to skillet and add pineapple with syrup, vinegar, and salt.
Stir water and cornstarch in a cup; add to skillet and cook until sauce is thickened and smooth, stirring constantly.
Makes 4 main dish servings; 360 calories per serving.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Cook the carrots until tender in salted water; drain.
Add the butter and mash the mixture (easier to mash in a blender or food processor).
Mix together the sugar, flour, baking powder, vanilla and eggs.
Add to the carrots and blend well.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: liver pate
directions: Combine sour cream and dry onion soup mix.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Beat cream cheese with steak sauce and Tabasco.
Add sour cream and mix.
Add chicken livers and liver sausage.
Beat in blender.
Chill.
May be frozen.

title: quick and easy chicken
directions: Salt chicken.
Melt butter with garlic salt.
Dip each breast in the mixture.
Roll in crumbs and place in lightly greased shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: creamy first-down fudge(makes about 2 pounds)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line 9-inch square pan with aluminum foil.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press firmly on bottom of prepared pan.
Bake 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: easy spinach salad
directions: Remove stems from spinach.
Wash leaves thoroughly and pat dry.
Tear into bite-size pieces.
Combine spinach, oranges and almonds in large bowl.
Serve with salad dressing.

title: rosa's king ranch chicken
directions: Saute onion and pepper until soft.
Mix all soups, onion, chicken (which have been cut into bite-size pieces) and cheese together and layer tortillas and mixture in 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Top with cheese and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
This may be made ahead and refrigerated overnight.

title: western baked beans
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Put in crock-pot; cook slowly for 1/2 day.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onions, drain.
Layer in casserole dish the meat and soups.
Top with layer of cheese and then top layer of tater tots.
Sprinkle a little cheese across the top of tater tots.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crabmeat surprise
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions.
Stir milk into soup.
In a greased 2-quart casserole, layer ingredients in the following order:
stuffing, broccoli, crabmeat and soup. Cover and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Remove cover and continue baking for another 1/2 hour.
Spread cheese on top and bake another 5 to 10 minutes.

title: slaw
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Let stand 3 to 4 hours.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Mix all with electric mixer very slow but well.
Bake in greased tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Don't preheat oven.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground turkey with onions, add remaining ingredients simmer until brown sugar has dissolved.
Serve on open-faced hamburger buns.

title: easy potato casserole
directions: Put potatoes in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Melt margarine in a saucepan.
Add sour cream, soup and onions.
Spread over potatoes and mix with a fork.
Sprinkle paprika over the top; cover with the Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: 12 minute fowl
directions: Heat a cast- iron skillet until very hot (smoking).
Add olive oil, then immediately add the chicken and onion.
Season.
Stir-fry until chicken is brown.
Add water and cover for 1 minute (to steam the meat).
Ready to eat.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook shredded or chopped small cabbage head until tender. Drain.
Season with butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Combine chicken soup and water.
Stir until smooth.
Alternate layers of herb-seasoned stuffing mix and cabbage in greased baking dish. Pour soup mixture over.
Top with dressing mix.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: orzo
directions: Cook orzo macaroni as directed and rinse.
Cook eggs, sugar, salt and flour with pineapple juice until slightly thickened.
Add the macaroni and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, fold in fruit and Cool Whip.

title: elaine's fruit dip
directions: Mix together the vanilla pudding mix and the juice.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool completely.
Beat until fluffy.
Stir in 8 ounces "Cool Whip".
Refrigerate.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mash together all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 30-40 minutes or until bubbly and golden brown.

title: hatteras crab cakes
directions: Soak bread in milk and egg mixed together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Make into patties. Fry until brown.

title: prune velvet cake
directions: Measure prunes whole, then remove pits and slice fine.
Cream butter and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add egg yolks and beat until creamy. Add milk alternately with flour sifted with salt, baking powder and soda and beat well.
Add prunes and flavorings.
Stir until well blended.

title: potato latkes or potato pancakes
directions: In a large bowl, blend grated potatoes and onion; stir in beaten eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Heat oil in frypan.
Drop potato mixture in by tablespoonful.
You may press cakes with spatula.
Cook until golden brown and crusty on both sides.
Drain on paper towels. Serve with bacon, applesauce or ham.
Serves 6.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and rinse your macaroni.
Boil eggs.
In large bowl combine onion and pepper; add in macaroni, eggs and Miracle Whip. Add black pepper to taste.

title: melting moments
directions: Stir together flour, cornstarch and sugar.
In a large mixing bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat the margarine until smooth and fluffy.
Add flour mixture and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet about 1 1/2 inches apart.
Flatten with two fingers.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix brown sugar, margarine and egg; stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, 10 to 12 minutes. Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Cool slightly.
Frost if desired.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Combine milk and sugar in heavy saucepan.
Beat yolks in small bowl until smooth.
Add to milk and sugar when mixture is just warm.
Bring to boil and cook, stirring constantly until thick. Remove from heat and beat until.
Add coconut and pecans and frost top of each layer of German chocolate cake.

title: spicy meatballs
directions: Mix and make meatballs.
Cook meatballs like you would a hamburger, then cover with sauce.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place stick of butter in a 13 x 9-inch oblong baking pan and melt.
In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar and milk; mix well.
Heat peaches, sugar and cinnamon.
Pour batter of butter; pour fruit over batter.
Cook until golden brown.
